{"Author": "Amazon Addict!", "Date": "on July 31, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "System needs more and better options", "Text": "Just took away a star. Got my dimmer/bulb kit today and as I installed and configured it i was reminded of some of what I consider sugnificant short comings of this whole sytem.\nFor those who want a basic smart light system, Philips Hue is a good choice. For those of us who want more control, not so much.\nFirst, you can't install anything until you set up at least one room.\nSecond, as you set up scenes, you cannot remove bulbs in a room from a scene. You can turn unwanted bulbs off in a scene, but then whenever you execute that scene those other bulbs will go off even if that was not your desire. Example: I now have 5 Hue bulbs in my bedroom. One in my nightstand; one in a wall fixture and three in the ceiling fan fixture. If I have the nightstand and the wall lights on and decide to turn the ceiling fan lights on, the other lights go off.\nThird, no facility in Hue to set up groups - only rooms - and bulbs cannot exist in more than one room.\nPhilips, please address these limitations."}
{"Author": "Paul Dupuie", "Date": "on July 31, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My young grandson hate it.", "Text": "My grandson is sooo old fashioned young man. He don't like the idea of having the smart lights in the house so he shut everything off on purpose. What he don't realized and don't give a damn about his own grandmother safely at night. Now, it sitting in the closet collecting dust."}
{"Author": "RC SuperFreak", "Date": "on July 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to get linked", "Text": "Easy to get linked, took me a bit to get everything setup and working with easy voice commands. Absolutely in love with my on-going smart house project, these are at the heart of it.\n\neasy voice command for on/off, and dim-able, setting up groups is a must"}
{"Author": "Alyson R", "Date": "on July 29, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love these. The programming is so much better than using older timer technology."}
{"Author": "Troy Glidden", "Date": "on July 28, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic!", "Text": "I purchased this starter pack (required, as you need the hub if you want to get these to work with Alexa) from the Treasure Truck recently and discovered my love and need for internet-connected lights! These things are great for all kinds of uses, and I have even purchased additional bulbs since purchasing this starter pack.\n\nFirst off, these lights are not WET RATED, but I have taken the risk of putting them in each of my porch lights. So far my experience has been good, but it has rained very little since install. Using the Hue app, I was able to set the lights to automatically turn on at sunset and off at sunrise, which is something I struggle with. I remember to turn the porch lights on at bed, but forget to turn them off when I wake. These do it for me, which is great.\n\nI also placed on in my hallway to use as a nightlight. The brightness can adjust from 1% - 100% from the app or via Alexa, and it's a great night light replacement. My kids prefer this light over a traditional nightlight due to the light that it emits over an entire area versus a small area against a wall.\n\nThe lights are soft white, so not overpowering, but they're pretty bright. They look great on the porches and are a great addition to my smart home.\n\nThe setup of the hub is easy, and it's even easier to set it up with Alexa! It's easy to then control your lights from your phone, through Alexa, and even Xfinity Home application if you have Home Security."}
{"Author": "Kumar", "Date": "on July 28, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product", "Text": "Great product"}
{"Author": "Gary Lopez", "Date": "on July 27, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it", "Text": "I like it but some times it glitch out using the home kit on the iPhone but it\u2019s nice"}
{"Author": "Harry Hur", "Date": "on July 27, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible UX.", "Text": "okay. updating software disconnected me from alexa. and I always have to go through IFFT for activating HUE bulbs. Terrible UX."}
{"Author": "Jason C.", "Date": "on July 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I Feel Lazier Already!", "Text": "I will admit, I was a skeptic of the whole \"smart home\" thing. I've had a google home for a while now and never really used it to it's full potential. With this kit though, I took large step towards achieving that. Set up for this only took about 25 mins and then google was turning on/off my lights whenever I asked. The app for your phone is great and easy to use. You can also add several other lights after you set this up. I have it controlling my living room lights and my bedroom lights."}
{"Author": "Thomas Rivington", "Date": "on July 26, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I'm addicted to these bulbs and pairing them with my Echo."}
{"Author": "Surprise Oma", "Date": "on July 26, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Total scam for consumer support. Only offers support for companies.", "Text": "What a scam. If you try to go to the Philips Hues Website and contact support, as soon as you change it from Company to person, the form remains, but the send button disappears.\n\nPurchased the A19 two bulb starter kit. Installed them in two identical lamps on either side of the bed. Showed my husband how to work his. He thought the light was brighter than what we used to have in there so he asked if it could be dimmed. We tried Alexa at all percentages from 10-90. Unless you had it at 100% it flickers. I assumed it was just the bulb. But tonight Alexa was having issue so I went to the Hue app to turn off my light and I found the three scenes - night light - dimmer and normal. I turned on night light and looking at the lamp on my side of the bed it was lovely. But turned my head to see my husbands side and he has the flicker. So apparently it\u2019s just his bulb that is defective.\n\nI went to manufacturer to ask the question and see about replacing the defective bulb since I really don\u2019t want to return the entire kit I purchased with the Echo Dot and Bridge that I\u2019ve already setup."}
{"Author": "Samuel", "Date": "on July 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great!", "Text": "Works great! Very easy to set up and control from the app as well as using Alexa."}
{"Author": "dhanraj mohabir", "Date": "on July 25, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Color", "Text": "Not white, its yellow.\n\nAlso packaging looking like it has been opened before but it say new."}
{"Author": "FavoinoA", "Date": "on July 24, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "so much for amazon claiming a product is like new or very good", "Text": "i purchased this as a warehouse deal a number of months ago, but unfortunately didn't go to use it until now only to discover that someone had swapped the hub with a different ones and therefore the numbers didn't match and the hub wouldn't even turn on. so much for amazon claiming a product is like new or very good, i thought they were supposed to check things like that."}
