{"Author": "Charles Brawner", "Date": "on June 15, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I happily use Insteon now", "Text": "I purchased this and within a year both bulbs malfunctioned. Lights would turn on and off unexpectedly. Philips accused me of using dimmable controlled fixtures, I didn't. One was ceiling fan and one was old floor lamp made before dimmers were available. Philips would not help me. I happily use Insteon now."}
{"Author": "Yass", "Date": "on June 14, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Total control over the lights.", "Text": "This is the second set of Philips Hue lights I buy. I love the control I get with them, whether using the Philips Hue App, Alexa or Siri, I can control each independent bulb, the light intensity, etc.\n\nOne thing to mention, these are NOT white as the name indicates. These are yellowish lights. If you want a white light (or something closer looking to a true white) you'll need the color bulb which can be adjusted to white.\n\nOther than this, I love everything about them."}
