{"Author": "Tech Reviews", "Date": "on April 20, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If you're going Hue get colors, else get logic built into the light switch", "Text": "I cannot recommend these when competitors have the brains in the switch instead of the bulb. Philips Hue is best for colors, I took my white ones out and they live in the box now."}
{"Author": "Darkcar", "Date": "on April 20, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love being able to say light on light off!!", "Text": "We got these to be able to say on and off for all the lights in the house. Works great !!!"}
{"Author": "Gift of Heart", "Date": "on April 20, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So convenient!", "Text": "Our very first smart bulbs! They were easy to set up and the app is easy to use. I had problems with the bulbs not turning off under \"routines\". I noticed it's best not to change the routine time but simply add a new routine and delete the old one. That did the trick. It's probably just a bug they need to work through in the app. Love that we no longer come home to a dark house!"}
{"Author": "Rod", "Date": "on April 19, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Connected this to my google home and it worked well!"}
{"Author": "Dave P", "Date": "on April 19, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The Philips Hue Smart Hub Works Great", "Text": "I wanted a hub to tie in with my Alexa devices. The Philips Hue hub was easy to setup and manage devices with the Hue app. If you want to manage it with your Alexa devices, you will need to go into the Skills area of the Alexa app and download the Philips Hue skill. This will enable you to add the bulbs into the Alexa app when they can then be managed via the app or via voice command."}
{"Author": "Joe L. Givens", "Date": "on April 19, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Useless in a Power or Internet Blip!", "Text": "Here is the biggest problem with this, if you are using the system in a home where you only go to once a month and there is a internet blip, or power failure, there is NO WAY to reset the bridge remotely!!!! Totally useless and ridiculous! Since the power to all the lights has to be on, whether it is a wall switch or lamp switch, it means the lights will be on and stay on 24/7 until you can go back and manually reset! An inexpensive timer can work better!!!!"}
{"Author": "Robert", "Date": "on April 19, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great after you get it going", "Text": "One of the bulbs died immediately. The other 3 work perfectly with Alexa so it's great. Be wary that these can dim only if a dimmer switch hasn't already been installed. I had a dimmer switch previously so I just swapped it out before I used this product. Also this is not a multicolor lighting experience. This just satisfies that itch for telling someone else to turn off the lights for you."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 18, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good idea however", "Text": "Good idea however, bridge constantly fails network connection and associated app is just as bad. It worked successfully for 1 week and then began suffering intermittent failures. Online blogs, support feedback, and customer reviews are all unanswered and ignored. If bridge fails, enjoy having now paid a massive premium for regular bulbs because you will unfortunately get no help and no resolution."}
{"Author": "Kathleen Bowman", "Date": "on April 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "works great with Alexi!"}
{"Author": "Kindle Customer", "Date": "on April 16, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't buy this unless you just need bulbs", "Text": "I bought the kit because it was supposed to be easy to set up and I don't have one of these but I need a light that comes on by itself at a certain time.\n\nI plugged in the lights and bridge, turned them on, installed the app, and tried to connect to the bridge. The app found the bridge, then said there was an update available, and then no matter what I do it won't update. Tried following various troubleshooting guides that involve turning everything off and on repeatedly, nothing works.\n\nI ended up finding something online that outlined my exact problem and tried following instructions about how to force it to update but the instructions are apparently outdated, and the hue website has deleted the help page for it.\n\nThe makers of this device deleted the help page that would get it to work... let that sink in...\n\nI can't use the app or the bridge because the bridge won't update, and there's no way to get it to work without contacting tech support.\n\nI work all week during business hours and I'm supposed to take hours off work to come home and set this up?\n\nWhy couldn't you make an app or bridge or both that works without the update? Why can't you make it update without me having to update it?\n\nThere are any number of ways this could be fixed in less than a half hour by the company that makes this, but apparently they want to be able to jerk people through hoops and make them sit on the phone to get help instead of providing a product that works out of the box."}
{"Author": "billiebobber", "Date": "on April 16, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Must have with Alexa.", "Text": "Works Great. Can read at night, then tell Alexa to turn off with out having to get out of bed. Like the dimmer feature also."}
