{"Author": "Chalayne M.", "Date": "on March 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Never have to get up and flip the switch again.", "Text": "We LOVE these - in fact, we are now trying to convert everything in our house over now that we have them integrated with the HomePod."}
{"Author": "James McBee", "Date": "on March 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't just light your home, illuminate it.", "Text": "If clothing makes the man, well, lighting makes the home. For many years, I have preached that. Be environmentally friendly! Chose light temperatures (colors) that are relaxing and pleasing. And, yet, somehow I survived the horrors of florescent lights and compact florescent lights. Lights in the 2000K to 3000K range are considered \"warm white\" and much like what we had with old-school incandescent lights. Personally, I consider 2700K to be a good light color for my home.\n\nPhilips has warmed the cockles of my heart. In a \"playing-with-home-automation\" binge, I ordered this starter kit. I wanted something that would integrate well with other home automation systems and would be expandable.\n\nThis was easy to set up. The hub can control up to 50 Philips light bulbs. Each can be programmed with different scenes, on / off times, randomization, and brightness levels. A few hours after opening the box and playing with this, I had ordered 4 more sets for friends and family members. They all love these, too. And, I ordered some color bulbs as well.\n\nThe color temperature for these lights is pleasing and comfortable. The features are excellent. I'm very pleased with this purchase."}
{"Author": "Ms Pat", "Date": "on March 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best of the best", "Text": "You just have to have a smart light kit. I use with my Alexa also. Just set the time and you're done."}
{"Author": "BambiHands", "Date": "on March 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This system is very easy to set up and really convenient", "Text": "This system is very easy to set up and really convenient. I have these bulbs set up to be operated through my Amazon Alexa for my bedroom and dining room. There's nothing like realizing you forgot to turn off the light in the other room before you go to bed, then remember you can just say \"Alexa, turn off the dining room light\" and having the light smoothly dim to off in less than a second."}
