{"Author": "Cindy", "Date": "on February 21, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not a nice bright white light", "Text": "These say white bulbs but they are that old dirty brown color that incandescents used to be. I pulled out some nice bright white bulbs in order to use the connected feature and I hate the dirty light these put out. If you like that 'warm' color these may be for you but I want a nice bright light and these are not it.\n\nAlso, despite this being a wi-fi system you will need to hardwire the bridge to your router/modem and find a power outlet for it near the router, and then hope everything communicates through walls, That said mine does communicate and it works well with my Cortana Invoke. Mostly I hate the light and found it to be more of a pain to install than expected."}
