{"Author": "jonathan quezada", "Date": "on February 6, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Thats where these bad boys come in", "Text": "Bought these along with alexa and so far im loving them. When im lying in bed about to go to sleep i dont want to get up and turn off a lamp. Thats where these bad boys come in. With the app of alexa you can sit comfy in your bed and turn off your lights like that. Plus the dimming feature is also very handy. Overall 5/5"}
{"Author": "Caitlyn S.", "Date": "on February 6, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I can easily say this is the best purchase we've made to ...", "Text": "i bought this kit after buying the two-pack of just bulbs, not knowing I would need the \"bridge\". Once we got everything set up and linked with our Echo Dot, I can easily say this is the best purchase we've made to compliment the Echo. You can tell Alexa to dim the living room lights to 20% if you're watching a movie and down the lights go! it's awesome! my husband has even requested the color bulbs for his man-cave!"}
{"Author": "aks", "Date": "on February 6, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Needs more R&D before it's ready for market", "Text": "I've had two of these bulbs for 6 months now. At first worked great but recently none of the \"routines\" (what they call schedules) work properly; they don't turn the bulbs on or off at the designated times. I can still use the app to switch them on and off manually, but that's not really why I bought the things. Needs more R&D before it's ready for market."}
{"Author": "lisa blank", "Date": "on February 6, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "easy set up", "Text": "easy to set up and great to use - you can dim the lights without installing a dimmer"}
{"Author": "Alec J. Yetter", "Date": "on February 6, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome when it works, which is rare.", "Text": "The app changes the bulb names and disconnects the hub at random intervals. I need to work on this thing all over every day. It sucks with Alexa, who can\u2019t find the lights. Unserviceable. Terrible customer support.\n\nIt\u2019s very cool when it works, which is not often."}
{"Author": "Avboden", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great starter kit!", "Text": "Overall this is a great kit to get you started in the smart-home lighting realm. The 4 bulbs are fully dimmable via most controls (apple's siri, amazon alexa, google home, etc) and are a nice tint. THESE ARE NOT THE COLORED BULBS, these are white only. They are a slightly yellow tinged light so nice and warm."}
{"Author": "KW", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great when it works - Just never move!", "Text": "It was great when I first set it up; however when I moved to a new house the device REFUSED to work no matter what. I tried a Factory Reset and that didn't do anything. The 'App' would show that it found the device but wouldn't get past the part when you press the button on the device to finish the setup.\n\n$60 completely down the drain for NO REASON AT ALL.\n\nThere's NO FORM OF MANUALLY CONNECTING either! I was literally putting the IP address into the App but since, for whatever reason, when I hit the button on the Hue Base Station it WOULD NOT ACCEPT IT.\n\nI ended up going Office Space on it because it was so frustrating!! What a horrible product design! NEVER MOVE!"}
{"Author": "HankMI", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Beware!", "Text": "If you have satellite internet service none of the Hue products will work. You will be able to turn the lights on and off using the Hue app but scheduling them to go on and off automatically will not work. Something Philips fails to mention."}
{"Author": "JR", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The connection with the bridge is very finicky. I've ...", "Text": "The connection with the bridge is very finicky. I've had to do a hard reset on the bridge and router twice in 2 months."}
{"Author": "layzboy1986", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "But since I got a good deal on this", "Text": "At the end of the day I would have rather replaced the light switches. But since I got a good deal on this, this is a great way to get into a smart home with out alot of risk. Plus these system works with all virtual assistants, google, apple and amazon."}
{"Author": "Sheldon", "Date": "on February 5, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Works as advertised, nothing wrong with the product."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 4, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works well. Enable skill in Alexa. Expensive though ...", "Text": "Works well. Enable skill in Alexa. Expensive though."}
{"Author": "BarnsOfFDR", "Date": "on February 4, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "A nice convenience! Sometimes glitchy but still nice", "Text": "A nice convenience! Sometimes glitchy but still nice."}
{"Author": "Tyler L", "Date": "on February 3, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Wish I could enjoy it", "Text": "Unfortunately, I have not been able to enjoy this device properly. I purchased two bulbs at a local retail store to just try out the well-known Philips Hue bulbs. I was under the impression that all I needed was some sort of smart hub to control the bulbs. I was surprised to see that a separate hub, Hue Bridge, was required and immediately order this starter kit. I did not read any of the requirements and just purchased it due to wanting to enjoy controlling my lights with my voice and IFTTT.\n\nWhen the kit arrived, I was surprised again to notice that the Hue Bridge requires an ethernet cable that needs to be connected to a router due to the Hue Bridge not having it's own wireless system. Due to the area that I live in, my home WiFi consists of protable Mifi cards through my phone service. This was a huge disappointment and entirely my fault. I have seen reviews and hints that you can attach a router without internet and it will work fine through the app but I have no figured it out. I was able to get the system to work briefly by turning my laptop into a wireless router and attaching the router to my laptop and attaching the Hue Bridge to my router...it sounds terrible but worked briefly. For those few moments of the system working, it worked relatively well. I have since ordered a device that will receive wireless connection through an ethernet cable and will update this review once it is working.\n\nUpdate: I found a system that allows it to function with wireless only. This system works flawlessly. I love being able to turn off all the lights in my house with just my voice/app. I would recommend it to anyone if they asked."}
{"Author": "Jonathan", "Date": "on February 3, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "it's easy to use and functions fine for now", "Text": "Had to get a replacement because one of the bulbs couldn't be recognized a few days after everything was setup. Followed troubleshooting guide on the Philips Hue website with no results. Sent a message to Philips using their online contact form. Never heard from them. Contacted Amazon and was provided a replacement. Aside from that headache, it's easy to use and functions fine for now."}
{"Author": "Veekay8", "Date": "on February 3, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very easy to install... first step to an automated home"}
{"Author": "Jose Leal", "Date": "on February 2, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great"}
{"Author": "Stephen", "Date": "on February 2, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very nice and well made bulbs,", "Text": "Love these bulbs, just re-ordered another set to finish up the rest of the house. They work well indoors as well in outdoor closed light fixtures,\n(at least in CA weather)."}
{"Author": "Rene Coderre", "Date": "on February 2, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It has been a lot of fun and a lot easier to turn of some lights ...", "Text": "This product has been working as advertised. It has been a lot of fun and a lot easier to turn of some lights behind furniture. I have enjoyed using them."}
{"Author": "scott a wendell", "Date": "on February 1, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best Dimmable Lights Out There", "Text": "Ordered a couple cheap colored LED bulbs before switching to Phillips Hue. I prefer to have the hub at my house interacting with Alexa, rather than relying on severs in China like the other cheaper bulbs use. Great purchase for the hub and will look into buying other separate bulbs. You get what you pay for!"}
{"Author": "Alina", "Date": "on February 1, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Try something else", "Text": "It works intermittently and super frustrating. Constant updates I would try a different smart build"}
{"Author": "T. Marble", "Date": "on February 1, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easily the best \"Smart Home\" purchase.", "Text": "Works fantastic. I have these in the main rooms, bedroom, and front door light. Works great with Siri and Alexa (I use both). Quick to set up, and easily set up automations based on your schedule. no more flipping lights on and off, and I can have lights turn on and off throughout the day as a robbery deterrent. Highly recommend."}
{"Author": "Dino", "Date": "on February 1, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent starter pack of wifi bulbs", "Text": "Set a few bulbs up on timers in my living room lamps and one on my porch light. I come home to a lit house and they turn themselves off. Work flawlessly. Color is warm just like an incandescent, dims no problem."}
{"Author": "Miguel", "Date": "on January 31, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Expensive", "Text": "I like the product, but the price is just too of a turn-off. Besides changing the \u201cscene\u201d of the room, there is not much you can do. (Atleast with the Official Phillips Hue app."}
{"Author": "BCIM", "Date": "on January 31, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great", "Text": "This set works great so far, we are very happy that they connected to the internet immediately and work great. We had a lifx bulb that never connected to internet and were interested to give another brand a try and are happy we did"}
{"Author": "Christopher Ament", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but not too bad..", "Text": "These work as advertised. You need the little Hue \"bridge\" and then it can support around 25 lightbulbs. It gets kinda complicated if you setting up alot of rooms and lights because you have to assign the lights to a room, but not too bad.."}
{"Author": "Nick Carter", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Screws in like and other light bulb", "Text": "Screws in like and other light bulb, takes minimal effort to set up and Google Mini works just fine with it."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "At any distance from bridge bulb does not function"}
{"Author": "Paul Bohannon", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "nice", "Text": "Reliable dealer, nice product"}
{"Author": "dpolk", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No-Brainer Starter Kit", "Text": "This smart bulb system is a must. It completely transformed my small apartment. Philips does a great job of making it easy to set up and easy to use for the best (and priciest) in the smart bulb. The hub can be uses across all of Philips smart bulbs/lamps. Works great with Alexa and Siri. I think it's worth the extra cost to have a quality product, mobile app, and customer service. Wouldn't highly recommend. I 've already expanded mine beyond this great little starter kit."}
{"Author": "gary", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "worked great with alexa home"}
{"Author": "W.Marz", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No need to get up and turn off the light", "Text": "I'm one of those people that leave the lights on until right before I get tired enough to fall asleep. It used to annoy me that I would have to get up from a comfortable position to turn off the light and then get comfortable again. Now I can ask Alexa to turn off the lights for me or manage it via my phone. If you're a light sleeper like I am, I have Alexa use the light as an alarm and the alarm \"goes off\" by turning on the light which wakes me up instantly. It was scary at first but works every time lol."}
{"Author": "Fran Pelletier", "Date": "on January 30, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Amazing !"}
{"Author": "Cristian A Cuevas", "Date": "on January 29, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I\u2019m in love with these smart bulbs. Will be buying the white ambience next!"}
{"Author": "colin", "Date": "on January 29, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Setup sucks. Don't use hue app", "Text": "Setup sucks. Don't use hue app, just use Google home or it won't work. After that, they are very convenient."}
