{"Author": "Richard", "Date": "on January 28, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pros: Work with alexa and wink hub, lights ...", "Text": "Pros: Work with alexa and wink hub, lights are dimmable\n\nCons: Bulbs need to be fairy close to the hub or need a z-wave device half way (works as a repeater)\n\nMy thoughts:"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 28, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pricey and Proprietary", "Text": "They are dimmable, but only one color: can't do warm vs cool light. Setup with Google Home was relatively easy. Replacement bulbs aren't cheap, and only Philips bulbs work with the rest of the system."}
{"Author": "Cristian Araneda Tolosa", "Date": "on January 28, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love this lights and bridge", "Text": "I love this lights and bridge, there are perfect for me and with amazon echo dot and Alexa are the perfect combination. I recommend it especially if you live alone."}
{"Author": "Lyz", "Date": "on January 28, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Alexa makes me lazy", "Text": "My bedroom is now powered by Alexa and I love that I no longer have To get out of bed to turn the lights off"}
{"Author": "Itai Nathaniel", "Date": "on January 28, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart & Siri", "Text": "Not having to use a switch to turn on and off lights in my house was the mission. Philips Hue let me have rules to turn on lights for my pets when it's dark, and because of its HomeKit alliance I can ask Siri to turn the lights on/off."}
{"Author": "Jess", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very Convenient", "Text": "Not having to get up once your in bed...not having to walk back upstairs cause you forgot to turn your lights off....genius!"}
{"Author": "Fer P.", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Perfect product, a must for an intelligent home", "Text": "Love it, now we can control the lights of my front door and the ones outside my garage even when I forget to do it due that you can select sunrise and sunset function. The app is super easy to use and we loved it when we were on vacations due that we also control lights on the inside just like w were at home."}
{"Author": "Jordan F.", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My experience with this product was not a pleasant one ...", "Text": "My experience with this product was not a pleasant one. The lights were flashing whenever they were on which caused so many headaches with me. This left me with two choices. Either replace the dimmer switch, or return the bulbs. I returned the bulbs due to this problem. Also, their were some flaws in the software, for it was really hard for me to set up mine and my sisters on our Alexa's."}
{"Author": "runnerjud", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If you can figure out how to set it up, works like a charm, but expensive way to go.", "Text": "Very, very pricey and you need a hub attached to router. Very user unfriendly connection to Alexa. Wasn't sure which app to download to make it work. Then I found out I could buy wireless plugs for less money that don't require a hub or special expensive light bulbs. They too were difficult to get set up and attached to Alexa. In fact I had to google it (suggested by my daughter) and was able to figure it out that way. Why are instructions on electronics so useless?\n\nOnce I finally got the hub set up and connected to Alexa - works like a charm - I just tell Alexa to turn on or off lamps in a certain room or all lamps."}
{"Author": "J.Scott 6", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Paired to Amazon ECHO", "Text": "Easy to set up with Amazon ECHO"}
{"Author": "Nate", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Simple and easy to use.", "Text": "Super well designed app and hub. Simple to set up and use. Great."}
{"Author": "Jeff Piotrowski", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works but not a good bulb", "Text": "Easy enough to set up but the bases cord is short...wish these would have come with day light bulbs and not a yellow bulb/warm light bulb"}
{"Author": "Tim", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Awesome product with easy setup!"}
{"Author": "Earth22BoundX", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Eh", "Text": "They worked great. But I found out you can\u2019t control them anywhere with 4G LTE like my TP-Link lights, that for me was a huge deal breaker as I want to turn them on/off whenever/wherever"}
{"Author": "Kat-L", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Loving the Hue Smart Bulbs!", "Text": "These bulbs make life easier: It's great to schedule lights or use the GPS feature to have the lights turn on as you enter your neighborhood using the Philips app. They also work perfectly with Alexa. The adjustable brightness/dimming feature is a nice bonus. I also bought a starter set for my parents & they love using them with Alexa!!"}
{"Author": "Emanuel Beltrame", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worth the investment. Using with google home and works ...", "Text": "Worth the investment. Using with google home and works ok. Light is dimmable and you can ask for more or less brightness"}
{"Author": "John S Dalziel", "Date": "on January 27, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This item sounds good but would not link up with my Echo or ...", "Text": "This item sounds good but would not link up with my Echo or my Bluetooth, just flicking a switch is easier. Returned it for refund!"}
{"Author": "haksy1", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "very happy with the kit", "Text": "very happy with the kit! I have the system set up throughout my house with Alexa controlling. it's really nice to just tell her to turn on/off, and the app is pretty customizable."}
{"Author": "Koop", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I love the hue lights, this basestation works great with Alexa."}
{"Author": "Mark J. Chiu", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not What I Have Hoped For", "Text": "I was looking for something that I could command orally, like those operated in connection with Amazon Echo."}
{"Author": "William S. Murphy Jr.", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome with Alexa", "Text": "I love these things and I can\u2019t wait to see a price drop so I can get the color change package. Very cool product..."}
{"Author": "Crystyle", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is my first smart bulb purchase and i really", "Text": "This is my first smart bulb purchase and i really, really love that i made the choice to invest in these. I have never had a problem with the bridge not responding or not working. I do wish they were a little bit brighter bulbs, but the fun color bulbs make up for the lack of brightness. I have owned for about 4 months now and haven't regretted it once."}
{"Author": "Long Time Kindle Customer", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Disappointing results with Hue", "Text": "I\u2019m re evaluating this product.\nHue worked well when I was at home or nearby. BUT, I bought it so I could control lights while I was away from home.\nHere I am in Florida, the Hue hub and lights are in Indiana, and I am unable to make contact.\nYes, I\u2019ve tried the Hue Help, such as it is, and looked on line but could never find a way to connect.\nI\u2019m very disappointed."}
{"Author": "JoDinIRB", "Date": "on January 26, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Even My Non-Technical Family Loves This!", "Text": "I love these lights so much that I ordered multiples as Christmas gifts. I felt kinda like Oprah, \"You get a light kit, and you get a light kit, everyone gets a light kit!\". Seriously though, these are super easy to set up, work fantastic with our Echo Dots, and make it easy to turn off lights that people can't ever seem to turn off manually. My low-tech family loves how easy these are to use with their Echo devices. I love that I don't have a ton of apps to manage... we can expand this kit to 50 devices and still only use the Philips Hue/Alexa apps to manage everything. The bulbs may be more pricey than some of the more generic ones, but it's worth it for the convenience."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Poor color", "Text": "The color of the light is a bit green. It's not got the warmth of tungsten. Don't use these where you care about color or might be taking photos."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Perfect. No complaints. I even recommended people."}
{"Author": "Lynn Pierce", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great lighting", "Text": "Don't ever turn on or off a light , just say it. Great when your hands are full."}
{"Author": "Michael", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Expensive-ish, but worth the price!", "Text": "Philips Hue, as usual, delivers an excellent product and works quite trouble free.\nThe only complaint I would have about these kits, and Hue series in general, would be the cost.\nThey do deliver on the quality though with that added cost.\n\nThe bulbs are beautiful, the light is excellent for the power consumption.\n\nThe Hue hub and my SmartThings are playing quite nicely now for some time."}
