{"Author": "Joaris Manning", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works perfectly. Some times you might have to turn ...", "Text": "Works perfectly. Some times you might have to turn the switch off (power cycle the bulb). But hey. electronics are not 100% fail proof."}
{"Author": "thowell", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Takes some getting used to but training the household is problematic", "Text": "I contemplated a 5 star rating but the reality of utility has proven to be not as friendly as one may think. Years of habit make turning the lamps on and off manually is hard to overcome but doable. Setting up auto on and off is great option, especially if going out of town. Also great is the remote control; you can be out of the country and still control the lights (assuming someone didn't turn one or more of them off manually). Using Google Home is a hit or miss; I've almost quit using it altogether, opting instead to just open the app on my phone and controlling them that way. I'm fairly sure that once we all get accustomed to operating the lamps, we'll stop remembering how to work those lamps manually. I would get them again, just for the remote operation."}
{"Author": "Joey Clark", "Date": "on January 25, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love the Phillips Hue.", "Text": "I bought this starter kit during the Christmas shopping season, on sale for about 40% off. This was a great start to my smart home. Normal price is a little high, but they work almost flawlessly. Hope to add color changing bulbs soon."}
