{"Author": "Billy", "Date": "on January 24, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "its working out good for me right now", "Text": "its working out good for me right now, the bridge help me out with other things i got to make it easy for me"}
{"Author": "Stephen B.", "Date": "on January 24, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy setup works great with Alexa", "Text": "This kit is easy to setup and does exactly what I expected. I recently got an echo dot as well and it integrates perfectly with these bulbs. I can now control my lights hands free, with my phone, and even when I am not at home. My phone does occasionally have a delay connecting when I come home but with the dot I can still easily control my lights. They are also a bit pricey when you have fixtures with multiple bulbs. My favorite part is not having to get out of bed to turn the lights off at night."}
{"Author": "Brad", "Date": "on January 24, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Price is hard to swallow but works really well to get started. Expanding is an investment."}
{"Author": "K.C.", "Date": "on January 24, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Frustrating. Constantly shuts down.", "Text": "Hue bridge constantly stops working and is not compatible with Alexa... only when she feels like it. Very frustrating. If Alexa tells me one more time that my Hue Bridge is not responding I am going to cry. omg"}
{"Author": "Purple Platypus", "Date": "on January 24, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "great system", "Text": "We've tried another smart lighting system that only brought frustrations...\nThe Hue system is intuitive. With the Hue base, there are no more connecting the bulbs via wifi, which require resetting if you ever switch off the light manually by mistake or if the power goes out. We've now added A LOT more bulbs to the system!"}
{"Author": "Sandra Baker", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "easy to install and command"}
{"Author": "Michael", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "this was a gift and they love it. Easy to set up", "Text": "this was a gift and they love it. Easy to set up, though I recommend plugging in one bulb at at time and setting up each in turn. Otherwise, it's hard to know which is which."}
{"Author": "Aaron Herbst", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These are very good, premium at a slight cost.", "Text": "Work great, I'm buying a single $50 color bulb for the morning waking up feature. These are not recommended for morning wake apparently. These are fun to use and are very convenient. I bought this kit as an investment into the hue ecosystem. All of their products are expensive but there aren't any unified alternatives, and even the cheap bulbs aren't very much less expensive."}
{"Author": "Tim H.", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "Issues with Alexa duplicating bulbs so Alexa can\u2019t control because of duplicates"}
{"Author": "Joshua Lewitter", "Date": "on January 23, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "light up my night!", "Text": "Way to be lazier works like a charm with a smart home device to improve it even more!"}
{"Author": "Marisa", "Date": "on January 22, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Makes such a difference", "Text": "I bought this to use with the Echo Dot that I received for my birthday. I have a physical disability that makes it painful and difficult to get around. With these bulbs, I can turn my lights off and on without standing, turning, or walking. Sometimes my son leaves a light on in the other room. I replaced the lights he leaves on the most and now I can turn off all my lights without getting out of bed."}
{"Author": "Philip McDermid", "Date": "on January 22, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great controlled lighting option", "Text": "Another toy I have wanted for a while. These are great for secuity lights allowing programs that can even randomize the on and off times. I like them personally for messing with the kids. t"}
{"Author": "Dima", "Date": "on January 22, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is just amazing!", "Text": "It\u2019s very helpful to turn off the light in the bedroom, when you almost fall a sleep! And don\u2019t get up from your bed!"}
{"Author": "dcspace", "Date": "on January 22, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Plug The Hub To Your Router", "Text": "Fun color lights, timer settings, Alexa voice control.....expensive bulbs."}
{"Author": "Zach g", "Date": "on January 21, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome with Alexa", "Text": "Use these with Alexa dot and they work perfectly. Timer modes and diming options are pretty cool. From what I've tested losing internet connection does not affect the state the lights are in at that moment."}
{"Author": "Stephanie", "Date": "on January 21, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These bulbs are life changing!", "Text": "These bulbs are life changing. I am a night owl, always have been, the fact that I can time my lights to dim on their own gradually (so I actually get sleepy and go to bed at a reasonable time) is a game changer. I recommend these to everyone. They are amazing."}
{"Author": "Franklin H.", "Date": "on January 21, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works Well but More Expensive.", "Text": "Worked as advertised. Integrated easily with my SmartThings hub. Just wish th Phillips Hue stuff wasn\u2019t so much more expensive than the other options."}
{"Author": "Abraham Perez", "Date": "on January 21, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Fun to play with, they get very bright and work great with my several Google home mini."}
{"Author": "Nate", "Date": "on January 20, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not ready for primetime.", "Text": "Pretty disappointed in the bulbs. To be told by the app that the lights they provided me in the kit are \"not optimal\" for doing basic functions like fading in to wake me up is poor execution.\n\nPlus, the hub won't even tell you if the bulb is online.\nI can switch off the power to a bulb, and turn it on in the app as if it's online, and the app has no idea. Just switches it on (as far as I know) and shows as on in the app, only to get home and find that there's no power to the bulb at all because the switch was off. Wouldn't you think the app would tell you if it can't find a bulb?\n\nPretty poorly put together in my opinion. That said, if you know the limitations, and account for them, it is a fun toy to play with.... you just can't count on it."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 20, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love these bulbs", "Text": "I love these bulbs. My daughter gave me the 4 pack starter kit for Christmas and i love them."}
{"Author": "J. Bush", "Date": "on January 20, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to set up, can use 3 different ways to control, great customization, very happy", "Text": "Very easy set up, install the app, add the skill, I can control these lights by voice via the Echo Dot/Alexa, via the Smart Home app, or via the Hue app itself. During times when the Hue app can't connect from wherever I'm at away from home, the Smart home function in the Alexa app never lets me down. I've since added another 4 Hue bulbs and I really like during set up the individual bulbs flash so you can identify which ones you are setting up and naming. I am not a fan of bright artificial lights so I really like that I can adjust dimness down to a percentage."}
{"Author": "Chris Jr", "Date": "on January 20, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love them and they have changed my daily routine entirely", "Text": "Got this on a special price. Love them and they have changed my daily routine entirely."}
{"Author": "Gail Fleming", "Date": "on January 19, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... the day but my husband and I are having fun and enjoying echo and all the gadgets to go ...", "Text": "Never thought we would see the day but my husband and I are having fun and enjoying echo and all the gadgets to go along with Alexa."}
{"Author": "Julianne Peer", "Date": "on January 19, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love this very much I turn my lights on on ...", "Text": "I love this very much I turn my lights on on my way home about 12 miles away\u2026 When I go to bed at night I get in bed and I turn on my lights off awesome I want to get up in the morning I turn my lights on with my phone"}
{"Author": "eslmike", "Date": "on January 19, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not too swift but ok.", "Text": "Can only control lights when in bluetooth range. For the money this is not a good value."}
{"Author": "Canescent", "Date": "on January 19, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These are great fun! We got this one as a gift", "Text": "These are great fun! We got this one as a gift, but we have the hub and about 6-8 bulbs, and it\u2019s great. I can tell Alexa to turn the nursery light to lower and lower percent dim as we read the kid bedtime stories, turn on porch lights with inconvenient switch locations, program the lamp to come on and turn off at whatever time we need to, etc."}
