{"Author": "Haji", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Good"}
{"Author": "Paul", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works flawlessly with my setup."}
{"Author": "Janet B", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy set up!", "Text": "Love the convenience of these lights. Easy to set up and add to my echo system."}
{"Author": "mc", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "They're great. Excellent for remote activation for safety while on vacation. Works great with Alexa."}
{"Author": "aaluck", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Impressed....for about 3 hours, anyway.", "Text": "This is my initial impressions and comments on the setup and function. Out of the box set up was simple and easy. You simply put the bulbs in the lights, turn them on, connect the hub to the power and ethernet and open the app. Everything is simple and straightforward. To connect it to the Alexa I downloaded the \"skill\" and Alexa immediately found all of the bulbs and group I had setup.\n\nHad a little frustration with Alexa claiming I had \"several\" devices with the same name--despite only having one with that name, but I renamed the ones it had a problem with. I was impressed, dimming lights, turning them off and on in groups and individually, the family was impressed. It worked GREAT-----FOR ABOUT 3 HOURS!! Then the Hue hub went offline. Alexa said \"the Hue hub is not responding\". So I checked everything and sure enough the Hue hub would not connect to the internet through the Hue app. This is especially perplexing as it is CONNECTED with an ETHERNET cable, not WIFI (and for your information it CANNOT connect with WIFI). How does a device plugged directly into the router lose a hardwired connection? So now I apparently have to start over again with a full reset. So I'm guessing this will be a bust, but Ill update later.\n\nCannot give more than 2 stars at $80.00 for 4 \"dumb\" LED bulbs I could get for $2.00 each. Kinda pricey LED bulbs. I will be returning it if it goes offline again and going with the plugs to see if those work.\n\nUPDATE When I got home from work the Hue was back online and working. So at this point everything is functioning as it should.\n\nUPDATE again....back to no connection to the hue. At this point it does work about 70% of the time. But it is very unreliable at best. Not sure why it disconnects itself randomly but it does. Usually corrects itself but very frustrating."}
{"Author": "Robert P.", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Product, it's nice to be able to control ...", "Text": "Great Product, it's nice to be able to control lights through the Echo, have the family come home to a lighted house and to be able to control the lights when not at home."}
{"Author": "Anthony Ballo", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to setup", "Text": "Easy to setup and get connected. Programming was a breeze. Great product - will be adding to these lights. This is a great starter kit."}
{"Author": "Tactical Panda", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "DOA bridge, don't let it frustrate you.", "Text": "Hue bridge (part that connects to your network) arrived DOA. After spending over an hour troubleshooting turns out this piece of junk was just dead. Tried to do a return hoping for a quick exchange but all amazon offered was a refund 7 days after receiving. Screw that. Went and bought one from the local Best Buy and it works fine."}
{"Author": "Tracy Schuller", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "More Hassle Than Convenience", "Text": "Bought a starter kit with 3 bulbs. 1 bulb wouldn't connect while in some lights, but would connect in others (a different bulb *did* connect in the former.) Got all 3 bulbs connected, seemed good to go... 2 days later Alexa can't \"discover\" any Phillips devices. I see I could manually enter the serial numbers off each bulb & try to reconnect, but I honestly don't feel like doing that even once, much less every time the product fails. We were initially excited & bought more bulbs to set up, but now I won't even bother."}
{"Author": "anthony", "Date": "on January 18, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very good for smart homes", "Text": "Works great with my home. Just need to make sure you leave the light switches on. I was able to connect these to the Amazon Echo too."}
