{"Author": "Peter M. Celestina", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great product."}
{"Author": "Greg Cwalina", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does not work.", "Text": "Would not set up at all. Followed the instructions precisely and the hub would not find my router. Tried several times and still nothing. Tried the advanced method of manually logging my IP address, same results. After about 10 attempts I have given up and will return the item. I even tried to go the the website listed on the bottom of the link page and was directed to a GERMAN site, what kind of crap is that?"}
{"Author": "Steven A Marshall", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Connecting is easy when the proper process is followed.", "Text": "Bridge was easy to install. All bulbs work perfectly. Just beware that you must have an led capable dimmer switch in order to have the bulbs work properly. If a regular dimmer is used, the bulbs may flicker and/or not work at all. Downloading the Hue app was easy and fast and the bulbs were discovered on the Hue app immediately. If attempting to connect using Alexa, I found that the devices had to be discovered using the Hue app first and then they would appear on the Alexa app."}
{"Author": "Robert W. Tippery", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Set up was easy, however", "Text": "Set up was easy, however, connectivity with Apple home is intermittent and a known problem. I wish I had checked the support page for Philips before purchasing these and discovered the issue."}
{"Author": "Elijah Phillips", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best in class. Great value. Easy to use.", "Text": "I never thought these would be a big deal. We use lamps with smart plugs all over the house, so I didn't see the point in bothering with expensive smart bulbs.\n\nI was totally wrong. These are great. So many smart plugs make a very quiet, high pitched ringing noise that annoys me. These don't.\n\nThe ability to dim and adjust the lights is awesome. They animate smoothly when turning on, off, high, or low. It looks cool.\n\nThe color is great, the usability is great. I didn't want to like these as much as I do, but they really are the best smart lighting system I've seen."}
{"Author": "philip", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "2nd gen at a great price", "Text": "2nd gen at a great price"}
{"Author": "Anonymous Digit", "Date": "on January 17, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic!!!!!!!!!", "Text": "Best thing since sliced bread. Seriously!!! We are seniors. We can ask Echo Dot to turn off of on lights for us. It helps in dark house at night, especially with 2 black cats coming to greet us."}
