{"Author": "dolores frederick", "Date": "on January 1, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hands -Free Lights", "Text": "Ordered and couldn't be happier with the connection to Alexa, which makes our lives a whole lot easier with the On/Off of the lights in our house."}
{"Author": "S. Gay", "Date": "on January 1, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for a growing smart home", "Text": "Got these as a Cyber Monday deal. Work great with my Google Assistant and have made it much easier to manage the lighting in my living room and basement."}
{"Author": "Circle B Ranch", "Date": "on January 1, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "PRETTY HAPPY", "Text": "I bought this starter set to work with Echo and three Dots. To be honest, the Hue Bridge and the bulbs set up nicely, and I could control all of the bulbs from the Hue app. The issue was in connecting it to the Echo and Dots; not the most straight-forward approach to marrying the Hue Bridge to the Echo platform. I think the apps should be more intuitive.\n\nIn the end, I called Philips and talked to \"Rhonda\", who helped me work thru the app connections. I like the product (maybe a bit overpriced?), but the apps (Echo and Hue) need a simpler interface and instruction."}
