{"Author": "Y. Gaung", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Would like to have three stage settings (off, dim and on) with Alexa voice control!"}
{"Author": "Shawn F.", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy", "Text": "Works very easily. Had these all set up in less than 20 minutes"}
{"Author": "Manuel G", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Awesome product! Love it!"}
{"Author": "Skilla", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good for those who embrace it.", "Text": "I originally bought these not knowing what I would do with them but now that I have them I will probably buy more.\n\nPros\n\u2022 Can turn on, turn off, or dim with voice (through Echo) or phone app from another room or even away from home.Want your kids to come down for dinner? Flash their lights off and on to let them know.\n\u2022 App is better than its reviews. Simple and intuitive.\n\u2022 Responsive.\n\u2022 Routines are the best! Lights that turn on at sunset or turn off at 2 AM when everyone is asleep. Waking up to a light slowly turning on instead of an alarm. My child\u2019s light slowly dimming to a nightlight as they are falling asleep.\n\u2022 Functions like ordinary LED bulbs when your wife doesn\u2019t want to deal with downloading the app.\n\nCons\n\u2022 Requires a hub that has to be plugged into the router.\n\u2022 Way more expensive than ordinary LEDs even after you have the hub.\n\u2022 For me, installation did not go smoothly initially.\n\u2022 Be careful what you name these if you have an Echo or Alexa is going to be confused!\n\nConclusion: Expensive but convenient especially if you are the type to embrace the system and set up routines. Don\u2019t bother if you are not going to spend a little time upfront with it."}
{"Author": "Andy C.", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome system if you take time to learn it.", "Text": "I can see why people rave about this device. This whole kit makes being lazy easier and the same time makes you feel safe if your not home or will be arriving home late or will be on vacation away from your house. I can also see it being beneficial for individuals who may be handicapped or have a physical ailment or be for a senior citizen. Just set the device up with an Alexa, google device and then teach individual to use the system."}
{"Author": "Sam", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy Setup and Works Great!", "Text": "I currently rent an apartment so I was not able to swap out the dimmers and switches for automated ones so this set was a great alternative. The setup was easy where all I did was plug in the hub to my ethernet switch and then installed the lights.\n\nOnce I did that I downloaded the Philips Hue app and followed the instructions.\n\nThen I connected the system to my Echo and have been controlling the lights with my voice ever since. When I dont want to talk like during a movie I use the app to dim the lights or turn them off."}
{"Author": "Sarasota FL.", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Its awesome and work great."}
{"Author": "tom ackerson", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Never works 1 out of 10 times", "Text": " Never works"}
{"Author": "Daniel", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "They work great, and are very cool to use Amazon's Alexa ...", "Text": "They work great, and are very cool to use Amazon's Alexa with! I like the dimming feature as well."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy to install and set up with my current Google Home."}
{"Author": "KevinLeven7", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Useful", "Text": "They work great and are really handy with your google assistant"}
{"Author": "Nathan Turner", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great gift for my wife", "Text": "Great gift for my wife. These lights are in my bedroom, kitchen, and foyer. Echo and echo dot work great with them. My wife loves them in the bedroom because when she gets up she just say turn them on 20% and it allows your eyes to adjust before you get up. Also if anyone says they are not bright enough I would just tell them to stop looking at the sun. Great product."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hue app will not function on Kindle Fire tablets", "Text": "Purchased this starter pack from Amazon for my parents for Christmas. They already had the Echo so this item was logical to expand the functionality. The problem that I have is that they both use Kindle Fire tablets and when we attempted to install the Hue app on the Fire tablets to control the lights, the app would not function (will not recognize the Hue bridge). After much time researching, we found that this is a known issue and the Philips Hue app will not work on Fire tablets. Called Philips tech support and they confirmed the posts concerning the issue. Having older parents who don\u2019t have smartphones and are happy with Kindle Fire tablets, this purchase was not a good one. I have installed the Hue app on my iPhone and set up their lights at this point, but the developers should look into having an app that is compatible with the Kindle Fire or Amazon should consider the products they market that will not work with their own smart devices. Also curious why Amazon has the Hue app in their Amazon App Store if it will not work with their devices."}
{"Author": "kwbeattie", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Our soon is excited about using the system in his new apartment with his Echo. Thank you!"}
{"Author": "Steven A", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Perfect smart lighting! Works great and easy to use.", "Text": "Phillips Hue is one of the best smart lighting systems on the market. I have tried a few others and but after I received my first Hue starter kit I decided to upgrade all of my lights to it. The Philips Hue White Smart Bulb Starter Kit I ordered has the basic A19 bulbs which are their most affordable bulbs. These lights can remotely turn on/off and even dim and are amazing for most locations. The bulbs in this kit can get extremely bright and even fade when turned on/off (something some of the other smart bulbs dont do.) The Hue app is one of the easiest smart home apps I've used and should be great even for beginners."}
{"Author": "Gabriella", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works perfectly. Very simple and easy setup.", "Text": "I purchased this for my grandparents who vacation a lot and they like to turn the lights on and off when they\u2019re away to make it look like someone is home. The setup was so easy. I had everything set up for them in under five minutes and it\u2019s very easy to control. They love it."}
{"Author": "Don McLaren", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Needs to have a battery back-up", "Text": "Looses the connection to the hub when power has been off, has to be manually resconnected, wanted to use when away on vacation, can't depend on it. This is my second brand with same issue."}
{"Author": "Lucas", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Changed my world."}
{"Author": "DJ", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Warning: Keep Receipts and Boxes", "Text": "My boyfriend purchased me three of these bulbs for use with Alexa. 1 of the 3 simply didn't work. Rarely do I receive broken or defective stuff so I threw out the boxes and he tossed the receipts. Keep yours!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Be very wary; you won't find this out until ...", "Text": "Be very wary; you won't find this out until you've bought the set and installed it, but upon discovering my Hue Hub could not connect to the internet for updates and such, troubleshooting led me to the information that Philips advises you not to connect the hub to any network switches or hubs. Well for one thing, if your router has multiple ports on it, news flash, that's a network switch built into the router. So don't tell me this thing can't work through network switches. And even if so, WHO in this day and age would design ANY kind of network device that can't \"see and be seen\" in conjunction with the most common network hardware there is, next to Ethernet cables???\n\nIn short, unless you have the simplest possible networking infrastructure at home, I wouldn't bother. if Hue doesn't work for you, you're just going to get a shrug and \"yeah, it really doesn't work with network switches\"."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Absolutely love, Easy to setup with my google assistant. Nice bright light bulbs."}
{"Author": "splashy", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to set up, useful, bulbs are warm white, not daylight", "Text": "Pros: I really like being able to control these with my Dot, that's going to be handy when I have my hands full, or otherwise need to control these lights. Being able to dim them is nice too - I'm sure will be useful too. Being able to schedule them going on and off will be good too. The controls are easy to use, both in my phone and with the Dot. It was easy to get it all working together once I got the app and signed up. No more plugging and unplugging (for the attic, where I had to plug the light in before going up or could hurt myself in the dark), or having to use a dimmer slider.\n\nAlso, you can add bulbs to the system without having to do much, which is really nice. I'm looking into adding some daylight ones.\n\nCons: I do NOT like the warm white color. I prefer the daylight light, and have always looked for that in LED bulbs (used to look for it with the old incandescent ones too once I saw grow lights which were daylight lights). The warm white always looks greenish to me, and the yellow seems sickly. I'm just not fond of it. It's also harder for me to see things with the warm white.\n\nI'm hoping I can find bulbs that are compatible with this to just add to the places where I want daylight bulbs, so I can have them for reading and other things where I want better color rendition and it's easier to see things with a whiter light.\n\nNote: I should mention that color blindness runs in my family, so I may be seeing more colors than most people do because I'm female. Female relatives of color blind men sometimes see a broader range of colors compared to normal color vision. So, it may look just fine to pretty much everyone else."}
{"Author": "NBC", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "easy set up", "Text": "As advertised. easy set up. arrived on time"}
{"Author": "Shawn R", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I really like these lights", "Text": "I really like these lights. It was super easy to pair up and use out of the box. You simply screw in the light bulbs, connect the bridge to your router, download the app and then the app walks you through the rest. You're able to group them into rooms and then link them with Google Home (which was the reason I got them) to control them with your voice. They give off a good amount of light as well. The only reason I deducted a star is that I wish I didn't have to hardwire the Hue bridge to my router."}
{"Author": "thatoneguy", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smarter Home for the win", "Text": "Such a simple add to our home that makes it so much better. Works really well with Alexa"}
{"Author": "Fredrick S Bell", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Easy to setup works great!!!"}
{"Author": "lexa_arce", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Works great in my home, eventually will have all my rooms with these bulbs."}
{"Author": "Jason Hall", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love them!", "Text": "Absolutely love these! They have made us feel more secure with the ability to schedule on/off times and control remotely"}
{"Author": "Climbtosafety", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I have an olde model, which has been plagued ...", "Text": "I have an olde model, which has been plagued with constant issues. I purchased my girlfriend the 4 light starter and much the same. One light couldn\u2019t be detected on the app and there were software update issues that took hours to resolve. Before you purchase, do a Google search on Philips Hue issues!"}
{"Author": "Taylor Potter", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Absolutely love it!", "Text": "I LOVE THIS PRODUCT! I got this for my parents as a Christmas gift. I set it up for them and it was super easy. It took maybe five minutes. I also paired it to the echo dot i got them and that took about another ten because i had to create a philips account to sign in on the Alexa app. If you don\u2019t want to connect it to an amazon echo product then you don\u2019t have to set up and account. You can just download the app and name your house and each of your rooms and boom you\u2019re done. I love it so much i am getting them for myself."}
{"Author": "Ricky S", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Paired with Alexa and work great !"}
{"Author": "Annette McClure", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I suggest these to all my froends who are considering to go with smart home lighting", "Text": "Setup is done in a jiffy and works exactly as described. I suggest these to all my froends who are considering to go with smart home lighting!"}
{"Author": "Matt Stettler", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bridge bricked", "Text": "Bridge bricked after required update during initial installation using Android app - \"update failed\" message. Tried multiple power cycles and \"factory reset\" button to no avail. Totally useless. Will update if any resolution."}
{"Author": "Jimmy 1961", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My wife's favorite DYI project for 2017.", "Text": "Took ~45 minutes to read everything and figure out how to set this up. It's not too hard, but it's not too intuitive. That said - I overthink things, so others may find it easier to set up. Linked the 4 lights to the hub. Assigned 3 to \"Living Room\" and 1 to \"Front Hall\". Later linked Phillips light strips to the hub and labeled as \"undercounted\" lights in the \"Kitchen\". And it's all linked to Alexa. My wife loves this. She's showing all her friends how she can turn on/off lights in each room with a simple command to Alexa... \"Alexa - turn on living room lights\". And at night we tell Alexa to \"turn off all lights\" and poof... everything is turned off. It's awesome."}
{"Author": "dezsantos", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Experiencing a few hiccups with Echo recognizing my bulbs, ...", "Text": "Experiencing a few hiccups with Echo recognizing my bulbs, but I think that's more due to user error in the setup. The bulbs need to be updated and take an hour per bulb to update."}
{"Author": "Emmanuel Barajas Gonzalez", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy and fast setup"}
{"Author": "Shawn", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No Windows 10 app nor full support from the Web App?!!", "Text": "Astounded that there is no Windows 10 app and you can't get full functionality from the Hue website. Cortana and third party apps provide basic functions but this really limits usability."}
{"Author": "Nick T.", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It's ok to be lazy sometimes, and these help", "Text": "I've had Philips Hue lights for years throughout much of my home, but given their expensive nature I hadn't replaced my kitchen lights with Hue bulbs. Well, now I have, and they're pretty great. Biggest benefit is the ability to control my lights w/ voice via Alexa (using my Echo)... it sounds super lazy (and it is) but with my kitchen lights directly behind my TV I no longer have to begrudgingly slog back to the kitchen to flip a switch after having flopped on the couch. And being able to control the kitchen lights as part of my larger \"TV lights\", \"Movie lights\" and other routines is very nice.\n\nI went with just the white bulbs because I was putting them in pendant lights that have colored glass around the bulb. It's probably best this way, but I do miss some of the customization that came with being able to change colors."}
{"Author": "SierraDelta", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome", "Text": "Purchased this starter kit along with an Echo. Works flawlessly, I can control any connected lights from anywhere else in the house via my Echo or Dot, on either the Alexa or Philips app. The Philips app is very straightforward, initial setup was very easy and it's also easy to add additional bulbs at any time. The app also gives you the ability to create \"routines\"; for example, you can have your front porch light turn on at sunset and turn off at sunrise. You can also control the lights remotely when outside of your home network."}
