{"Author": "Michelle Smith", "Date": "on December 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "We love our Phillips hue lighting system with Amazon Alexa. Best investment ever!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love this!", "Text": "Love this!!!!! I hooked it up to my Alexa and its absolutely amazing. At first it took some time to actually get them syncing on which light bulb was which but after I love it! bye bye clap ons!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 25, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Lights are great. Software needs an update. More customization is needed"}
{"Author": "ccarney33", "Date": "on December 24, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very easy to set up in the home / within the ...", "Text": "Very easy to set up in the home / within the alexa app. Took maybe a total of 5 minutes. Works as expected, except two of the four bulbs in my starter kit worked for about two minutes before burning out and now they won't turn on or register in any lamp in my house. So only half the system I purchased worked out of the box. Over all its neat. I'll likely buy more bulbs and for my house but ita annoying that I already have to replace bulbs 10 minutes after the box was opened."}
{"Author": "JAR1599", "Date": "on December 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not necessary, but I LOVE MY SYSTEM", "Text": "I absolutely love my system. It helps my daughter to not be scared around our house, it makes me feel safe to come home to a lit house. It makes my whole life just so much easier. I have 5 bulbs and I would recommend to anyone."}
{"Author": "HPR928", "Date": "on December 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome start to making home smart", "Text": "Use these in bedroom for night stand lights., It's great being able to tell Alexa to turn on/off or dim lights. Can also be programmed to turn on/off at certain times. Can't wait to add more lights."}
{"Author": "User101", "Date": "on December 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic product.", "Text": "They work great with the echo. Super easy to use and setup. Will be buying more bulbs for other rooms. Highly recommend when you are getting started with smart home devices!"}
{"Author": "richawolf", "Date": "on December 22, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but works as advertised and easy to set up", "Text": "Not life changing, but works as advertised and easy to set up."}
{"Author": "Rover", "Date": "on December 22, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This was a great deal for getting started", "Text": "This was a great deal for getting started. (In my second home) I've been doing Smart Home stuff on Echo as long as it's been available. I'll be glad when the hubs are obsolete, but Hue has been pretty solid."}
{"Author": "Megan Cunnington", "Date": "on December 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Maintains connection and functions well", "Text": "I bought this starter kit as I often come home late, and my porch light is controlled by a switch inside, so it would be hard to see the lock to get into my house. I wanted to be able to custom control my lights and this seemed like the simplest solution. I don't have any home assistants, but I can see the appeal of using this with a home assistant if you have one. You could always have the light on and turn off the switch, but then the connection is lost.\n\nFirst, setup is incredibly simple. I plugged the bridge into my router via the ethernet cable it comes with and then plugged the power cord in. It takes a moment to connect, and then you follow the steps on the app. You basically just hit buttons on the app a few times, and i goes through. I skipped an home assistant setup, but that can be part of the setup process if you have alexa or another assistant. It does appear to be compatible with alexa per other reviews, if that's what you're looking for.\n\nSecond, these bulbs are very easy to use. The app is very simple and straightforward. I have explored setting up routines, so I'll probably update this review if they don't seem to work.\n\nSo far, they have maintained a great connection. They have a standard setting, but you can also dim the lights and adjust to perfect brightness. I really like this as I like to have a light on while watching a movie but don't like the glare from the standard wattage. This is a very simple and energy efficient upgrade for your home."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 22, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Quirky response some times. Have to cycle lights/commands to ...", "Text": "Quirky response some times. Have to cycle lights/commands to get them to respond sometimes. Very convenient when it is working correctly."}
{"Author": "Radarchick", "Date": "on December 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it!", "Text": "I bought this in February, and have been using it ever since, with both HomeKit and Alexa, and after ten months I still get giddy when I figure out something new I can do to automate my lights. I\u2019m slowly adding bulbs to my system, and love it so much I bought one for my brother-in-law for Christmas. My only complaint is that it requires an Ethernet connection to the router."}
{"Author": "Dennis Grube", "Date": "on December 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "The lights and app work great with my Echo"}
{"Author": "Sarah W.", "Date": "on December 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to set up", "Text": "I bought these for my husband and they work well! They were very easy for him to set up and he was able to pair them with the Amazon Echo and Dot. He also put them on the Apple home app on our iPhones. Now we can control them through Alexa or our phones. My only wish is that I had bought more."}
{"Author": "Leon Qubick", "Date": "on December 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great! WIFI Light bulbs", "Text": "Works great! WIFI Light bulbs !!!!!!! Can use alexa or my phone to turn on and off from anywhere. Plus its dimming capable even though the fixture is not! Amazing product. Would work great in a location that doesn't have a switch wired in."}
{"Author": "DeniceAZ", "Date": "on December 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "With opposable thumbs you can do this!", "Text": "I\u2019ll start with the fact that I\u2019m technologically challenged and I always seem to arrive at the party late. I know this stuff has been around awhile and I avoided it because I thought it would be expensive or difficult to set up. It was neither!\nIf you have a butter knife to slice through a little strip of tape on the box, and opposable thumbs to open a box and push a plug into a wall socket, you too can speak to your lights and dim them, etc. I\u2019m thrilled with my purchase and purchasing a dozen more this week. I may even get creative with the colored bulbs.\nI did purchase the Amazon Echo Dot at the same time though it\u2019s not at all required. I also have them set up on my Apple Home Kit so I have several ways to operate these lights and I didn\u2019t require my teenagers help once!\nThey also cast nice light and the dimming feature is my favorite."}
{"Author": "Lonni W", "Date": "on December 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Choose color when you can, but the whites are great too!", "Text": "Love the Hue system. I prefer to go with the color lights. But I bought these for my parents, along with an echo dot, as an intro into having lights they could control via voice and app, since their mobility is limited. It's a great system really."}
{"Author": "Chad Smith", "Date": "on December 20, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... other bulbs but the color ones and they were great but giving three stars because these came damaged", "Text": "I have other bulbs but the color ones and they were great but giving three stars because these came damaged . One bulb was not recognized . Don\u2019t recomend to buy these on a warehouse deal unless you don\u2019t care ."}
{"Author": "Arun Gopalan", "Date": "on December 20, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "No wireless? Seriously?"}
{"Author": "Shaun M", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best smart light ever.", "Text": "Works exactly how I wanted them to. I have an old house with very old walls and electric. My living room light was insanely bright and I wanted a way to dim it easily.\nI paired this with amazon Echo and et viola! Works like a charm. Haven\u2019t had an issue yet and have been using this for about a month now. Definitely 5 Stars."}
{"Author": "smt32697", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Such a convenient idea! I connected these to my ...", "Text": "Such a convenient idea! I connected these to my Echo Dot~! I want to get the colored versions for my living room now!"}
{"Author": "Thinh Dinh", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "AWESOME! Get it...."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "CORRECTION", "Text": "We apologize. The prior review we submitted was fir another company and product - theGE Link Starter Kit w/ A-19 bulbs, which we purchased from Lozia Company, in the same order. Our Philips Starter Kit works great."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice to be remote with my lights!", "Text": "Works great with my Dot. Using 1 in 4 rooms and works perfect. Don't like that the Hue is not wireless. That would be my suggestion to the manufacturer to make it wireless instead of having to plug into hub."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as described. Wish I had done a bit ...", "Text": "Works as described.\nWish I had done a bit more forethought in what kind of bulbs I'll be buying in the future to sync my house to this. Phillips is a bit more expensive than other brands."}
{"Author": "Lorrie Vail Stevens", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Product", "Text": "Great Product"}
{"Author": "Matthew Doritty", "Date": "on December 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "In love", "Text": "This product is amazing!!! Works so well with Alexa products. I love the wake up feature and being able to just turn off the lights when I am ready to sleep is so nice. Want them for the entire house"}
{"Author": "SomewhereinVA", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is a great way to get started with a smart home", "Text": "This is a great way to get started with a smart home. You can control the lights from your mobile device which is nice. But I really like controlling them with my voice using Alexa."}
{"Author": "Mgoodyg", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very happy", "Text": "Love this product. Works great. Took awhile to get it to work with iPhone and Siri but once it did, I was very happy."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty close to \"It just works\"", "Text": "I was leery of smart bulbs after a frustrating with another manufacturer's product. I had spent an afternoon trying to get bulbs to pair to the system, with no luck. So I figured it would probably take an hour or more to get the Philips Hue kit set up.\n\nIt took ten minutes. First, I downloaded the Philips Hue app to my iPhone, and the app guided me through the setup.The bridge (which acts as a hub for Philips Hue bulbs) plugs into your router and into power. Once it powered up, the app found it on my home network and gave me an option to scan an accessory for use with Apple HomeKit. I wasn't sure what they meant by 'accessory'--after a couple of minutes, I figured out that the app wanted me to scan a code on the bottom of the bridge. I hit the 'Scan' button, and pointed the phone's camera at the bottom of the bridge. It picked up the code immediately and registered the bridge in Apple HomeKit.\n\nThe really pleasant surprise was that all four bulbs supplied with the unit were already pre-paired to the bridge. No setup at all required on the included bulbs. After my last experience, that was a real plus for me.\n\nIt took a minute to figure out which bulb was #1, which was #2, and so on, but once I did that, it was a simple matter of screwing the bulbs into the lamps that I wanted to use them in. Apple's Home app, which controls HomeKit devices, was a little harder to figure out--it isn't Apple's best-designed app. But once I had the bulb assigned to the rooms they are in, I was able to use Siri to turn lights in each room on and off, and to dim them.\n\nIt may not quite rise to the level of \"It just works\", but the Philips Hue is the closest gadget to that standard that I've set up in a while. I can recommend this kit without reservation for use with Apple HomeKit.\n\n01/01/2018: I've had these bulbs for several weeks now, and I continue to be pleased with them. We've had one power outage, and a visit from my old-school sister, who would only use the hard switch to turn lights on and off. Through it all, the bulbs have maintained sync with the hub--no resets necessary. I noticed some flicker in one of the bulbs, but it was the result of a fixture-dimmer not being turned all the way up. So far, so good."}
{"Author": "Zack Wilcox", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic for those who want to use with Alexa, google home, and Siri.", "Text": "These lights are fantastic. I have set them up to be controlled through the echo dot. It feels like I have moved into the future in an instant being able to control each and every light by telling Alexa what lamps to turn on and off and even select a level for each or globally.\n\nThe setup does take a bit of work and I do have trouble auto finding the bulbs with the hub and had to enter the code for each bulb. About 45 minutes set up time is worth it for the freedom they offer. And the end to the get up out of bed and turn the lights off game that my wife and I used to play is worth every penny."}
{"Author": "Klaudia", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Good quality and easy to use with the HUE app :)"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Faster and More Reliable than Lightify", "Text": "The Hue controller is a more responsive and faster controller than the Lightify one, and seems to be cross impartible with Lightify globes.\n\nThe lights themselves are pretty neat too, although they're just a warm white,they are dimmable, and a good starting point for all the lamps around your house."}
{"Author": "Andrea Hyde", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One bulb did not work.", "Text": "Arrived promptly, but when Bob did not work."}
{"Author": "Amy M.", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dumb, requires router.", "Text": "The necessity of a router is stupid in this day and age and makes these systems completely useless to me. I had high hopes for getting my entire house running \"smart lights\" but cant because I dont use a tradtional ISP/LAN setup. I wish that were clearer in the item descriptions. These should be able to be run over wi-fi only."}
{"Author": "Todd", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice dimmable app based led bulbs by Philips.", "Text": "Great app based led bulbs. Easy to controll with the hue hub, these are only dimmable wont change from warm yellow to whitish blue like other hue a19 bulbs."}
{"Author": "Dr. P", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Requires HARD WIRED Ethernet on the SAME LOCAL NETWORK!", "Text": "Requires HARD WIRED Ethernet on the SAME LOCAL NETWORK as your PC to work. Unbelievable that the hub is not WiFi."}
{"Author": "N. Bittick", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't waste your time", "Text": "I bought the kit and the dimmable smart lamp. Neither of them worked with Alexa, and even though I did the DL from HUE, the instructions were the most confusing. The bridge has to be hooked up to the ethernet connection. It doesn't work unless you do this. Then you have the smart phone app, which then takes you to a third party if you have questions. i spent two hours trying to get these products to work correctly, only to make the decision, it isn't worth the aggravation. I live in a rural area, wifi is very sketchy, so having another ethernet device, then a wifi link only complicates the whole situation."}
{"Author": "grappalover", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great with Google Home.", "Text": "Very nice starter kit to get you excited about the possibilities. Works well with Google Home. I like they way that fade in and out and that you can control them from your phone. Great that I can be in bed and say \"OK Google, turn off the bedroom light!\" A must-have for every home."}
{"Author": "Robert Miller", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "works great", "Text": "I love how will they work but like most of these things it take up room on my router and there is only 4 plugs that I can use has to be hooked to the main router not hub or switching hub that you can add on to your router for more plug in's computer things like printer and computers"}
{"Author": "Sumatra Drayton", "Date": "on December 17, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pay close attention to advertising.", "Text": "The light works fine with Siri but I think the advertising is a little bit confusing. I did not realize that I was only buying white lights. The commercials I\u2019d seen made it a look like the light could go from white to blue. Disappointed"}
{"Author": "Capitan Bill", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Adds nice security and easy to set up.", "Text": "Great addition to the home."}
{"Author": "Britannia", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great!", "Text": "Easy installation. App is intuitive with loads of features. Integrates easily with Alexa app."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It was easy to install", "Text": "It was easy to install! I installed it myself using the instructions. However, if you add more lights later on, which my husband did, you have reinstall the application on your phone again. I learned this through reading someone else's comments when the new lights could not be reached. Other than that perfect! My husband likes that he is able to voice control the lights."}
{"Author": "Galen", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "U can adject the brightness.", "Text": "Love it. When u are watching movies , u can brighten the lights to 10%, perfect!"}
{"Author": "keith eakins", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Everything I was looking for at a good price."}
{"Author": "Alex", "Date": "on December 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy to install. Easy to set up.\n\nNo complaints."}
{"Author": "Charlotte", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works like it is supposed to", "Text": "Works like it is supposed to. It does operate with your mobile phone as long as you are on the same network. I also found that you can operate on a mobile phone by using your web browser instead of the app. I give it a four because the lights are not as bright as I thought they would be."}
{"Author": "Houston C.", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Be prepared for problems", "Text": "Buyer beware on this one! You need to download the Hue app, which is only found in Apple and Google Stores, not the Microsoft store. I had to download the app on a phone to get started. There are a number of difficult steps to set up the system in your home. Then you have to link your Alexa and Hue accounts by pressing the button on the bridge. When the button doesn't work, you are stuck in an endless loop of trying to link these accounts. You never quite know if you are doing something wrong or you have defective equipment. YouTube videos don't help if your equipment (i.e. bridge) is defective. I hope Phillips will respond to my email request for support. Otherwise, I am stuck with another piece of Chinese-made junk."}
{"Author": "Terry L West", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for home automation", "Text": "Philips needs the bridge to use these bulbs but it is well worth it. I have five bulbs and think you can add as many as you would need. Great for home automation. Works with Alexa."}
{"Author": "Jose", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "They do what they are built to do and very convenient.", "Text": "I like the fact that I can tell it to turn on and off or adjust the brightness. I don't care for the yellowish tone it gives off. I replaced these with a nice set of truly white led lights and you can definitely tell the color difference.\n\nI'm still keeping them due to the fact that I can control them wireless and via my security system."}
{"Author": "Ron Happy", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Excellent combo when on sale."}
{"Author": "Cory Gardner", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love these lights work great and having the ability to ...", "Text": "Love these lights work great and having the ability to dim them is great. They are a little yellow color but I like them and they do a good job. The kit is a good deal, the bridge has had issues connecting a few times but overall like this so far."}
{"Author": "Cliff", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "were easy to set up and pair with my Echo dot", "Text": "were easy to set up and pair with my Echo dot. I really like to programmable ability with the bridge and the phone app."}
{"Author": "Josefina Sanseviero", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love them! Work great with my google home", "Text": "I love them! Work great with my google home. I wish the colored ones were priced closer to these."}
{"Author": "Griffen", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not recommended for main lights.", "Text": "The Philips Hue smart light system works most of the time. The main reason I purchased these smart lights was to use the sunrise wake up feature because I get up very early. That feature of the system has worked very well for me and has definitely helped me become a morning person and avoid being late to work. Aside from the sunrise function, the smart lights are just less convenient to use as primary lights for a bedroom compared to regular \"dumb\" lights on a switch. To turn the Philips Hue lights on and off, you either have to use the mobile app or use the location control based on your phone's gps. I have the location control turned on, so my lights should come on when I get home and turn off when I leave. The location control is frustratingly unreliable. It works about half of the time, and the other half of the time, I have to fumble around in the dark to get my phone out to turn the lights on. It would be much easier to just use a switch on the wall. In addition, since the lights connect over wifi, the connection is not always perfect, and sometimes there is a significant delay between the time I turn the lights on from my app and when they actually come on. For me, it would make much more sense to use the Philips Hue lights in a bedside lamp or secondary light, but I think they would be less of a hassle if you also integrated a smart switch, amazon echo, or other smart devices that would make turning the lights on and off more reliable. I was also excited about having the ability to set the brightness level of my lights, but I have found that I really don't use different brightness levels. I found a level that works well for the room, and I pretty much leave it there. Overall, I really don't think that these lights are a good replacement for normal switch driven lights."}
{"Author": "Lloyd Christmas", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product. Easy to set up and operate.", "Text": "Easy to install and set up. I've had no issues with the lights cutting out or going offline at any time. The smartphone app is easy to use and allows you to customize the on/off/fade/etc schedules with no learning curve at all. I've since purchased additional Philips bulbs and have been very satisfied."}
{"Author": "ThomasC", "Date": "on December 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Work great. Very convenient. I use them in all rooms."}
{"Author": "David P", "Date": "on December 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very nice, simple set up. Using with my Echo Dot and loving it!"}
{"Author": "Jonathan Mueller", "Date": "on December 14, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "At first I hated it but now I love it.", "Text": "At first I hated it but now I love it. At first I had some trouble getting the bridge to connect to my iOS devices. Turns out my router has 3 wifi networks (like many new routers) and I had to connect to my 5.4Ghz network instead of my default network. After that... everything works pretty great. I am still having issues sharing my Home settings to my wife but that isn't a problem with Philips Hue. I do think to call it a \"Smart\" bulb... it could be a lot smarter. Anytime I have to Google how to get something to work I tend to get irritated. If you asked me the first hour I opened it I was pretty upset. But, after some research I got it all setup and working. It is so cool to be able to dim the entire house to 1% at bedtime. I will order bulbs for the rest of the house. But still... not very \"smart\" for a massive corporation with millions in assets... could be a lot better as far as the setup goes."}
{"Author": "Dan", "Date": "on December 14, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I bought it for playing it around. it dimmed ...", "Text": "I bought it for playing it around. it dimmed as I expect by using huecontroller app on my iPhone, but this is not hue system, there is no color adjustment at all. I used them daily now."}
{"Author": "cashmereanscombatboots", "Date": "on December 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not needed but certainly nice to have", "Text": "I have not had one issue with the hub or the bulbs since installing six months ago.\nI have pretty much every light on them in the house now as I keep adding and it is nice and convenient.\nWorks seamlessly with my Echo and Echo Dot as well as the android app for HUE. It's nice to pull into the driveway and be able to light the house up from the phone or adjust the lights from the phone if I'm away for a few days."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great starter kit."}
{"Author": "Mary Connelly", "Date": "on December 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "We love them! Just got a amazon dot and I ...", "Text": "We love them! Just got a amazon dot and I love being able to just say Alexa turn off the light!"}
{"Author": "Katy L", "Date": "on December 13, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not quite what I was expecting", "Text": "Easy set up, except I am not sure how you are supposed to tell which bulb is which but I either guessed right or it's easier than I thought. Connected to Alexa easily and voice control is nice. Kind of fun actually. I am disappointed that I didn't realize these bulbs could not change color. It clearly says white on the packaging but all of the descriptions say they change color. I put them all in my kitchen where I want bright white light and will try to get colors next time."}
{"Author": "Ndiesel1", "Date": "on December 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Excellent"}
{"Author": "WSP", "Date": "on December 13, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Complicated setup - requires other devices to function properly", "Text": "Overall, this is not super simple to install and make it functional over the internet the way it is advertised. For example, a WEMO smart plug connects wireless to your internet, then is controllable via internet while away from your home - no hub necessary. In order for Hue lights to function, you must buy this overpriced hub (e.g. you can buy an internet modem/router for the same price). Then to make this work via internet, you must have some other device capable of controlling your lights via internet. In my case it's an iPad with the Home app but the iPad must remain in the home or I'm unable to control the lights when away. Or if you have an Apple TV (3rd gen or 4K) you can use this as well. From there you control the lights using your smart phone with the Home app. So the question is, why couldn't they just make bulbs that are capable of connecting wireless without the need of the hub? Seems like a good way to get you to waste $$ buying unnecessary products.\n**UPDATE** - Unable to connect via the internet using the Hue App. If using the Apple Home app things work flawlessly. But like I said, this requires Apple TV or another device in the home to communicate to the hub."}
{"Author": "Kaypee", "Date": "on December 12, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not needed if you have the Echo +.", "Text": "If you have the Echo + you do not need this starter kit. You simply need the Phillips bulbs."}
{"Author": "T W", "Date": "on December 12, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Updating our home with smart devices is pretty fun but can be frustrating as ...", "Text": "Updating our home with smart devices is pretty fun but can be frustrating as well. I absolutely love these lights and the capabilities they can provide. I only gave 4 stars because the Hue system won't run the routines/schedules as their set up. As a matter of fact, the settings for turning the lights & off just isn't working. As I understand it from all the post's I've found from other users, the latest software update is to blame. Having my lights on a schedule and setting brightness is why I got these so I'm a little disappointed but I'll continue to use these in the hopes that Philips will correct this."}
{"Author": "Owen L.", "Date": "on December 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "UH. MAZ. ING. Truly Amazing, Get them!!", "Text": "So cool. Connected right to my Alexa and had everything working in minutes. Everyone had a blast programming their own morning routines, as we all work different hours. Nothing like waking up, my side table light turning on to 20%, the bathroom lights going on and then the Living Room turning on to 50%, all at the same time. Even better, with a simple, \"goodbye\", it all turns off. Love this product."}
{"Author": "JourneyMan", "Date": "on December 11, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Easy installation and setup. Works great with Echo. Waiting to expand our smart home."}
{"Author": "Shawn", "Date": "on December 11, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works with Wink smart light bulbs", "Text": "It works great with Amazon Alexa. The reason I did not give it a 5 Star was the instructions on how to was not all that good. Basically I relied on YouTube videos to set it up. Works with Wink smart light bulb!"}
{"Author": "Meagan", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The best lights ever", "Text": "The best lights ever."}
{"Author": "Shelley N", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love them", "Text": "So cool! I use with Echo Dot."}
{"Author": "C. Taylor", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works w eco", "Text": "It is what it is supposed to be...."}
{"Author": "jerry", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "sealed is opened. the bulbs are so used.", "Text": "My box has a seal but it's been opened. The white receiver inside looks used and the bulbs is not clean as new.\nBe careful to get used bulbs"}
{"Author": "yamargie", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "how about some \"troubleshooting\" instructions - cause it doesn't work as easily as described", "Text": "MOST FRUSTRATING thing to connect to Alexa, connecting the bridge is not as easy as it seems as all three lights do not come on easily - I had to unplug, replug, unplug, replug more than 10 times to get the bridge to get ready to pair. FINALLY paired the bridge - then connecting the lights, dear lord I want to pull my hair out.... NO INSTRUCTIONS in the box. online searching for over 2 hours. finally got it to work. Ordered more individual bulbs... GOOD GRIEF - starting all over again"}
{"Author": "gabriela gonzalez", "Date": "on December 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice color bulbs!", "Text": "Love it bought it for my boyfriend because he loves all technology lol but it really makes your home cozy."}
{"Author": "Cujo", "Date": "on December 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "THANKS PHILLIPS", "Text": "Received about 10 days ago, wanted to wait till Christmas to open... It did not work.. Opened..set it all up...In 20 minutes we were up and Dimming!!!!!!."}
{"Author": "franklin", "Date": "on December 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "PHILLIPS HUE LIGHT KIT.", "Text": "The Phillips hue kit really works good and easy to set up.."}
{"Author": "Kevin G.", "Date": "on December 8, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Weak product, ineffective application that only works half the time and two of the four bulbs flicker off and on instead of on.", "Text": "These bulbs don't work on the schedule or with mobile application. Two out of four bulbs are flashing off and on and there's no support. Phillips has a long way to go at that price. A weak product at a very high price."}
