{"Author": "Nn", "Date": "on December 7, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One of my best buys", "Text": "My husband bought the wrong color of light but other than that it works exactly as advertised. Love the ability to turn lights on in the house even when I'm away so I never have to come home to an unlit house. It works even better when I'm feeling lazy in bed and don't feel to move but want to turn on a light in a room\nSynced with app fine and easy to use"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 7, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Work brilliantly. Unfortunately cannot use it across Homekit if you ...", "Text": "Work brilliantly. Unfortunately cannot use it across Homekit if you don't have a AppleTV and are not connected to the same Wifi. You can use them across the Home and Away with Phillips Hue app though. But then, you 've got to deal with two apps, which isn't going to be very intuitive/user-friendly."}
