{"Author": "David", "Date": "on December 6, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Possible fire hazard?", "Text": "I was excited to try the Hue system and bought a four bulb starter kit in November 2017 when there was a good sale. I've been using them since but last night one of the bulbs gave an audible pop, went out, dimmed the other (non-hue) lights in the room, and started smoking. We quickly turned off the power but it was too late for the lamp and the power strip it was plugged into - the lamp no longer works w/ any light bulb and the power strip gives off a disturbing electric fire kind of smell. I'm grateful I was awake and in the room when it happened - the lamp was next to our Christmas tree so the fact that it could have started a fire and burned down my house seems like a real possibility - at least to me.\n\nI don't see any other reports of this kind of Hue failure on the internet so maybe this is just a one in a million, bad luck experience. Your mileage may vary.\n\nI'll edit this review and update w/ what Philips and/or Amazon does to make this right."}
{"Author": "Meg", "Date": "on December 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Serves its purpose well!", "Text": "Wasn\u2019t the easiest thing to set up it wouldn\u2019t sync with my new iPhone X luckily I have my old iPhone 7+ and I got it synced with our WiFi using that phone then transferred to my new phone. One thing that\u2019s awesome is the night vision I Love also that I can talk through it live. I didn\u2019t like that I had to get my own screws and put two holes in my wall just to hang it up but oh well and I don\u2019t like the white cord that just dangles there but I\u2019ll figure something out. I got it for my pet so when I\u2019m gone I can check in on him."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product. Was able to connect the lights to ...", "Text": "Great product. Was able to connect the lights to Alexa without any issues."}
{"Author": "Slanted", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Still our favorite setup to use when getting Alexa ready in an office, or a family members house"}
