{"Author": "Brian Reid", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Hue White A19 60W Equivalent Smart Bulb w/Hub", "Text": "These are my first set of automated lights. They were a little difficult to set up at first but I finally figured it out from online resources. I am, to say the least, very impressed. I am generally pretty tech savvy so when the Hue Bridge, ST and Amazon Echo didn't work to get going, I was slightly confused. I finally read an article online that got me up and running. I am in love with these things! The color is more of a soft white than white. The dimming effect is just what I have been looking for. I have them with Smartthings and Alexa so once I figured it all out, they are quite nice and convenient and the hub is not longer needed. The scenes, dimmers, grouping and all are pretty easy to get used to and having the lights come on at a given time or off with a phrase is excellent. My wife, who is techno-illiterate even loves them. The first morning she came into the living room with her hands full and just said \"Alexa, turn on the living room lights\" immediately fell in love with these. I am pleased to say that I have ordered 4 more bulbs and cannot wait to get all of my home set up. Well worth the money for convenience, cost effectiveness and ease of use."}
{"Author": "Hip Dwayne", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Lights, Great App, Excellent Entry Point for People Interested in Smart Home Features", "Text": "I was a bit hesitant because I thought these smart lights might be a bit gimmicky. I absolutely love the though! They integrate well with my Amazon Echo ecosystem. I use them mainly in lamps and not main lighting fixtures. The dimming features are fantastic. I love using them to adjust lighting for watching movies, reading books in bed, or to gradually wake me up in the morning with the Routines functions. I especially like to set routines for when I'm out of town to make it look like someone is home during normal hours and then turn off the lights at normal sleeping hours. The companion iPhone app has a clean, easy-to-use interface that didn't take any time trying to figure out. It was pretty intuitive. These are a great entry point for someone thinking about getting into the whole Smart Home thing."}
{"Author": "r533dr", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very Nice", "Text": "These have changed my life. I have a poorly wired switch in my Master and used this to replace the switch and provide control to more lights than my previous switch ever could have supported based on the original wiring."}
{"Author": "Armando Toledo", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love the technology ! Will buy more !"}
{"Author": "Cheng Li", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Seems good.", "Text": "Purchased for my friend. Seems good."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Multipurpose solution", "Text": "This is the perfect solution for a number of unique problems. Do you need to dim lights in a ceiling fan?, this is a your answer. Want to turn on inside light before you enter the house? this is also your answer. Want to use your Alexa for something other than party tricks, the Hue gives her a real function. I read about other people having issues with losing connectivity, so far no issue."}
{"Author": "D", "Date": "on December 5, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I then fixed that and it seemed like all was good", "Text": "Set these up, 4 bulbs in different rooms so that we could use Alexa to control some of the lighting in the house. I Did set up with the bridge and that went ok then tried to turn on lights they did not correspond to the labeled rooms.I then fixed that and it seemed like all was good, Lights were working with the app.Tried to set up with Alexa that never happened! ! Had to leave my house for a couple of days and wanted this to work so I left figuring the app would be able to control.Got to my destination and tried to control the lights and received the message \"No Hue connection\". Researched and found out either the hub has to be unplugged and reset or I have to re-install the app.Tried to re install the app and it is searching for the hue bridge,so since I am not home it will never find it.I am left now with the light on (maybe) 24- 7 till I get home.Frustrated, tips for Phillips hue, set up is not easy it should be no one wants to spend hours doing this. They buy these for convenience and safety. They need to be easy to set up and work consistently. I am comparing this to Wemo mini outlets that I have they were simple set up worked out of the box and no bridge to set up! Also Alexa worked well with Wemo. never did get it working with Hue! I will update this review if things change when I get home to try and reset everything."}
{"Author": "K. Mats", "Date": "on December 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best Black Friday Deal!", "Text": "Paid $61 during a Black Friday deal and I just had the chance to set these up in our home. Very easy to setup and connect to both the app and the bridge. I was up and running in minutes. These are my first hue bulbs and experience with \"smart\" appliances and I have to say that I am very impressed with it. I was also able to connect to Apple's Home Kit so now I can even use Siri to turn the lights on and off. I'm already looking for other bulbs to replace around the house to have even more control over them."}
{"Author": "julia", "Date": "on December 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It's a good choice.", "Text": "Bought to my friends. Per they said. It's a good choice."}
{"Author": "Juan Arboleda", "Date": "on December 4, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Product. Set up is extremely easy just install ...", "Text": "Great Product. Set up is extremely easy just install the bulbs, turn power on, download the app, connect the Hue bridge included and done. Took me around 10min to set everything up. Make sure you get the bulbs that are compatible with the ones in your home. The bulbs have like a two second delay from when you control them through your phone or through Alexa.\n\nDefinitely recommend this product"}
{"Author": "MG", "Date": "on December 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Bought it at 40% off and they work really well. Integrates well with Alexa."}
