{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "very cool", "Text": "Find this set on sale.\nNice starter to begin the smart lighting experience.\neasy to set up after adding a few apps."}
{"Author": "Hannah", "Date": "on December 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Will buy again!", "Text": "Awesome x a million! Bought as gifts but had to try them out for myself and it's just so fun. Very easy to set up with my google assistant. Can use voice control AND can use app to set lights on timer, to set them to turn on and off at a specific time each day and so much more."}
{"Author": "er1rn", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but it was easy to figure out", "Text": "Just as expected. Connectivity was difficult at first, but it was easy to figure out. I got this on sale so it was a great price that I could not argue with. It's not too bright so it won't brighten up the room too much, but works well."}
{"Author": "Erik", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Another thing I didn't like about this product is that it requires an ethernet ...", "Text": "The Technical Details and From the manufacturer state the product is Soft White, but the packaging states Warm White. Returned product since it's not warm white. Another thing I didn't like about this product is that it requires an ethernet connection at all times. You must have an open port on your router since there is no wifi connection option available."}
{"Author": "Skinny Lumpkin", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Just Plain Awesome!", "Text": "This is just plain cool. Simple to configure. I've also added the skill to Alexa so I can control with any Echo Dot in the house. Goodbye to walking into a dark house -- everything is controllable from anywhere. Plan on expanding well beyond the original 4 bulbs."}
{"Author": "Ben Cairns", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "FBA shipped it badly", "Text": "The product seems fine, but Amazon fulfillment sent it in a super weird way.\n\nThey slapped the shipping label on the product box rather than a shipping box-- So all the corners of the box are all weird and there's a giant sticker covering the logo and product picture.\n\nMakes it kinda awkward to give it as a Christmas gift like I was planning."}
{"Author": "yue", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good hardware with stupid software limitations", "Text": "1. Bulbs don't remember last state, if the power flickers in the middle of the night these bulbs will wake up full power on you. There is no obvious way to fix this problem in settings or through the Hue IDE.\n2. Bulbs can be controlled only from inside the house, I found no way to change their state from outside.\nBoth these design flaws are serious and make the bulbs useless for most automation purposes."}
{"Author": "swapy", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "App needs update", "Text": "I think the app needs update. Even though I have setup a schedule for few rooms, the lights switch on random times. Most of the time it works but they need to fix the randomness."}
{"Author": "CairoKid", "Date": "on December 1, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Misleading - These are Warm White, NOT White", "Text": "Functionality is fine, but these are not white bulbs as described. The color is very much yellow and the box actually says in tiny print \"warm white\". \"Warm white\" is not white!"}
