{"Author": "Jazzy", "Date": "on November 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bulbs work great and sync with my echo dot perfectly", "Text": "Bulbs work great and sync with my echo dot perfectly. Takes a little set up in the app to get all the rooms, scenes and things set up but once its done, you dont have to mess with it again. Love being able to control our bedroom lighting without having to get out of bed once we are all comfy! Will be buying more bulbs to expand into other rooms as well!"}
{"Author": "Sanford Weinberg - TechTalk Radio (sanford@techtalk.net)", "Date": "on November 30, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "A partly wrong description leads to an unhappy customer....", "Text": "I love home automation and have been eyeing the Hue since it came out. I am also quite technical. When a cyber Monday sale showed these at such a lower price, I grabbed 2 and was quite excited. Two issues. 1. The information from Philips for this listing showed COLOR which was what I was interested in. I would not have bought it for just white (which is what I got) The second piece is that the lack of instructions in the box. Because this was two starter kits it came with two hubs, each hub was paired with the bulbs it came with but I had to go online to find that I did not need to setup up both hubs to control the lights and the information on how to add lights is hard to find. Not at all thrilled. Now I can't get the color bulbs at cyber Monday prices and I have 8 white bulbs that I am not sure what to do with. Like the idea, Like Alexa controlling things... but wanted to be able to do it in color for a price I could justify."}
{"Author": "MJ", "Date": "on November 30, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to set up and I have it paired with ...", "Text": "Just received this product and it is frustrating. Easy to set up and I have it paired with Siri and Google Assist. However, when I ask that light #1 turn on, light #2, 3 or 4 comes on. There is no rhyme or reason to the lights coming on. I ask for the sunroom light to come on and the den or livingroom light comes on. I guess I'm stuck with this product and I suppose I have to disconnect the bridge and start over, this will be the third time. I'm sorry I didn't do more research. Will never buy a Phillips product again."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice addition to my smart/safe home", "Text": "Easy to set up, love that I can voice control my lights. I can dim them or turn them off with my phone or voice. Added safety to my home so I don\u2019t fall over the cats or trip on the furniture getting to a light. And fun, I can name and rename the lamps. I don\u2019t have to leave lights on all day just to lights on when I get home. Nice investment with my echo dot."}
{"Author": "Kimberly White", "Date": "on November 30, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Overall great", "Text": "Works great, the only problem is I got one super white bulb and the other one is super yellow. Overall a great product."}
