{"Author": "jmt", "Date": "on October 27, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The instructions make it seem like you only need to plug the hub into your ...", "Text": "Cons:\n(1) The included \"instructions\" for the hub are not instructions at all - literally no way to glean setup process from the poorly illustrated 3-step manual (it essentially just says \"plug it in\").\n(2) Findings ACTUAL instructions for how to set up the hub was incredibly difficult. There is a reference within the included manual that directs you to a website, but this proved to be incredibly difficult to navigate.\n(3) THE HUB NEEDS TO BE PLUGGED INTO YOUR WIRELESS ROUTER AT ALL TIMES. Philips is very vague about this, likely because they know this may put off users. The instructions make it seem like you only need to plug the hub into your router during setup, but the hub WILL NOT WORK unless it is plugged directly into your router at all times.\n(4) The app to control the lights is not particularly user friendly and connecting the hub to the app was also difficult. You really need to be RIGHT next to the hub during the pairing process or it will not work.\n\nPros:\n(1) It is pretty convenient not having to get out of bed to turn off the lights.\n(2) The tonal quality of the bulbs is actually really really good - I would say probably the best I've seen. The bulbs are very bright but they have a beautiful natural tone.\n\nBottom line, I am not particularly impressed. I would probably return if Amazon Echo interface wasn't so amazing."}
