{"Author": "Craig T. Bennett II", "Date": "on October 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "it only sucks that the bulbs cost a lot", "Text": "The bulbs are pre-program into the hub. This is dead simple to setup.\nThe fact is, it only sucks that the bulbs cost a lot. After this I found out going with something like SmartThings and some of their bulbs. The $50 color bulbs you get with Hue, you can get $12 from other places. On top of that, it really sucks how Hue doesn't have a wall switch nor seem to work with any on the market. The reason why I'm not dinging the review on this is I believe the review should reflect the product itself.\nBut just note this."}
