{"Author": "Michael Zukas", "Date": "on October 18, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "between bad and horrible", "Text": "we have all outdoor lights on Philips hue. patio, deck, two garage lights, garage emergency exit, entrance door. The task is simple. Turn on lights on a sunset. Turn off at 12pm.\na) to accomplish this simple task you need to use third party apps.\nb) half of the lights always Unreachable. But works when you turn them on-off in the app\nc) at the sunset you have all lights off except one random is off\nd) you wake up in the morning - all lights are on. but you can turn them off from app\ne) sometimes hue hub is unresponsive at all. need to restart. ( all lamps and hub are up to date firmware )\nf) apple siri \"turn on all the lights\" - \"OK, Almost all the lights are on!\" - 1 or 2 is always off. but you can turn on them with a manual app. after playing 2-3 times. all the lights on.... what a HELL !?\n\nI don't know how it is possible to make so terrible product. Especially when we are talking about PHILLIPS! It is not cheap to buy these for all the house. I want to install it , setup and forget. Phillips you should be ashamed !!!"}
