{"Author": "J D", "Date": "on October 17, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great when it works, annoying when it doesn't.", "Text": "I really love the Hue system... when it works. I bought this starter kit along with an Echo Dot to control the lights in our living room that are hard to reach. Controlling the lights with my voice is amazing! We love it... WHEN it works. Unfortunately every other day or so, the Hue bridge does not respond to Alexa and we have to power cycle the bridge, then it works fine. The only advice I could find online is to add bulbs in the path of the wifi signal (the Alexa and bulbs are just around a corner from the Bridge), which we have not tried yet, but we do not have use for a bulb in that location and without a guarantee that would work, it doesn't seem to make sense to purchase another bulb as a test. We are still using it but we are hoping for some fix to increase the time period that we have to keep power cycling the bridge. Any tips welcomed!"}
