{"Author": "Megan", "Date": "on October 14, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Beware: Make sure you know the difference between the \"White\" and \"Ambiance\"", "Text": "I was really excited about this system, and used an Amazon gift card someone gave me to buy it. To be clear, it works as described, and the setup is pretty easy. But the thing that was such a BUMMER is that I didn't realize these lights cast a *really* white light. I would never use such a bright white light on indoor bulbs, and frankly don't know why Philips even sells this bulb for indoor, residential use. Somehow, I must have watched a video about the light settings for the Ambiance and thought it applied to these. While you can adjust the brightness, there is zero warmth for these bulbs. So if you are even moderately particular about not having cool white light bulbs in your lamps, chose carefully and get the Ambiance. To an extent, I feel like I wasted money on these because I really don't feel they are usable indoors."}
