{"Author": "AGonzales7", "Date": "on October 3, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dimmer feature is great; linked with my Echo Dot", "Text": "Love these smart bulbs! Dimmer feature is perfect when I'm awake after my wife falls asleep. Placed a few throughout my house and paired them with my Echo Dot, that was I can tell Alexa to dim the living room to 20%, have her turn all lights on/off at once or control each room via the Hue app. Initially, it seemed a little pricey to pay $15 per smart bulb, but they come with a two-year warranty and are designed to last 15 years or 15,000 hours (if I read the warranty info correctly). Which if that math is true, $15 for a dimming bulb that should last guaranteed two years is actually a good deal. Also, each bulb does work as an extender to the other bulbs from wherever your bridge is linked to your router. Setup took me about an hour but only because our router is on one end of the house and I have the 4 bulbs on the other side. So, I had to temporarily place some bulbs closer to the router in order to establish a connection with the others. I plan on putting more of these bulbs throughout most of the rooms in my house, so I will definitely be purchasing more periodically."}
