{"Author": "K. Murphy", "Date": "on September 21, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good bulbs if a bit dim", "Text": "Good bulbs if a bit dim. The major problem I have is the bulb on the far side of the house gains and loses connectivity with its hub (or maybe my phone?) sort of randomly, so if I have the bulbs set to come on when I am not home and turn off when I am, that one turns on and off randomly as it loses and then finds its connection again. Which would not be so bad if it were not in my bedroom. Woke me up three times last night. ALEXA! TURN OFF THE BEDROOM LIGHT! seemed to work better than trying to turn it off through the Hue app."}
{"Author": "Doug Simmons", "Date": "on September 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Quite easy to setup and use", "Text": "Quite easy to setup and use. My wifi router had no trouble finding it and the Android app works great. Gives a decent level of comfort to control home lights when traveling. Better than in-wall timers (old school!). I thought this was a very good value/bang for the buck. Will buy a couple more bulbs soon."}
