{"Author": "6mom", "Date": "on September 20, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Seldom used but now unresponsive after 1 year.", "Text": "The Philips Hue lights are a genius idea and when they work they are wonderful.\nIf someone is unable to reach a light switch there is now a remedy. If you are up in the middle of the night not only can you light your way but you can also dim the light for sensitive eyes. It's all very handy.\nWe did have considerable frustration configuring the lights and syncing them with Alexa but I figure there's a learning curve with everything new.\nThe reason I only gave it 3 stars is that I have one bulb that has hardly been used in the year that we have had it. I'd be surprised if it has 20 hours of use and it turns itself off and becomes unresponsive. Then all of a sudden it will turn itself on, sometimes in the middle of the night. I could have bought a 5 year protection plan but seriously, isn't the light bulb expensive enough?"}
