{"Author": "TX gadget nut", "Date": "on September 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "gen 2 hub : smooth upgrade from gen 1 if you follow instruction and prompts in app", "Text": "I bought this kit to upgrade my bridge to gen 2 so that Alexa could invoke \"scenes\" with different color and brightness settings. I followed the migration instructions and it worked without issue. Incidentaly, the commands to get echo to invoke scenes was not what I expected. I found that I have to say, \"Alexa, turn on cottage sunset in kitchen\" rather than 'set kitchen lights to cottage sunset' which is what I expected to work. I've not deployed the bulbs yet but have been using one that I had already in a lamp. These require the light switch to be left on so it can be a little problematic vs a smart switch but you get the color scenes."}
