{"Author": "Yifan (Brandon) Yang", "Date": "on September 16, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Perfect lightbulbs! Bridge doesn't work with google home.", "Text": "I bought this for my desk for my high school dorm. They work perfectly. The light bulbs are bright and the bridge connects to the ethernet easily. I use Simple Designs LD1003-WHT Basic Metal Desk Lamp with Flexible Hose Neck, White with the light bulbs and they work perfectly! I really love them. The bridge also works with the hue app that is on both android and apple app store, but not all the time. Your internet connection must be perfect for no delays when changing the brightness of the lights. The internet in my dorm is really bad and I have a huge delay when I try to change the brightness of the lamps. The delay is about 2-5 seconds.\n\nThe main reason why I bought these bulbs and the bridge is because of my google home, but it doesn't work with my google home. I asked both the philips hue and google home costumer service but their feedback are not informative and basically they can't fix my problem. For some reason, my google home app on my phone can detect the philips hue bridge but can't connect to it. SO IF YOU HAVE A GOOGLE HOME, AND YOU ARE BUYING THIS PRODUCT BECAUSE OF GOOGLE HOME, PLEASE THINK TWICE BEFORE BUYING THIS PRODUCT WITH GOOGLE HOME!!!"}
