{"Author": "papermaven", "Date": "on September 1, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "AVOID PHILIPS HUE!", "Text": "I would recommend any other way to control your lamps . . . other than Phillips Hue. Very disappointed; in fact, likely to retire the bulbs. Found lights coming on when unexpected, but the worst problem is that I have the Hue bulb in the lamp next to my bed. When I am ready, I turn it \"off\" from my iPad . . . but it simply does not go off; there's still an annoying glow, forcing me to reach up and turn off the lamp at the lamp switch. So, why bother with the WIFI Hue?! In another location, I used a TP-Link plug, and I can set up schedules, but also turn off the lamp from any of my devices flawlessly. AVOID PHILIPS HUE!!"}
