{"Author": "Mark A.", "Date": "on August 30, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Tp-link bulbs are much better for the price", "Text": "I bought these for my living room to go with a ceiling mounted light. I figured if I'm going to be forced to buy the stupid hue hub I might as well get the bulbs for my lamps too. I also bought 3 tp-link bulbs for my bedroom. Unlike those bulbs that are actually cheaper and do not require a hub to connect to my eco dot, these philips bulbs can not change between daylight and soft (very yellow) light. And on top of that they're not even that bright. The hub also doesn't really add any additional functionality over the hub-less tp-link bulbs. If the ceiling light doesn't totally look amazing when it's installed I'm going to return all these phillips hue bulbs and go with tp-link for the whole house."}
