{"Author": "Kevin E. Perry", "Date": "on August 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for light sockets without switch legs", "Text": "While going this route with smart lighting is a bit pricy, it does have its practical uses. I have lighting in areas of my basement that do not have switch legs and only have pull chains. This is a far more convenient way to control light in these areas (and cheaper than running switch legs. It works great with HomeKit and Echo. I never have to walk into a dark basement trying to find that stupid pull cord again."}
