{"Author": "PJ Green", "Date": "on August 28, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Doesn't work in E12 sockets, even with adapters...", "Text": "Exasperating product. Wish I could return it--but return window has passed. Just set this up, and turns out the bulbs won't work in E12 sockets, even if you have socket adapters. I happen to live in a house where all the lights are E12. I have adapters, and thus have normal bulbs in most of the lights--but these don't work. Basically, this thing is useless to me."}
{"Author": "L-Valverde", "Date": "on August 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Waited to buy, should have done it sooner.", "Text": "Waited a few months to pull the trigger on this. Took 15 min to set up, at first my amazon echo couldn't find two of my bulbs that I bought separately, downloaded the hue app and was able to sync the two apps together. All my bulbs work perfect with my amazon echo now. I feel a lot of people that leave bad reviews for these aren't tech savvy or have the patience to set it up. Definitely replacing more bulbs in the future, never flipping another switch again."}
