{"Author": "Whitney B.", "Date": "on August 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Bulbs, Integration with Phone App and Echo Dot", "Text": "I bought this starter kit because a friend of mine had purchased the product. I had stayed with them for a week during my vacation and it was amazing with the integration with the Echo Dot through out their home.\n\nThis product was easily set up and the app on the phone works quite well. I am able to set scheduled times for the lights to fade in or out, turn on or off. I really enjoy the location detection as well. If I come home late at night, the lights will turn on automatically when I get near my home.\n\nThe integration with my own Echo Dot is all right. I think my Echo Dot has a difficult time understanding me - sometimes it does not turn lights on or off the first time. This may be my own user error (hence I did not dock a star) or because there is heavy background noise (TV or music).\n\nI think product is great! I cannot wait to purchase more bulbs once I purchase a bigger place. I highly recommend this product!\n\nBelow is a quick description of how I rate products:\n5 stars \u2013 I love this item and truly glad I purchased it! The item goes above and beyond what I would normally expect. I highly recommend that everyone purchase this product.\n4 stars \u2013 I like the item and it is what I expected, but there may be some flaws. I would most likely purchase this product again.\n3 stars \u2013 The item was okay, but it did not \"wow\" me enough. The product works as intended with flaws, but I would probably not buy it again unless I had to.\n2 stars \u2013 There are probably worse items than this and there are definitely better choices. I would likely not purchase this product again.\n1 star \u2013 I dislike this item and I wish I had not bought it. I cannot recommend it to others and I would not purchase this product again."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on August 13, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Too many bugs to work regularly.", "Text": "Great when it works but it constantly stops reading the bulbs. The only way to fix this is to unscrew the the light bulbs and then it finds it again. Unfortunately this happens too often. I would not buy this product again until they're able to get rid of all of the bugs."}
{"Author": "JMN", "Date": "on August 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great. Too bad only 840 lumen bulbs available for remote", "Text": "Works exactly \"as advertised.\" Easy set up. Easy to control away from home with the app for my iPhone. Great for mimicking presence while out of town. You can set a schedule when you'll be out, and set the times to come on and off, while adding some random change to the times. My only \"complaint\" would be that I wish they offered higher output bulbs, like 75w equivalent or 100w equivalent, and not just 60w equivalent (840 lumens)."}
