{"Author": "Gustave N.", "Date": "on August 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "and I love the way it works", "Text": "I had initial problems connecting to them with the included device, but I persisted and got it going. I hooked them up to my Echo, and I love the way it works."}
{"Author": "min", "Date": "on August 12, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but I can't recommend this product", "Text": "I purchased this item and paired it up with an Amazon Echo. Everything seemed to work well at first, but I can't recommend this product.\nThe first bulb died within 3 months.\nI thought, \"No problem, there is a one year warranty.\"\nSo I proceeded to fill out a warranty claim.\nPhilips created a ticket and asked me questions about its setup, pictures of the bulb, and for the receipt.\nI gave them pictures of the fixture, the bulb, the serial number, receipt, everything.\nIt was used in the correct kind of fixture, used exactly as it was designed for.\nNo response.\nThe second bulb died two months later.\nI filed another warranty claim.\nNo response.\n\nI cannot recommend this product that will die on you while the company ignores warranty requests.\nCompletely unacceptable."}
{"Author": "Austin Duncan", "Date": "on August 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Let The Light Shine On!!", "Text": "What a surprise!\nThis product delivers much more than I was expecting.\nIt is easy and simple to install, the app is also simple to install and use.\nI was greatly surprised at how easily this product connected with my Amazon Echo Dot.\nNow all I have to do is ask and the light turn on or off. Also the Phillips Hue App can be set to turn the lights on\nas an alarm. The lights come on very softly and get brighter over the next half hour this is great because I hate noisy alarms!!\nIts like having the sun wake you up coming through the window."}
{"Author": "Mike", "Date": "on August 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The Best Alexa-Enabled Smart Lighting Solution", "Text": "I am currently in the process of outfitting my home with a number of smart products. Currently, the core \"drivers\" of my setup include Philips Hue,Logitech Harmony, Yonomi, and Amazon Alexa for voice control (via multiple Echos and Echo Dots). I purchased my Hue Starter Kit on Prime Day, and have found it to be an intelligent, smartly-designed product.\n\nThe hub itself must be plugged in to your router via a wired Ethernet connection (I know, no WiFi is a bummer). I purchased a small, CAT5e 6\" Ethernet cable so I could set this on top of my router as to not take up any more space. Once you have the power and Ethernet cables plugged in, setup is incredibly easy and super quick. The kit comes with 2 bulbs, which were immediately detected by the hub as soon as the lights were powered on. You can then add these lights to \"Rooms\" which can be controlled together simultaneously, or you can still control them individually. This product was by far the easiest device to set up so far out of all the smart home products I've purchased. I have since purchased more light bulbs as well as some Sylvania Smart+ Plugs to use with our Hue hub, and setup has been just as easy with every new item I've purchased. \"Rooms\" can even contain a mix of Hue bulbs and smart plugs.\n\nAdding the Hue skill to Alexa was also easy, and automatically imports all the lights, devices, and \"Rooms\" you have set up in the Hue app. Be careful not to name your rooms and/or devices too similarly though. Alexa had a hard time telling the difference between \"Mike's Office Lamp\" and \"Mike's Office Lights\" (for the overhead lights), but works 100% of the time when I used \"Mike's Ceiling Lights\" as the group name for the latter. This seems like a minor issue with Alexa, not with the Hue product.\n\nPROS:\n- Incredibly easy setup\n- Works with Amazon Echo devices\n- Lights are dimmable (via app, Alexa, or physical accessories)\n- Sylvania Smart+ Plug works flawlessly with this hub, despite being a 3rd party manufacturer\n\nCONS:\n- Requires a wired internet connection\n- This version of the starter kit does not come with color bulbs\n\nFor anyone looking for a smart lighting solution that works with Alexa, I highly recommend this product. Extra bulbs can be purchased in highly affordable 3-Packs, and Philips has recently expanded their Hue smart bulb line to include BR30 bulbs as well as E12 Candelabra bulbs. I am thrilled with my purchase of this product, and cannot recommend it enough."}
