{"Author": "KH", "Date": "on August 8, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "NOT easy to setup....", "Text": "I loved the idea of using the Amazon Echo Dot in our kids rooms and incorporating these lights which could (in theory) be controlled by the Dot. We finally got it setup (we are tech-geeks, so it's not like we weren't fully capable...still it was difficult & took a few YouTube videos to find one that worked). It was a 'you-kno-what' to get it all working! And still it doesn't work all the time. I ended up reading that it might help to have ANOTHER hue bridge half-way between our WiFi router & the light bulbs to 'help reception'......geez, so much for easy (not). I love the concept, it just needs some tweaks to actually work & setup easier!"}
