{"Author": "Tolly", "Date": "on August 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No more nudging light switches with your elbows, chin, or nose! Speak and there is light.", "Text": "Where have you been all my life, Hue? This was a breeze to set up, and this is coming from someone who is technologically challenged. Just follow the directions, and if you are pairing it with Amazon Alexa, it's a dream.\n\nFirst you connect the bridge to your wireless router--this requires an email address and confirmation, so it's a bit of a pain at the start, but after that (and it comes with step-by-step instructions), it's all pretty much smooth sailing. Once you download and sign in to the Philips Hue app, Alexa finds it, no problem, so that part is easy.\n\nThe bridge itself will support up to 50 Hue lights, so it's a good initial investment. This kit comes with the bridge and two light bulbs. Once you have the bridge connected, you can tell Alexa what to call each one (living room, hallway, bathroom, bedroom, whatever), and she will turn the lights on or off and even dim them for you.\n\nYou can then say, \"Alexa, turn on the living room (or whatever) light,\" and she will. You can also tell her to dim the light (Alexa, dim the living room light). One thing I love is that you can also say, \"Alexa, turn on the living room light at 100% (or 50%, 36% or whatever),\" and she will do just that. She chirps out \"okay,\" and it's done.\n\nThis is hugely helpful if you come home at dusk or after dark with bags of groceries or are moving from room to room with your arms full of laundry or toys. No more flipping switches with your elbows, chin, or nose! Speak, and the lights will do what you want.\n\nThe bulbs themselves are connected to the hub and the descriptions you put in, so if, for example, you move a Hue bulb from the living room to the bedroom, it will still only work as the living room light until you change the designation in the app.\n\nI do think they are pretty hugely over-priced, so I won't be buying another 48 to fill up my bridge, but strategically placed and depending on your home's layout, this kit can be immensely helpful (and let's face it, it's just plain fun!)."}
{"Author": "Josue V.", "Date": "on August 5, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I can't connect the hue with Echo I spend like 3 hours but I just didn't", "Text": "I finally could connect with Echo and also works with the apple siri but....\n\nTip: You need to make the installation (Echo, hue& bulb) in the same room the first time"}
