{"Author": "K. White", "Date": "on August 3, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bridge must be plugged into your router all the time", "Text": "I'm sure this will get buried in all the reviews here, but I am (probably overly) annoyed that the bridge has to be plugged into your router at all times. There's no reason why it couldn't have a wifi receiver built in, like so many other devices these days. It's not like this is a cheap product, and it wouldn't take much more to add this functionality so it doesn't take up space/a plug on your router. Otherwise it works fine. My next step is to download a third party app so I can program my Alexa to turn on the lights by saying \"lumos\" cause I'm a nerd."}
