{"Author": "Charles K Leja", "Date": "on August 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Praticle use of huewhite light", "Text": "My reason for getting the starter kit was to solve a secific problem. In my house I have a walk in closet that has a pull string light. For years I have thought of having a wall switch put in. This would mean cuttingholes in a wall, installing a switch box, run cable up the wall into the attic and back down to the light. Not an impossible task but not one I would eagerly accept (mostly because of working in an unfinished attic).\n\nI have been researching smart lighting and how I could use it. This turned out to be both an efficient and elegant solution for my problem. I bought the white light kit and a separate switch for the job. Setting up the hub and connecting the light was easy. I set the closet as a separate room so that I could use the switch for only that light. The whole thing took a mater of minutes and cost much less then getting an electrician. So there are practical applications for smart lighting."}
