{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These lights are NOT WHITE. YELLOW.", "Text": "The color temperature on these lights is NOT ADJUSTABLE. They are a disgusting yellow eye-piercing color that cannot be changed. For the true white LED lights, you have to buy the much more expensive AMBIANCE lights that have adjustable color temperature. I was misled into thinking that these lights would be a true white, however this was obviously not true. LED lights should never look this horrifyingly yellow, ever. Very disappointed.\n\nPhillips has a great product here, it's just a shame how much sly misdirection, whether intentional or not, is in the mix here. For a new user, the requirement of a bridge to control the lights is not obvious. It says nothing about a bridge anywhere on the packaging, either. Providing three different types of colored lights, the \"White\" (yellow), \"Ambiance\" and \"Color\" is a little confusing as well."}
