{"Author": "mzgee", "Date": "on July 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "HUE LIT UP MY LIFE", "Text": "I absolutely love the Phillips Hue white lighting system. I lucked out on Prime day and purchased the Deal of the Day that included the Hue Lighting Kit and Echo Dot for the price of just the Lighting Kit. I had already purchased an Echo Dot but I couldn't pass up this deal. I have since purchased an additional 7 white bulbs locally and have them in almost every lamp on my first floor. The bridge readily paired with the wifi and can accommodate up to 50 Hue devices. Although there is a bit of a learning curve, the Hue app is easy to understand and works flawlessly. Best of all, everything pairs with my echo dots. I also like that Hue recommends partner apps for added lighting benefits if needed. I did purchase a few Hue color bulbs but the novelty wore off with the first one after 24 hours. I returned them; for the price, they did not \"a designer setting create.\" I had to play around with renaming the bulbs a few times. Remember after you rename them in the Hue App you must go into the Alexa App and rediscover them each time. I've also found that the shortest and most uniform name possible is probably best and easiest to remember.\nYou have to be pretty specific when you give Alexa a command to dim or increase a bulb. So it's easier if you say:\nright or left lamp, rather than right or left bedside lamp. Also, the uniformity comes in saying lamp or light but not both. At first, I would say right lamp and then left light so both Alexa and I was confused. LOL Just start out simple and it's easy.\n\nI also purchased another popular tunable bulb that didn't require a bridge but I really don't like it. It's not as bright as hue white lights, it's longer, heavier and cost twice as much. I can't send it back because there is nothing wrong with it so I'll keep it.\n\nAgain, I just love HUE lights and in my opinion, you cannot go wrong with the HUE lighting system."}
{"Author": "Hello Kitty", "Date": "on July 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Turning into my parents", "Text": "I feel like I was turning into my parents always asking or telling the kids to \"turn off the lights! \" \"electricity is not free\"\nWe put a playroom into our basement and every night and during the day I had to go down there and turn off the lights.\nNow I can just nicely ask Alexa if the playroom lights are off or she will turn them off without grumbling.\nI am looking now for lights for my kids room because they never turn their bedroom lights off, unfortunately their ceiling lights have 3 bulbs each and that's a little expensive.\nBut I feel so much nicer and less nagging because I never have to tell them to go downstairs and turn off the lights"}
