{"Author": "Chris Allen", "Date": "on July 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great lighting effects", "Text": "These are so easy to set up and to use. I use it with the app and my echo and have no problems whatsoever. I love how I can dim the lights by a certain percentage and set them to automatically start dimming at bedtime and continue to dim until they shut off."}
{"Author": "Willie V. Hughes", "Date": "on July 22, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Hue Will Leave You In The Dark", "Text": "My wife and I are both pretty tech-savvy (she uses an iPhone and a Mac; I use an Android phone and a PC). We loved this Philips Hue system at first, but then it stopped working. More accurately: Philips intentionally disabled the system remotely and forced us to request that they mail a replacement hub / base unit. We finally got the replacement, and then had to spend about an hour setting it up. We needed to create an account online, uninstall and then reinstall apps on both our phones, and then manually enter serial numbers for several light bulbs into the app. Even then, the app had trouble finding them. One problem we still have with the Philips Hue is a significant delay between when our phones can connect with the hub and then we can start controlling the lights.\n\nThe *concept* for this system is great. Colored lights, remote operation, etc. But it's just such a huge pain in the ass, that I'm ready to throw everything in the garbage and go back to using something else. Previously, we had some simple colored LED bulbs that could be controlled by bluetooth. They were cheaper, nearly as good as the Philips system, and a lot less trouble to operate and maintain. We're worried that Philips will once again-- any time in the future-- remotely disable the lighting system rending our investment useless."}
{"Author": "chris L", "Date": "on July 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice", "Text": "Nice lights...works well with the hue system"}
{"Author": "T. P.", "Date": "on July 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best invention ever.", "Text": "This is simply the best idea! I have absolutely loved having these lights. My son is 4 and when he wakes up in the middle of the night he gets to simply ask alexa to turn on his nightlight in the bed room and on come the lights to the proper setting! I cant tell you how much easier this has made his transition to a new room and sleeping at my house. Not to mention how great it is to be able to set the lights from the couch on date night without having to do anything but ask. If you have an echo its an amazing pair to own! If you don't, they HUE app is straight forward, easy to use, and very versatile in how you can label the lights, set the brightness for the three \"scenes\" (bright, dim, nightlight). Ill be adding some of the color variants to my set up soon as well!"}
{"Author": "Syracuse-NY", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great with Alexa!"}
{"Author": "DFrank", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not worth the expensive lights... UNREACHABLE", "Text": "Awful so far. The lights themselves work with the light switch on but they've never connected to the Hub. Followed directions of setting up the hub and plugging into router, turning lights on but lights have never become \"reachable\".\n\nBought to use with Amazon Echo/Alexa.\n\nAdditionally bought extra 3 lights which haven't even been acknowledged by the hub. I've manually typed in serial number but no luck even recognizing lights, let along being \"reachable\"\n\nThe app stays frozen in \"searching for new lights\". I've deleted and re-downloaded the app but that didn't help. I also deleted the lights and researched for them - now they don't even show up (see picture).\n\nAttempted to complete factory restart with pin but that didn't seem to work. Gave up after working on it for 2 hours will try one more time before it gets returned."}
{"Author": "Kenn Smith", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Husband bought a set & loved it so much he bought 2 more sets to ...", "Text": "Husband bought a set & loved it so much he bought 2 more sets to work with his new Alexa Show."}
{"Author": "Dennis Kunstman", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product but has some quirkiness with its operation", "Text": "Works fairly well but I find that if I try and turn on / turn off both lights at the same time, one or the other light does not react to the command from the app. If I interact with each light separately, they respond appropriately. I like that I can still control these bulbs with the normal light switch by turning the switch off then back on eliminating the need to use the Hue application to operate the bulbs."}
{"Author": "Jason C", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it! Use it with amazon echo and works ...", "Text": "Love it! Use it with amazon echo and works great. Like how you can dim from 1% to 100% and set schedules and turn off/on with voice command. Would be nice if it didn't require a hub, but it's not a big deal."}
{"Author": "joselobo", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works good. Distance from Hub to Smart Bulbs (I have ...", "Text": "Works good. Distance from Hub to Smart Bulbs (I have 8) is approx. 50 feet (same floor). Using with Alexa/Echo. Also, using Philips Hue app on my Android smartphone (ok). Also, using \"all 4 Hue\" app on my Amazon Fire 7 tablet (better)."}
{"Author": "Jonathan Ho", "Date": "on July 20, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great bulbs, easy to set up", "Text": "Definitely a good buy considering the world is moving towards a technology-based society. The hub and the bulbs were easy to set up, they had very simple instructions that needed to download their Hue app and voila, you can control it within 5 minutes.\nI further connected to my Amazon Echo and it sync'd up perfectly with no issues. The only slight issue I did find was that if I dim the bulbs anywhere below 15% brightness, it would have minor flickering. Once I go back to 15%, it's fine.\nOtherwise, it's great to have these in my place."}
{"Author": "William Hum", "Date": "on July 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "so save yourself like 30 bucks guys", "Text": "This works perfectly with Alexa.\n\nYou apparently don't even need the hub to make these lights work if you already have an Amazon Echo, so save yourself like 30 bucks guys."}
{"Author": "zTOT", "Date": "on July 19, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "too expensive"}
{"Author": "Carol A McCorkle", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Highly reccommended", "Text": "Wonderful & can dim them through Echo"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not worth it, does not recognize code on bulb", "Text": "This is just what I needed. I haven't learned how to sinc with the Alexia speaker as of yet.\nThese lights works when they want too. I can never control them away from home. I hate I ever purchased this item."}
{"Author": "MikeG.", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not great value.", "Text": "Expensive and finicky - perhaps when the price comes down.."}
{"Author": "edptrs", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Nice lighting product. Works as advertised."}
{"Author": "ALEX P.", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love these lights", "Text": "Love this with my new Alexa. Just have to download the app and sync it together which isn't hard."}
{"Author": "Ron S", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "just ok"}
{"Author": "Mike K.", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Range too limited. Only 1 bulb out of six were reachable.", "Text": "The range claimed is 30 meters but my Hue can't detect lights upstairs at all. Worst part is I went to home D and bought four more bulbs (about $52) but only get the message unreachable when trying to set them up. Also, my home has a lot of recessed lighting and the bulbs for that are $50 each, I would need 4 for the living room, 7 for the kitchen so hard for me to spend that kind of money when I can't get standard bulbs to work. The One bulb out of 6 I have working is kind of cool but the first time I told Alexa to turn it off after everyone was in bed I realized if I did actually get the ones in my bedroom to work I would still have to use the switches after bedtime unless there was an emergency. Can't rate the security use since only 1 works."}
{"Author": "Scott Schissler", "Date": "on July 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it, Gotta try it!!", "Text": "Got the starter pack to test it and see how I liked it before investing in a lot of lights and other accessories. I love this product, I have since added the dimmer switch and more bulbs to my home. So easy and convenient. I can set my porch light to come on and go off at specific times so I don't have to do it every night and morning. Saves electricity, only draws 8w and produces a 60w light, so it saves me 52w per bulb."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 17, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "LOve the convenience but not so happy with bulb Hue", "Text": "works perfectly but as you will review by others, its more of a soft white than a bright daylight! We are getting use to it but wish the yellow hue wasn't so prominent"}
{"Author": "michael john fanta", "Date": "on July 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Can't use unless you are home", "Text": "Unless I'm missing something you have to be home and connected to the home wi fi to use the Hue App.\nTherefore you cannot control the lights from the App when you are away.\nHow at this date and time in tech can you not use the App to control your lights?\nSo too much money for very limited purpose."}
{"Author": "J D", "Date": "on July 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So Happy!", "Text": "I ordered these with my new Echo. I didn't realize they were not the color bulbs but I still love them. They are extremely convenient. When I'm coming into my dark room, I can turn on the lights by voice or the app on my phone (no searching for the fan where my light is sourced). At night you can turn them low or off without having to get up from bed. The lowest setting is a great night light. Works great with Alexa. I will say it does take a moment to set up, and figure out which app to use. I set up the bridge (a bit tough because my internet is in another room than the lights, so I had to go back a forth a little). I used the Alexa app first to set up my voice and then download the Hue app on my phone. The hue app works really well, as does the Apple Home app. You can use all three with the lights, even going from one to another. Next I'm going to get the color bulbs. I'm extremely happy with this purchase and would recommend them to anyone."}
{"Author": "Jim Hayden", "Date": "on July 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great lights", "Text": "Works great, as expected. Highly recommended."}
{"Author": "Tim Proctor", "Date": "on July 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "all is awesome.", "Text": "Made turning lights off SOOO much easier. Just realize the bridge requires a hardwire connection. The lights are wireless though, and once you realize this, all is awesome."}
{"Author": "Mudpaws", "Date": "on July 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "very cool lights love them going to buy the RGB lights next for my gaming room ."}
{"Author": "Lawrence", "Date": "on July 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great and easy", "Text": "I wish everything was this easy to set up. Works like a charm and I love it."}
{"Author": "Garrett G. Graham", "Date": "on July 15, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Useful, fun and looking forward to the next generation", "Text": "These wifi lights respond slower to commands via Alexa then the smart plugs (GYMAN Smart Plug) I was playing with previously. They are also less consistent from what I assume is from less powerful radios. However, the benefit in having the wifi connectivity in the lights themselves provides more flexibility. The Hue app is okay and the bridge is easy to setup. My recommendation to people is that if you are committed to going with smart lights these are a good option. I plan to purchase more of the flood light type for my kitchen when the prices drop a bit. I would like to know if these bulbs put out more heat then standard LED bulbs and if they are expected to last as long as a standard LED bulb. I hope Philips can improve on the following in the next generation of Hue bulbs. 1.) Stronger signal for better connectivity. 2.) Longer warranty to give us confidence that this combination of technology does not shorten the life of the product. 3.) Better instructions by recommending you set up one bulb at a time or figure out a way to determine which bulb is which when you hook up a bunch at once. 4.) Make it easier to name bulbs during setup. 5.) Lower the price of the BR30 floods so I don't have to wait for a reasonable price."}
{"Author": "Pen Ken", "Date": "on July 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Completely awesome!! Just wish the color bulbs didn't cost so much"}
{"Author": "MICHELLE M BERGGREN", "Date": "on July 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic Product!", "Text": "Brilliant! Absolutely Brilliant!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "love it love it"}
{"Author": "Kathleen Elizabeth", "Date": "on July 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Buy - it'll make you smile. I promise.", "Text": "Hue is my first smart home product. When I first used it with the Echo Dot I was amazed and wanted to call people to tell them how awesome it was that I just turned on lights, dimmed them, went to full brightness then turned the lights off just by the sound of my voice. The kit comes w 2 bulbs but I'm buying more today. Kit days it can support 50 bulbs! I'm going to have 10 in groups. This will help w hard to reach/difficult switches, entertain me when I'm bored or when I want to impress friends. Mostly I look forward to use it w the app over manual timers when traveling or for my dogs (so I don't have to pay to keep lights on all day to prevent them from sitting in the dark when daylight savings goes into effect)."}
{"Author": "Bennett M", "Date": "on July 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "easy set up", "Text": "Neat product, easy set up, plays very well with Alexa. Can't ask for more."}
{"Author": "Don Quijote", "Date": "on July 14, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Cannot control anything remotely!", "Text": "The bulbs are ok, and the app works fine so long as you are inside your house (connected to the same wifi as the bridge), but this is supposed to also work when you are outside your home. The description of the product clearly states that \"you can control remotely wherever you are\", but that is not true. Do a Google search of \"no hue connection\" and you will see how many hits your search will produce; that is the message you receive when trying the app when away from the wifi network the bridge is connected to. I tried every tip I found online, and nothing; emailed phillips, and nothing. Customer service is non-existent.\nAdditionally, when you set up an account online with \"meethue\" (something I did only to try to find an alternate way to control the lights when away from home), you are supposed to \"add the bridge\". Problem is, instructions tell you to \"push the button on the middle of your bridge\", and then nothing happens. I tried that while connected to the same wifi, and then also when not connected to the wifi. It does nothing!!\nAll in all, it may be decent product, but if your goal is to be able to take advantage of all features that depend on being able to remotely connect to the bridge (and therefore the lights), do not bother; it does not work!!\nI am returning this, the dimmer switch I bought, and the additional bulbs I ordered.\nSuch a pity, but no sense in paying for something that does not work."}
{"Author": "BofWV", "Date": "on July 14, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dot works great. This however did not work right outta the ...", "Text": "Just purchased this with the Dot during 2017 Prime Day, Dot works great. This however did not work right outta the box. Would not connect to my network. I followed online troubleshooting guides, tried four different Cat5 cables, tried to manually enter an IP etc... nothing worked. fooled with this thing for well over an hour, I have to assume the unit itself was bad."}
{"Author": "Julio", "Date": "on July 13, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No daylight hue option, but working as intended.", "Text": "Bought this item and 2 days later it dropped $5 in price. Also, the bulbs are a SOFT WHITE which are the yellowish looking ones. I would've appreciated if soft white was specified on the title. I thought these could change hue to more of a daylight kind of light bulb. Otherwise, these work as intended."}
{"Author": "a software qa engineer", "Date": "on July 13, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Needs work. Too finnicky.", "Text": "I'm a pretty smart person, but this was finicky and overpriced. It requires an ethernet connection and costs more than an Alexa device itself. Makes no sense. I bought this with Alexa as an Amazon Prime day bundle, but they still do not work well together. Sometimes Alexa would accept my command to \"Turn off the bathroom lights\" but then nothing would happen. Sometimes she would not understand the command. I'd repeat it the same way (close enough) and then it would be recognized just to be dropped (accepted but do nothing)."}
{"Author": "Steve K", "Date": "on July 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great start to your smart home!!", "Text": "These are seriously plug and play. The app is really simple to use and the integration with Alexa is great. No need for timers anymore. Great place to start with your smart home."}
{"Author": "John in OC", "Date": "on July 13, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "too flakey. I bought 3 bulbs but could never ...", "Text": "too flakey. I bought 3 bulbs but could never maintain connectivity to more than 2 at a time. It's a pain to setup because the hub must have a wired connection (ethernet)- but cannot be close to a wifi router. And the bulbs can't be too far apart from one another or the hub. So, after a couple of weeks of moving things and changing zigbee channels I returned to $5 mechanical timers, and they work perfectly."}
{"Author": "Ross B.", "Date": "on July 12, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as expected", "Text": "Works just fine. Only issue arises when someone kills the power by turning the lamp off the normal way. So get in the habit of never turning it on/off except through Alexa!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is an immediate upgrade to any home as it ...", "Text": "This is an immediate upgrade to any home as it lets you have complete control of your lights, whether you have an Android, iPhone, Google speaker, or Amazon Alexa."}
{"Author": "steve schmidt", "Date": "on July 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy to link and manipulate by naming each light."}
{"Author": "ZM", "Date": "on July 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "super convenient.", "Text": "Works well. I have issues connecting when I'm outside of the house but other than that, super convenient."}
{"Author": "Leonardo Oneto", "Date": "on July 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "works perfect and fits well, love it!"}
{"Author": "Kelly E McDonald", "Date": "on July 9, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not if you want to control it from your home computer", "Text": "Do not buy this thinking one of the highly rated third party Windows apps will work. All you will get is the ability to turn the lights on and off. You can't set a schedule or anything. This is a really expensive product that doesn't have an app that supports the operating system most people us in on their home computers. This is only good as a gimmick."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love this product", "Text": "I love this product. I love showing it off to people when they come to my house. It was one of my first buy after I bought my Echo. It was pretty straight forward hooking it up. I also like the fact that it is dimable. Great product."}
{"Author": "Ugene", "Date": "on July 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... bulbs for a couple of months and they work great. I've setup a time schedule and they perform ...", "Text": "I've used these bulbs for a couple of months and they work great. I've setup a time schedule and they perform very well. It's nice to now that I have lights on after dark and I didn't have to leave them on all day. I would definitely recommend these."}
{"Author": "kevin blackwood", "Date": "on July 8, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it", "Text": "Late adapter but love this system. Wish it came i daylight. It awesome to not be able to use a light switch. Have not touch a switch in my house in months"}
{"Author": "Steve", "Date": "on July 8, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bad Product", "Text": "Couldn't Get These To Work.. Returned And Purchased TP Link Bulbs...Which have been easy to install and have worked flawlessly."}
{"Author": "Polite and Kind", "Date": "on July 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Let There Be Light!!!", "Text": "Do not be fooled or upset if you open this and it says all over it that it only works for apple OS. The printed instructions must be old, because the google App store had the updated app for android. I use android version 4.4.4 and his works great on my device. Took just a bit of time to set it up but it was easy to follow. Works great. No more coming into a dark house."}
{"Author": "Scott", "Date": "on July 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These are great! Use them with my iPhone and Echo", "Text": "These are great! Use them with my iPhone and Echo. I have since added a few more light bulbs with no issues. The dimming feature is a really nice touch. I have yet to check out any of the colored lights."}
{"Author": "Felicia", "Date": "on July 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Well worth it", "Text": "These lightbulbs are amazing. They work well with Alexa and the app is great. Since my first purchase I have since added to my arsenal of hue lightbulbs and I've only started replacing them. The first one that I had to replace lasted eight months and the others are going strong still. Great labels and a wonderful convenience."}
{"Author": "jovigirl", "Date": "on July 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Better then a clapper!", "Text": "I got the starter kit for my husband and myself because he is crazy about having to have certain lights on at night to be able to walk through the house, but then he doesnt turn them off and I'm the one who has to get up to turn them off because I'm just as crazy about having the lights off when not in use. This just seemed perfect. I have it connected to an Amazon Dot, Now when he leaves the lights on (two key lights that always get left on) all I have to do is say \"Alexa, turn off the hall light\" and boom, done! Amazing. It's also nice to be able to control the living room lamp from my phone so I can turn the light on before I even get out the car when coming home after dark. Pretty nifty gadget, I can see getting more bulbs to control more of the homes lighting in the near future."}
{"Author": "Lefty", "Date": "on July 5, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not capable with other Alexa platforms", "Text": "Did does not work with my Insteon system!"}
{"Author": "Brax", "Date": "on July 5, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product anyone can appreciate.", "Text": "I really didn't expect to get so much use out of these lights. I figured that they would just be a novelty that I'd play with for a few days and then be done with them like all the other gadgets and tech junk I have laying around.\n\nBoy was I wrong! I could not live without these lights now. I bought this set, an additional Huge White A19 bulb, and a Google Home for my bedroom. Being able to use my phone or voice to control the lights in the room is amazing. Additionally, I can dim the lights in the room to all manners of levels without having to install a dimmer switch which is a huge plus!\n\nFinally, the ability to set up some level of automation (Hue calls them \"Routines\") for Home & away settings, wake up settings, sleep settings, and more, is also very nice. You can have the lights slowly increase in brightness in the morning for a gentle wakeup, and have the alarm as a standby for emergencies rather than go from deep sleep to loud alarm instantly.\n\nI did dock the review 1 star for inconsistent connectivity issues between random lights and the hue base, or the networking of the Hue base.\nOccasionally I'll attempt to turn off all 3 lights only for 1 to stay on, or the hue app will say that it does not have a connection even when I JUST turned the lights on with it.\n\nOverall, a great product that I suggest for anyone and everyone who uses lights."}
{"Author": "Cheryl L. Lester", "Date": "on July 3, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Buyer Beware! Not wireless!", "Text": "I was fooled by the \"wireless\" description. Unfortunately I didn't bother trying to hook up the hue until more than 30 days after I received it. While the lights are controlled wirelessly, the hue station has to be hard wired to you're wireless router. I don't use a standard router in my home for my wireless so no way to connect it. Very disappointed and too late to return it. Guess someone is getting this as a gift this Xmas."}
{"Author": "William R Rawson", "Date": "on July 3, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The light bulbs are great quality. The set up was easy and it ...", "Text": "The light bulbs are great quality. The set up was easy and it works great. Will buy more for the rest of my house."}
{"Author": "Javier Monge", "Date": "on July 3, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "not bad at all", "Text": "Does its job, not bad at all. The light is yellow though, not white as it says in the description"}
{"Author": "Les", "Date": "on July 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome", "Text": "Wow. Love these!! Addicted now"}
{"Author": "Humble Reviewer One", "Date": "on July 1, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Too bad for it seemed like a great solution", "Text": "The concept is great: Remote control over light timing. In practice, this product failed for me, despite numerous attempts at getting it right, including working with Hue's customer service people. Problems experienced included the lights going on and off at random times, and also failure to integrate with my Nest outdoor camera."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on June 30, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not Exactly as Described...", "Text": "Although the product description claims you can dim lights, the included bulbs are not capable of being dimmed. The claim that the bulbs are the equivalent to a 60 watt bulb, is definitely a stretch. They are noticeably dimmer than the 60 watt bulbs they replaced. Note also, that while the bulbs may be wireless, the hub is not. It must be connected via Ethernet. You have to examine the installation photo to see that. Which brings me to another concern. You are supposed to have connectivity for the bulbs anywhere your WiFi signal reaches, I have not found that to be the case. I'm still playing with it so we'll see. Their proposed solution is to insert additional bulbs as they can act as a \"repeater.\" I'm not interested in that as the bulbs are not cheap and one hub should be able to support all but a rather large home. If my experiments continue to be unsuccessful, I'll deduct another \"star.\" For now I'll give it the benefit of the doubt."}
{"Author": "Kin kwan", "Date": "on June 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy Home Automation.", "Text": "Very easy to setup with my Amazon Echo Dot, it took a little bit of time for me to get it going at first since my phone OS was not up to date but after phone update using the software was easy and got it up and running within minutes."}
{"Author": "Caiti", "Date": "on June 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "good product.", "Text": "It occasionally does not respond to the app or Alexa, other than that frustration, good product."}
{"Author": "NG", "Date": "on June 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "it works. the app is poor"}
{"Author": "Lio Faamasino", "Date": "on June 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent", "Text": "Best purchase I've made in a long time. Works great love turning my lights on and off from my phone."}
