{"Author": "Marissa Ruggiero", "Date": "on June 27, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does NOT work on existing DIMMER switches", "Text": "I recently received an Amazon Echo with Alexa as a gift so I decided to upgrade my first floor lighting with these \"White\" LED light bulbs. I bought the bridge, 27 total bulbs, and 7 dimmers. The cost was $600. First thing, the bulbs are not white, they are yellow. I had white non-smart LED bulbs already in place in my house and there was a significant difference. Not the biggest deal in the world, but I wish they disclosed that. I hooked up my bridge without a problem, I was able to easily download the Hue app on my iphone and it didn't take too long too set everything up by grouping the bulbs together in different rooms (living room, dining room, kitchen, porch, etc). The software allows each bulb to \"wink\" which identifies each bulb, which is a very nice feature. With a little patience I was able to set up all 27 bulbs and even managed to transfer the information to the 'Homekit\" app on my iphone that I was not even aware existed until this process. This allows you to control the lights from the your iphone and Siri without even going into the Hue app. The benefit to this is you can put all of the light groupings in your \"favorites\" on your iphone. You simply 'swipe up' from the bottom and they are there. This ease of software set up is the only reason why this is getting a 3 star rating and not a 1 or 2. I also set up 7 hue dimmer switches. Pretty simple process. Was able to put these dimmers anywhere I wanted. The are a small portable remote that connect to the wall plate magnetically. Very nice feature, You can turn the lights on/off and dimmer them from these devices if you do not want to use your iphone, siri, or alexa. Again, very nice. Here is my major complaint which I had no idea about. If you have any existing light fixtures hardwired to a dimmer switch, the hue lights will NOT TURN OFF. Apparently, Hue Lights do not work well with existing dimmer switches. When these are working properly, all of your existing wll switches will always be turned on. This doesn't mean that your lights will be always on. The lights will be controlled by your iphone, alexa, or Hue Dimmers. There is no reason to ever touch your existing outlets. If any of your existing light fixtures connected to a dimmer switch, you will only be able to turn them off by actually turning off the light switch, thus making the new 'smart bulbs\" completely useless. Now I have to spend more money getting 6 new non-dimming light switches for these light fixtures. It is disgraceful Hue does not prominently share this information in their product description."}
{"Author": "Vibin ramakrishnan", "Date": "on June 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Working good so far .."}
{"Author": "Bartleby", "Date": "on June 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice wireless lighting solution, not perfect", "Text": "DId not get five stars because the hue hub included in this package needs an Ethernet connection to your router (will not join your wifi network), so if you are out of Ethernet ports, you either need a splitter or another lighting solution. Note that you cannot change the color of the bulbs unlike some other Philips hue products. Having said that, it is great for my elderly parents, because paired with an echo dot in their room, they can turn the lights on and off by voice command instead of having to get out of bed in the dark."}
