{"Author": "Amazon User", "Date": "on June 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good for standalone lamps, not so much for larger implementations with more bulbs, like a room with recessed lighthing.", "Text": "It was a good product, however does not meet all of my needs.\n\nThe features in the app and the integration with Alexa was great. Many options to set different times, brightness levels and even random. This works best on standalone lamps that you can switch on and forget about them.\n\nWhen buying, please consider the following. With recessed lighting, you may need 2 or more per circuit, which really isn't an issue since you can group your bulbs, but you will need so many. 1 smart switch and a SmartThings hub would handle that and many rooms for maybe cheaper. Initial costs for this method would be more expensive, but would be easier to scale up. Instead of buying 6 bulbs, 1 switch would be all you need to add to your hub.\n\nThe second issue I had was for the standalone lamps, were that when off, they were still pretty warm. That was pretty much it."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on June 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best purchase I ever made", "Text": "Best purchase I ever made. It is so nice to open the front door and tell Alexa to turn on the light and it happens. No more stumbling in the dark. Absolutely worth every penny!"}
