{"Author": "Jonathan Feist", "Date": "on June 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great place to start your smart home adventures", "Text": "Home automation, what can I say, Philips Hue is top dog for a reason, they're good. As a basic starter kit, I am very happy with this purchase. The system works almost flawlessly and ties into my Amazon Alexa ecosystem very well. I used to mess with a physical light switch, now I just tell my lights to turn on, boom done.\n\nThe best part of this kit is that you get the Hub for future expansion, but do not have drop $200 to get started using the smart lights.\n\nBasically, if you are looking to figure out how smart lights fit into your world without spending too much, and are looking for something that will expand into more, this is a solid purchase."}
{"Author": "Christian Fernandez Cegarra", "Date": "on June 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "great!!"}
{"Author": "Grandpa Jim", "Date": "on June 20, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Stellar Product, App is \"Meh\"", "Text": "Hue lights are a really cool and innovative product. Initially, I shrugged these lights off as a novelty that wasn't worth the price point. However, I was ignorant of the home security value of this product. You can easily set and update timers for shutting your lights on or off. It's great to be able to turn on the lights in the house before you get home.\n\nMy only issue with this project is that the app doesn't perform consistently. Often, one or two lights will become unresponsive and require troubleshooting. Phillips needs to take steps to make sure that their app is better at consistently and quickly recognizing Hue lights that have already been set up.\n\nThat being said, I have every intention to add more Hue lights to more rooms in my house. I feel like the weakness of the app will improve without having to buy new lights to reap the benefits of the update - not a lot of risk in purchasing now. If things change, I will follow up and update my review."}
{"Author": "Edward", "Date": "on June 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good and Useful while some tricky in the software", "Text": "Very good and useful! It really makes home smarter. But I need to spend some time to figure out the routine in the official app. The \"Away/Home\" seems tricky as well. In terms of this function, I like the Nest thermostat much better. Another thing I don't like it that if you use Alexa to turn on the light, it will remain the brightness when it was off last time. You have to dim it again to 100%. (I think most people want 100% brightness at the time when the lights are on at the beginning)"}
