{"Author": "jon p thom", "Date": "on June 3, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Mixed results", "Text": "Update: the issues with HomeKit seem to be resolved.\n\nWhen everything works as it should, these are great. They do have intermittent issues executing scenes with HomeKit, and occasional issues finding individual bulbs. I have not yet been able to determine if the scene issue is cause by my Apple TV not sending commands or the Hue bridge not receiving or executing them. If I were to do it again, I'd do all Caseta, as I have a mix of both. So far the Caseta work flawlessly, as I have come to expect from Lutron."}
{"Author": "Mercedes", "Date": "on June 3, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Expensive but worth it", "Text": "We absolutely love the Phillips hue bridge and bulbs. We use it every night and I love that I can add more than the two bulbs to one bridge so I can control my lights from anywhere at anytime."}
{"Author": "Sleerts", "Date": "on June 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Replaced my outdoor lights, might need to make my home even smarter now", "Text": "Got sick of the programmable switch that never seemed to take into account daylight savings...pulled the trigger on these for outdoor lights and couldn't be happier. So far they've taken a beating outside almost out of wireless range but still work great. I also like the fact that you can run them at full power or dim."}
