{"Author": "Rob", "Date": "on May 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These ended up working great but admittedly the hub wasn't as easy to set ...", "Text": "These ended up working great but admittedly the hub wasn't as easy to set up as I thought it would be. Namely because I don't have a free spot on the back of my router so had to connect it to the network via one of the 2 switches I have. I should have read closer as I thought I could simply connect the hub to wi-fi versus having to hard-wire to the router. My fault. Anyway, now that's it's set up - it works great. I bought 3 more lights for various rooms so now I have 5 running flawlessly off this hub. Very nice."}
{"Author": "Bryan Gonzalez", "Date": "on May 29, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "this is disappointed and expected real white lights", "Text": "I am struggling while writing this review because the Lights works very well and integration with Amazon Echo (Alexa) is flawless, however don't get fooled by the description, these are not while lights but 1950\u2019s style yellow.\nI went and reviewed again all descriptions and couldn\u2019t find anything different that \u201cwhite\u201d light. For me, this is disappointed and expected real white lights.\nAs information for everybody, these are YELLOW lights but description says white."}
