{"Author": "southshore74", "Date": "on May 27, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Will not connect to Alexa", "Text": "Buyer Beware! Alexa Cannot find it, I bought 2 of these kits, both worked fine using our iPhone. However when trying to connect to Alexa, Alexa could not locate the Hue Bridge. I noticed nowhere on the Philips boxes did it say compatible with Amazon Alexa, however all over the internet it does say it works with Alexa. What is also weird is one Hue kit came in a cardboard box with a couple of Philips stickers on it and another kit came in a official Philips Box you would buy at the store. I have tried every reset there is and every manufactures app there is with no fix insight. All I wanted was the on/off feature with this kit, which worked fine with our iPhone, but not with Alexa. I am a prime member and had no issues returning both kits. These kits also only come with the pee-yellow (warm white) bulbs, which I hate. If you like the Daylight bulbs (bright white) you will have to fork out and extra $40 a piece for those bulbs. If you notice all the 4 and 5 star reviews are with using the Philips Hue app only, not with connecting to Amazon Alexa, watch out!"}
{"Author": "Nancy Drew fan", "Date": "on May 27, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Was disappointed", "Text": "Revising my review, bought the set May 13th all worked while in the house. Yesterday all was fine then this morning lamp one has been unreachable. It turns on via the app. but not through voice command.\nHave other plugs that work great with Alexa such as fan, coffee pot, tv and etc. Not sure why the hub has issues."}
