{"Author": "Shawn", "Date": "on May 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it the kit was easy to set up", "Text": "Love it the kit was easy to set up. So easy to set up as long as you download the Philip Hue App."}
{"Author": "VonPadraig", "Date": "on May 11, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Cute toy, waiting for a stronger, more functional lamp", "Text": "Idea is really nice. Execution, overall is great when I see it used at friend's homes. HUGE GLARING FLAW. Lumens about half what are needed in most living room lamps. Standard recommendation for lumens in a room is 20 lumens/sq foot. For a 250 sq foot room. That would require 6 or so of these lamps. I use less lumens in my room, but would still be required to put in more lamps AND not have the light be bright enough to read or do crafts with. When a 1500 lumen lamp (aka bulb) is made, you bet, I will buy these. Until then, they are a toy."}
{"Author": "tj", "Date": "on May 11, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "like but sometimes the bridge is slow to wake up ...", "Text": "like but sometimes the bridge is slow to wake up for Alexa to connect. Very expensive to add bulbs. The app is nice but still cannot get it to recognize when I come home to turn on automatically I think because bridge goes to sleep."}
{"Author": "Andrew C.", "Date": "on May 11, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart Lighting is the way to go!", "Text": "Good bulbs with good color saturation. Would like them to be just a little brighter. Using with Amazon Echo, setup first bulb easily but the second bulb took some time and several attempts to be discovered by the hub. Bought these and some smart sockets for a neighbor who suffered a bad accident and is confined to a bed while recovering. This is so helpful for her to be able to turn on lights and her fan as needed without having to call for someone else to help her."}
