{"Author": "BASE 5_NYC", "Date": "on April 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is definitely one of my new favorite things.", "Text": "This is definitely one of my new favorite things. I have it hooked up to Alexa via my Echo & Dot and also on my network for remote access over the Internet. It's incredibly useful and helpful. At first it seems like a toy for the ultra lazy but it's become a part of how my house runs. It's great for helpful tasks like turning lights on when you're hands are full or simple things like turning lights down when watching a movie. It's also great to be able to turn the lights on before we walk in with the app or from my office if I'm working late. The bulbs are also nice, very bright with a nice warm color & can be dimmed down very low. It's extremely simple & quick to set up and requires no maintenance whatsoever. I'm sure they'd be nice as is but using Alexa makes them much better. They are pretty expensive though once you start outfitting other rooms so that's something to think about. If you're into tech or the IOT these are a nice place to start. - If you're on a budget but want the full \"Jarvis\" effect get it with the Amazon Dot, works just fine with that."}
