{"Author": "Brian V. Hill.", "Date": "on April 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pleasant surprise, they really do work!", "Text": "I bought this kit to set up for use with my Nest outdoor cameras.\nI first set up the bridge, note that the bridge is hardwired to the router so it needs to be in a suitable location to access the bulbs via wifi.Set up was real easy and took just a few minutes including assigning their names and timimgs. I then set them to operate with the Nest Cams, I was able, without much effort, to have them operate on a regular, or irregular cycle for normal daily use and to work with the Nest when we are away from home, in this setup if the cameras pick up activity one or other of the lights will come on and go off after a while and reset.\nOverall I am very pleased with them and will be adding more to the bridge as I need them."}
