{"Author": "Bookman Bruce", "Date": "on April 15, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best Home Lighting Solution I Have Used! A Permenant Fixture in Our Home!", "Text": "I cannot say enough about how much I love my Phillips Hue lighting control system.\n\nWe bought this starter kit to try it out, and see how useful it would be. We quickly bought additional bulbs to expand it out to other rooms -- and will be buying the color lighted bulbs over the summer for our outdoor spaces.\n\nThe initial setup is fairly easy to get it going. Once you have the hub synced with the app, creating the schedules and room definitions is fairly simple. One criticism (which took a star away) is that every time you add a bulb, you have to physically touch the hub to make the bulb sync. I keep my hub hidden away and out of sight, so this is inconvenient for me to have to touch the sync button on the hub. Otherwise, the product itself is great and perfect for our home. We have bulbs in our living room, each of the kids rooms and our front porch light. All of them are on schedules -- and this REALLY helps when the kids forget to turn their lights off. Using the app is easy -- and the kids love to use the app to control the lights in their rooms. It is awesome to be able to simply schedule the front porch light to go on and off at specific times. My wife works nights, so I have the porch light scheduled to go on 20 minutes before she gets home, and go off 20 minutes after she gets home. When we aren't home, we have the living room light go on and off at specific times and the porch light does the same. You can have special schedules, or just have daily ones. Want the lights to detect when you are close to home and go on at that time? Yep, you can do that.\n\nReally a great product -- we even have it tied in to our Amazon Echo and our Apple HomeKit on our AppleTV. Can't say enough great things about this product."}
