{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on March 30, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Bulbs only work with Hue Hub (Not directly with Wink)", "Text": "I didn't really want to buy this product, having just dropped $300 on the Wink + 4x Hue Color bulbs but as it turns out you have to use the Hue hub no matter what the setup, much to my dismay. I tried pairing the 3rd gen hue bulbs directly to the Wink as a standalone Zigbee endpoint (IEEE 802.15.4), but Philips implementation is so bad that the lights would disconnect from the Wink after sending a simple \"ON/OFF\" command. Now im almost $400 deep just to get my lights working. BTW, the hue hub app only works on the local network so you can't control things remotely, or create simple automation scripts such as turning off all the lights when your smartphone is no longer on-prem. The Wink will run you $100 but I still stand by it. I am mostly disappointed in Philips because these are supposedly the best bulbs on the market yet they haven't even implemented ZigBee properly."}
