{"Author": "Phillysub", "Date": "on March 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Introduction into the world of smart homes", "Text": "Now that I own an amazon echo, I was ready to take that first step into the 'smart home' venture. Purchased the hue starter kit to get started. I got 2 light bulbs along with the hub. Setting up was so simple..you screw in the bulbs, initiate the hub, sign into the hue app, have the app acknowledge the bulbs....then you go into the Alexa app so that she can find the bulbs. You identify the location of the bulbs, and you're basically set. I won't use these for all of my lights. Just those that are not easily turned on by a switch."}
{"Author": "Norman W. Pressman", "Date": "on March 25, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The instructions are less than great especially for older people but once I figured them ...", "Text": "When I got the package it said (at least I thought) that you needed an I phone to make it work. I then scheduled a return. Then I realized I has misread the description. The instructions are less than great especially for older people but once I figured them out and cancelled the return the product was fine."}
