{"Author": "M. R. Chobanian", "Date": "on March 22, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The reason for the lowrating: was that installation requires ...", "Text": "The reason for the lowrating:was that installation requires plugging the supplied Ethernt cable into your wireless acess point, my A&T Uverse has a Motorolawap2500 WAP, which has no ether net sockets except for the one that connects it to the modem; but I had a Netgear WIFI extender that did, so that's what I'm usingI suppose it's my fault for not thinking o check."}
