{"Author": "hex2099", "Date": "on March 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Installed the bulbs in my bedroom and it works perfect with my Echo", "Text": "Installed the bulbs in my bedroom and it works perfect with my Echo. Love the convenience of being able to turn the lights on or off from the bed or another room. Also, being able to dim the lights just by using my voice is awesome! Can also be controlled via the app on my phone. Definitely would recommend and will buy more bulbs for other rooms."}
{"Author": "Ginger Wright", "Date": "on March 18, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very disappointed", "Text": "Said that it goes with Alexa but it has to hook up to router and if you run your router through the cable then you can't run it. No instructions for other solutions"}
{"Author": "Brown Bear", "Date": "on March 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It's 2017 up in here!", "Text": "I recently decided to see what the whole commotion was in regards to an \"Automated Home.\" Several Amazon Dots and various smart accessories later, my home is tricked out and I must say, it's awesome. This is one of the rare purchases and features that makes me stop and say \"Damn, the future is now\". Out of all the smart accessories I purchased, the Hue is my favorite. It took all of 3 minutes to setup and has been working like a charm. I initially purchased the TP Link version of smart lighting, but they couldn't stay on my network for the life of them. One quick exchange later, and the Hue was here and set up. It's quick, responsive, pairs with Alexa in no time at all, and the best thing yet; it's almost endlessly upgradable (for the normal sized home, that is.) if you have been throwing the idea of automating your home around, and have a couple houndred dollars lying around (I automated pretty much everything for around $400 which includes the Amazon Dots for a few different rooms), pull the trigger. You won't regret it. Just make sure your Network has full coverage of your home to prevent frustration. Also, to anyone disappoint the hub is not WIFI based there is a reason for that. Reliability. This hub transmits the signal to all of your Hue devices. Nothing would frustrate people more than a dodgy wireless signal relaying their request to their other devices. A hardwired connection ensures every relay is transmitted correctly and appropriately. Hard wired connections may be \"ugly\" but they ensure quality transfer rates!"}
{"Author": "Colly", "Date": "on March 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I LOVE these lights! They're so much fun!"}
{"Author": "James K. Hardy", "Date": "on March 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it.", "Text": "A really nice introduction to home automation. Installs in minutes and plays well with my iPhone and my Echo. Already ordered more bulbs."}
{"Author": "Brian P. Schwind", "Date": "on March 17, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "App is Very Inconsistent!", "Text": "I had been using a couple Wemo smart bulbs and was slightly disappointed. I thought that the Hue bulbs were going to be much better. Boy was I wrong. Basically it is the Hue iOS app that is really bad. The app itself is not very intuitive and the timers I set are so inconsistent it is worthless. Sometimes a bulb will be on, but the app says it is off. Other times bulb is off and app shoes it is on. I thought Philips would put out a better product than this. I now have a better appreciation for my Wemo Bulbs. They may not work with Alexa but at least they work with the Wemo App."}
{"Author": "jasper dean", "Date": "on March 16, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Disappointingly inconsistent", "Text": "Simply put, it doesn't work as often as it should, or as well as it should. When I get in range of my (very strong) wifi, it takes too long to 'sync up'.\nAnd even if i've been in the house for awhile, it will frequently return a 'no connection' error.\nNo rhyme, no reason, no way to troubleshoot. Just periodically doesnt feel like working.\n\nBut when it does, yeah. Cool product."}
