{"Author": "kurt gibson", "Date": "on March 15, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "and life was great, until one day the voice commands for turning ...", "Text": "It's extremely hard to hook up. You need to hire someone with an IQ of about 140. After I had to pay to get someone to link the bulbs with my Alexa count, it all worked, and life was great, until one day the voice commands for turning on the lights just stopped working, for no reason. I won't get any more bulbs."}
{"Author": "Don Schilling", "Date": "on March 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love the dimming feature as I can tell Alexa", "Text": "I currently have these installed on my night stands and use the Amazon Echo (Alexa) to connect to them. Alexa occasionally has issues connecting to them but it's rare. I love the dimming feature as I can tell Alexa, \"Alexa, set my light (or my girlfriend's light) to 20%.\" And voila! It's done. I'll be buying more in the future."}
