{"Author": "VP", "Date": "on March 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This system is just plain awesome!! I'm loving it", "Text": "This system is just plain awesome!! I'm loving it. I don't need crazy colorful lights...I just like regular white light...and this fits the bill. Now, you may ask, why am I'm loving it? What's the difference in just getting a simple wifi smart plug and plugging your lamp in it? Well I love the dimm factor. These bulbs can dim on command via the Echo Dot. I can say, Alexa, Dim livingroom light 30%...and boom...it's done. You can program the lights to come on or off any day of the week or every day, at what ever time you want.\n\nThe two best features I like are the gradual brightness and the gradual darkness. So, during the winter months when I wake up before the sun rises...I used to have hit the snooze on my alarm clock once if not twice....and even I wasn't really awake even after the second snooze...just plain groggy. Well, snooze no more for me. Yes, since I've set this up, I have not hit the snooze button once. When the alarm goes off, I'm awake without issues ready to go. How you ask? Simple, I have it set up at the time my alarm clock goes off...but the Hue system would gradually brighten 10 minutes before my alarm actually goes off. This tells your body it's day time and time to wake up.\n\nAt night, I have a particular time I go to sleep...so 30 minutes before it's time for bed, the Hue system will gradually dim to till its completely off.\n\nYou can control this system by turning the light on or off even while you're away from your home."}
{"Author": "Charles Jones", "Date": "on March 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great product. Can set it to go on as I get home."}
{"Author": "JD", "Date": "on March 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great.", "Text": "Simple. Works great. A few little bugs and a little pricey, but they work as advertised."}
{"Author": "Being Juan", "Date": "on March 7, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Hue White A19 Starter Kit", "Text": "I decided to dive into IoT and this was my first purchase. I must say, pleasantly surprised. Easy setup, plenty of 3rd party support so there's an endless supply of applications for most platforms. My only concern is lack of 2 Factor Authentication on Hue's website that allows 3rd party sites, such as IFTTT, to connect to your Hue account. While it's very secure in adding applications that directly interact with bridge, Phillips falls short in protecting users who decide to use 3rd party services, not to be confused with 3rd party apps that are physically authenticated via the button on the bridge. As such, think twice about creating an account with Hue until they implement 2FA when accessing your account via 3rd party service. This security hole keeps me from rating it 5 stars."}
