{"Author": "Journeyman", "Date": "on March 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Yes, buy this one to get started", "Text": "For anyone looking to get into home automation or who has an alexa they want to trick out with peripherals, this is a good place to begin. Easy to set up and use, allows for control while we are home and when we are out of the house. We use Amazon's Alexa as a voice-control hub and have gotten some neat programs from IFTTT (If this then that) which allows us to setup the lights to respond to dozens of situations. This is really a nice. We loved it so much we bought one as a gift for our in-laws."}
