{"Author": "Eric", "Date": "on March 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good entry kit to the Philips Hue system", "Text": "I've decided to try out the Philips Hue lighting systems as my first venture into \"smart homes\", and ordered this A19 Starter Kit (2 white bulbs + 1 bridge), as well as a Lightstrip Plus. So far so good, in the future I'll be going with color bulbs, since the white ones aren't that versatile, but if you just need a bunch of regular white lightbulbs that you can control remotely then these would be fine. The bridge was a quick and easy setup, lightbulbs are the same as any other LED lightbulb and should screw right in."}
{"Author": "Kingfish", "Date": "on March 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love this. Once you get it setup you won't ...", "Text": "Love this. Once you get it setup you won't want to go back to conventional switches. We've coupled ours with the Alexa Dot. Now I tell my lights when to come on and go of. Excellant product."}
{"Author": "Tomgadgets", "Date": "on March 4, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good but limited range", "Text": "Great item, but keep in mind the range of Zigbee is quite short. Best to keep distance to 1-2 walls MAX and on the same level, otherwise the bridge will not be able to control the lights."}
