{"Author": "Chris", "Date": "on February 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "THE HOLE HUE BRAND IS AWSOME"}
{"Author": "Reviewer", "Date": "on February 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "A great way to start your adventure controlling the lights and ambiance in your home with Alexa.", "Text": "We already had a Wemo switch that had allowed us to control a single switch, in terms of turning it on and off. This Hue set-up from Phillips is a million times better! In this set you get the Hub - which you need to control all of the Hue lights you install. You only need the one Hub. We also added a color capable bulb to this set and we find ourselves with a large variety of options that we didn't have before! We can dim the lamps as we choose, set \"scenes\" which are basically pre-sets and control all of it through Alexa or the app on our phones.\n\nWe are very impressed and have only just started playing with them. No doubt we will be adding more bulbs over time."}
{"Author": "Rurdy4this", "Date": "on February 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great concept, room for improvement", "Text": "I love the audibly controlled lights. Via Alexa, my mother has the safety of being able to turn lights off/on without traversing any area in the dark. Many additional convenience aspects, but for safety it can't be beat.\nThat said, it doesn't always recognize the command or think the light is connected to the network. Sometimes it takes 3-4 attempts, but with persistence it always works.\nI also put a bulb in a dimmable lamp. It would flicker on the dim setting, and burned out in 2 days."}
