{"Author": "Sue", "Date": "on February 14, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips doesn't care the item stopped working!", "Text": "I thought I loved it, but the product stopped being recognized by the Echo Dot about 3 weeks after hooking it up. I bought it late December for a birthday gift for my husband's birthday on Jan 17th. So, by the time the thing stopped working, it was too late to return. I tried to contact the Philips, but have heard nothing back from them. We bought some other items to hook up as well, but the Hue Hub doesn't recognize them either. And, yes....they are compatible with the Hub. I'm very disappointed. I feel the Philips Hue starter kit is a waste of money, and Philips does not seem to care about fixing the problem."}
{"Author": "Wendy", "Date": "on February 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome lights", "Text": "Love the ability to set my lights from home and away from home. Great product!!"}
{"Author": "ASVY", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not what I expected, or wanted.", "Text": "It's difficult to give a star rating for this item. For what it is, I would give it 4 stars, but for what I expected, this deserves 2\u2014therefore I am giving it a 3.\n\nLet me start with what I expected\u2014a light system that can be voice controlled through my Alexa, with color (warmth, white to yellow) options, that is dimmable. My living room has two ceiling lights, each requiring 2 bulbs. I purchased this starter kit plus two additional bulbs for $109 at my local Best Buy (same prices as here). Seeing as I only like the whiter (I typically buy GE Reveal bulbs) color, and therefore expected to use only that color in the spectrum, I thought that $109 was a fair price for a dimmable light in that temperature. These lights are NOT adjustable, in terms of warmth. The \"soft white\" color advertised is more like an intense yellow. My entire living room lit up in yellow tones. I searched through all settings to see if I could change it to a whiter color, and learned that I needed the Philips Hue White Ambiance set instead. After looking up prices I learned that for a similar set (hub plus 4 lights, or starter kit plus 2 lights) it would cost me $175-180. If $109 was a fair an acceptable price, $175-180 is exorbitant in my opinion, especially considering that I would only use one warmth setting. This is why I am returning them. When they have a white color option for the same price I will buy them then.\n\nFor what it is, here are the pros and cons of the lights and device:\n\nPros:\n- Easy to use once set up\u2014Alexa integrates easily;\n- Discrete\u2014as long as you have white furniture, or a way to hide the hub behind a picture frame, it is easily out of the way;\n- Dimmer works well\u2014good response time and all my lights dimmed equally if I gave the command (I heard other brands have issue with this). Each light and each bulb can be dimmed by a different amount if you give the command (you just need to create groups);\n- Works well with Siri commands on my phone.\n\nCons:\n- The setup is a bit confusing. The instructions start with \"turn all lights on,\" they don't mention that bulbs should be in lights that are turned on. Step 2 is to plug and pair the hub, step 3 is to download the app and continue setup there. Upon reading these, I wasn't certain that the bulbs wouldn't require close proximity to the hub for initial pairing of lights to hub in the app portion of the instructions, so I ignored step 1 and went to 2 and 3 instead. Considering my lights are on the ceiling and require a ladder to install (high ceilings), I wanted to make sure that I wouldn't need to complicate the installation process down the line. I'm all for 1,2,3 setup instructions, but these weren't worded well.\n- Had a few connectivity glitches at first when pairing with Siri. Had to restart the apps a couple of times to connect.\n- Not having choice of color warmth. I'd be happy to have only one color warmth (white or yellow) provided by this bulb, but I'd like to be able to choose which color. These bulbs provide shockingly yellow light, and this isn't improved when they are dimmed.\n- The fact that a hub is needed for these bulbs is a bit frustrating, an extra device in the house. I will look forward to future models that won't require a hub.\n\nOverall, an item that simplifies life\u2014if you also have the Alexa\u2014voice commands make this item really great."}
{"Author": "Christian N", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pre-historic device", "Text": "I bought this starter kit and I was surprised to find out that the hub had to be wired to your router. I mean every device you buy these days is wifi. This one is not! You gotta plug it and connect physically to your router! And on top of that its blue tooth capability is short range! So If you put a bulb two rooms away it is out of reach! Come on Philips, hello! What do I need next, a pricey range extender? I'm not payin' 70 bucks for a non-wifi short-range device. Return, return, return."}
{"Author": "Joseph A. Baratta Jr.", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great with either my phone or my Echo Dot."}
{"Author": "Mitchell", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "WILL STOP WORKING AFTER ONLY A COUPLE MONTHS", "Text": "It worked right away when I got it, but started to work worse and worse as time went on. Not a long time either. I've had these bulbs for about 2 1/2 months and at this point they basically don't work at all. They rarely connect, and when they do, they are very unresponsive. Definitely not worth the money. And for some reason they make it very difficult to contact them with any feedback. I would recommend looking at other types of smart light bulbs before throw away $70."}
{"Author": "DBV", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great place to start", "Text": "This was my first attempt to use a smart home product with Alexa and found it to be easy to set up and use. The only issue I had was connecting via wifi to my router. I was unable to connect wirelessly but had no issues when connecting it directly via LAN. Works like a charm and is very responsive to voice commands."}
{"Author": "Ed", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "So much fun."}
{"Author": "Alton A.", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it with the Amazon Echo", "Text": "I use these ALL THE TIME! They work great with my Amazon Echo dot and are easy to set up. Lots of options from the app on my phone and tablet."}
{"Author": "AMM", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "this was easy to install", "Text": "On the plus side, this was easy to install, and it works perfectly from the phone or google home. However, the main reason I wanted it was to be able to set up routines, so our front door lights work automatically at set times. For this it is terrible - it will work for 2-3 days and then the routines will spontaneously switch to \"off\", leaving the lights either on or off permanently.\n\nNo amount of troubleshooting has solved this, and if you search online for answers you mostly find other people complaining about the same problem, or recommending third-party apps, programming, etc. Someday someone is going to get the automated home thing right, but this isn't it."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Set up and re-set up", "Text": "We had trouble getting both lights to sync at first. We took care of that then one day they stopped responding. We had to reset the system to get it to work again. Overall it's handy and the ability to dim with Alexa is a cool feature."}
{"Author": "patches", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Stopped working a few months after first use. Could not re-set."}
{"Author": "Steveo", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "This was a great addition to the Alexa package."}
{"Author": "LilLJStuff", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Magic lightbulbs!", "Text": "This product is amazing for someone who is carrying a baby or laundry 95% of the time, and is admittedly just plain lazy and/or forgetful the other 5%. I am always forgetting to turn off lights when I finally get an opportunity to go to bed, and this is going to totally resolve me having to drag myself back up. My husband said the price per additional bulb was ridiculous, but after just one day of us being able to switch off just two of the lights from bed, he asked if I would add to our collection. The dimming feature is great for weary morning eyes or for mood lighting (wink wink). It is great that only one hub needs to be purchased for a home (unless you have more than 50 light bulbs, I think). It was extremely easy to set up and works flawlessly with Echo Dot, which is just fun! In fact, my daughter's first sentence may be, \"Alexa, office light on 20%.\" I definitely highly recommend this little system... Life is hard enough; let these magical lightbulbs let you take it easy once in a while : )"}
{"Author": "Jeff Taylor", "Date": "on February 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works as advertised"}
{"Author": "David Stern", "Date": "on February 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love It!", "Text": "Very easy to setup. Works exactly as described. Love the dim to any % feature. Will definitely buy more."}
{"Author": "Shookn", "Date": "on February 11, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hub NEEDS to be wired to your router", "Text": "It wasn't as I expected. I thought I would be able to wirelessly connect to my internet, but you need to be wired. My router is in another room and to run an ethernet cord from the room I wanted to install the Hue would be ridiculous. I tried connecting the hub to my computer and use my computer as an access point to connect to the wifi but that didn't work. I would have given it one star, but since I just used the bulbs as a regular light without the smart capabilities, that bumped it up to 2 stars."}
{"Author": "MM", "Date": "on February 11, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good product", "Text": "Workes well with Alexa/Echo love the convenience. However, if you used these on lights that also has a wall switch. Alexa cannot operate the lights if you shut it off at the switch. I am sure it would be the same if you shut off a lamp manually."}
{"Author": "RoDeYo", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "**** works well independently and with Echo", "Text": "works well, easy setup and works with Echo"}
{"Author": "David Sanchez", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hue App misses the mark", "Text": "Bought this starter kit to begin the process of automating lighting in my home - also have outlets from WeMo and TP-Link and the Philips Hue app is frustrating to me because, unlike the other apps, it does not have an easy to set vacation mode either at the household or light level. On top of that, I find the hub model too complicated and much prefer to use direct connect devices going forward."}
