{"Author": "Hammerhead", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Has some bugs", "Text": "The bulbs will dim on command, but will not brighten. Tried command\"brighten\" \"change to 100%\" & \"turn the hell up!\". Need to use the hue app for that until I find some helpful help. Other than that, it's working fine and I'll add to the two bulbs we have."}
{"Author": "JoLynn Oten", "Date": "on February 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy set-up. Works well with Alexa", "Text": "Plug the hub into an electric socket and a router. Find it with a mobile app. Screw in the bulbs. The app find them. Alexa finds them through the hub. She turns the lights on & off and dims them on command. The set up is quick and easy."}
{"Author": "JamieM", "Date": "on February 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very cool! I love telling Alexa to turn on the ...", "Text": "Very cool! I love telling Alexa to turn on the lights!! I have two echos, so I can freak out my friends from the other room!! Tell everyone your house is haunted!"}
