{"Author": "D. T", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The Hue app is not particularly user friendly but all it takes is a few minutes of figuring out before you're good to go", "Text": "Set up was a breeze. The lights are bright and quick to respond to my smarthome controls. I can't wait to get more bulbs and add them in to the system.\n\nThe Hue app is not particularly user friendly but all it takes is a few minutes of figuring out before you're good to go."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love being able to control my lights even away from home"}
{"Author": "Joes girl.", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Another neat product.", "Text": "Do you have a Dot. This is a good thing. I have a iPhone 6 Plus. And I use the Time Capsule for my wifi. {I am a Apple girl 100%}. The reason for me mentioning that is. I used to use some pieces of junk that supposedly was going to give my household great wifi. Yay aha. Reach areas all the way around the block. Hmmm. And I found that anything that needed wifi didn't work. I was blaming the product I bought. Come to find out it was that modem/wifi combo thing. Hmmm. Not just one unit, but 3 different units of modems and wifi boxes. Bla. Anyway. I purchased this to work with my Alexa Dot. For 4 different rooms. So when someone left lights on. Or if I wanted to get up in the middle of the night and wanted lights on before I got there. All I have to do is ask Alexa. And wella. I have lights. Even if someone hits the switch to turn the light on. And leaves it on. I can shut them off. I used my IPhone to sync everything up. I synced it up to Siri first. Then went to my Dot app and finished it up there. Took me about 15 minutes. I used all lamps. The light bulbs are bright enough for my house. And I never lose wifi connection. Ever."}
{"Author": "Jeff", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pricey bulbs. Working fine with Echo.", "Text": "The pairing is easy but not always working. I had to manually pair the bulb with its serial number for one bulb. The app is OK for remotely control. It works with Amazon Echo.The price is still a bit deep for two bulbs and the hub. When more people embrace the smart home idea, the price would go down. Right now, it is just for a few pioneers."}
{"Author": "Johnny Mac", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Glitchy!", "Text": "I bought this as a gift for my daughter. Tried getting it to sync up with her Moto Pure phone. We watched hours of videos. Tried everything under the sun. Tried the same things over and over. Finally it worked. Major pain in the you-know-what.\n\nExpensive for what it is and what it can do."}
{"Author": "Wilyue", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "best light set to work with Echo", "Text": "the set is for the initial set up, this is the best, I don't know why other user having problem with the distant I have two story house, I set this unit upstairs bedroom, i have no problem to have my light setting downstairs bedroom , I was able to control with my Alexa & echo dot upstairs without any issue ! it worked wonderful"}
{"Author": "b robinson", "Date": "on February 5, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Never worked", "Text": "Gave to my son for Christmas and he took it home from the holidays. Did not work so called Philips who sent a new charger. Still will not work. They say to contact Amazon. Bought on Black Friday so now to late to return. Sucks because I just wasted money on a worthless product to collect dust."}
