{"Author": "NitriQ", "Date": "on February 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great starter set!", "Text": "I got this to try it out. Once you get the hue hub you are golden and you can build upon that and add colored bulbs or light strips.\nHue has a lot of great features and I'd recommend watching a few YouTube videos to see if you would like the brightness and the way it works.\nMy favorite add-ons are the light switch and the motion sensor. Both add extra functionality without adding wires or complexity to the system. Bulbs are easily what I'd call 60 watt replacement. Just know these bulbs do NOT change color. They only turn on/off and dim but it's great for movies or if you have the motion sensor setting a night light for anyone walking around that area. Love it!"}
{"Author": "Tracy Verlin", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "work great. I like this as my first add on to try out."}
{"Author": "Gerald McGrew", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Disappointed", "Text": "I bought these to round out a front porch lighting group (two standard bulbs and two GU10 bulbs) I was automating to turn on at sunset and off at sunrise. I previously had TP-Link bulbs in the standard lights but because TP-Link doesn't yet make GU10 bulbs so I switched everything over to Philips Hue system. Having now used both, I really prefer the TP-Link app, system and products. These bulbs are ok, but the Philips Hue ecosystem doesn't have ability to do sunset/sunrise triggers within their own app and you have to go outside to use something like IFTTT which seems bonkers. Seem to be lots of useless light schemes that I'll never use and not basic ones that are more practical."}
