{"Author": "Vorsichtiger Konsument", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "so now i need to buy another device something like Wifi to Ethernet adapter", "Text": "My building is all wifi - no router required - but the bridge requires an ethernet wired network access. I made it work if i USE my hotspot from my phone connect the computer via USB to the Hotspot and use internet sharing via ethernet and connect the Hue to the computer's ethernet. I also share the hot spot over wifi so my tablet can then use the hue app to control the lights. BUT that requires a permanent hot spot service from my cellular plan.\n\nNow tried to share my wifi via ethernet on my computer and this don't work. only the hot-spot.\nso now i need to buy another device something like Wifi to Ethernet adapter.\n\nThe Hue is not well designed with its cables and connection to power and the 3 LED lights. The blue lights are disturbing - i wanted the hue because of ambient illumination for no blue light at night hours.\nIf you compare it with amazon fire stick - nicely designed - lean and small and much more powerful for half the price then the Hue is failure IMHO. sorry very disappointed."}
{"Author": "Mike - WK3T", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very nice!", "Text": "Works as expected. The color lamp is silly but nice."}
{"Author": "Carl K", "Date": "on February 1, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hub Range Limitation?", "Text": "The Philips hub is located upstairs, plugged into the modem. I operates the upstairs lights fine, but the downstairs lights do not work at all. I guess they are too far away. There is no mention of a distance problem in anything I have read -- anywhere. Very disappointing."}
{"Author": "John R.", "Date": "on February 1, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great first smarthub", "Text": "Hub setup and Alexa connectivity can be a bit finicky, but still is a great product. It uses the ZigBee standard and I am not sure if z-wave stuff is actually becoming the majority protocol, which could hurt this in the long run."}
