{"Author": "Vance Hanson", "Date": "on January 28, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Cool, but unreliable (with updates)", "Text": "The concept is cool and allows for more functionality than having lights on a switch. However, if you plan on integrating the system with Apple's Homekit or Amazon's Alexa there will be frustrations. If you plan on only using the Phillips Hue app, you will be less frustrated, but seeing as they advertise compatibility with Alexa and Homekit, it is relevant that Hue does not always work with them. Most of the time, there are at least 2 of the 4 bulbs I have that are showing unresponsive. I can rule out an issue with Alexa and Homekit because they both experience the issues, leaving only the Hue system to blame. There is some great value in the Hue system, but only at the beta level. I will endure the issues, and update the review if the problems are remedied.\n\nUPDATE - It is indeed the Hue system at fault. The 4 different bulbs cycle between \"reachable\" and \"unreachable\". I know it is not a distance issue, as one of the bulbs effected is in the same room as the bridge, only 8 feet from the bridge. Sometimes the lights will still function while in the \"unreachable\" state, but also sometimes they won't function regardless of the state. This needs to be resolved ASAP Phillips, it is unacceptable.\n\nUPDATE - So for the past 24 hours the system has been working flawlessly alone and with Alexa and HomeKit. I do not know why, the only thing I've done since my last update is pick it up to read some info on the sticker of the bridge. Maybe the 1 or 2 inches I moved it after putting it back down has effected it somehow. I will give the item a 4 until it proves to be no further issue, or until the issues resume."}
{"Author": "Southern Boy", "Date": "on January 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "plug it into your router and let is make happy with updates", "Text": "Well, on my way to automating my house, Star Trek wise, right? Buying this and the additional bulbs is cheaper than buying \"no bridge required bulbs at $33.00 apiece. Just unbox it, plug in the power cord, plug it into your router and let is make happy with updates. All the lights on the bridge will come on and then open your app you must install on your phone or use Alexa SmartHome app and go! I did have a problem (self inflicted) when i bought additional bulbs. I tried to sync them to a light on the same circuit. It would not sync them until I read the directions which said sync them on a different circuit in another room. I did that and it recognized them right away. I renamed them and took them to the same circuit I originally had problems with. Setup proceeded without further problems. Amazon, still waiting for the wakeword \"Computer\". :-)"}
{"Author": "James", "Date": "on January 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Id buy again, 2 thumbs up", "Text": "no complaints works as intended no issues.... i dont use light switches anymore they are beneath me"}
