{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Review/Troubleshooting Tip for flickering lights", "Text": "The installation and setup process for the Phillips Hue Starter kit was surprisingly simple. If my 8-year-old nephew attempted to set this system up, I bet he could! The Phillips Hue app that is necessary to make this system work has surprisingly limited functionality but you can download third party apps such as Hue Disco, Onswitch, Huey, etc. for more special lighting scenes and/or the ability to sync your lights with music or movies. I did encounter a problem with one light bulb coming on repeatedly after being turned off. My immediate response was to search Google to find out what other people did to fix this issue. This led me on a journey of changing the bridges IP address, removing all third party apps, rebooting the bridge and router, and failed attempts to login to my router (forgot what I changed default username/password to). After doing all of this and having the light bulb still flicker on and off randomly, I moved the problem bulb into another area of the house. Voila! Problem solved. It turns out that the cause of the problem was due to a bad outlet connection; the extension cable my lamp was plugged into was loose in the wall socket! Be sure to check the wall socket first to see if the connection is loose if you are experiencing a similar issue."}
