{"Author": "AC2MO", "Date": "on January 22, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love tech, but I have to say this Hue ...", "Text": "I love tech, but I have to say this Hue kit has been a little disappointing. I loved using my Echo Dot to control the lights in my office. I have a few issues with them though. First, somehow the \"sync\" between the Hue bridge and Alexa was lost, so I guess I'm going to have to reconfigure Alexa to use them again. Second, the Hue app leaves a LOT to be desired. If there's an update for your device (bridge, bulb, anything), you can't use the app until updating everything. so going to turn your lights off and go to bed, you have to sit and wait 5 minutes while the update finishes. Another quirk is the widget. I tried putting the widget on my home screen after the Alexa sync was lost and that was an even worse experience. Sometimes it appears to be sending the control, but nothing actually happens. Other times, the widget shows the opposite state of the bulbs (shows on when off and off when on). Maybe the next generation is better, but with the same app, I won't bother upgrading until I've seen a much improved workflow."}
