{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hackable Goodness", "Text": "I have had hours of fun hacking Hue. Philips was nice/smart enough to be open about how to hack it for those of us that are into that sort of thing. Basically, you just send JSON data to the hub's RESTFUL interface to turn lights on and set various parameters. My only mild gripe is that so far I haven't found a way to get it to run scripts on the bridge itself--everything has to be sent from another computer.\n\nOf course they provide normal software for those who don't want program. It gets along well with Amazon Echo and Dot."}
