{"Author": "K. Smith", "Date": "on January 19, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice, but kind of overpriced.", "Text": "So much fun to turn the lights off with Alexa. You can also dim the lights and dim some more. I can set a timer for the light and also control it from my phone from anywhere with Wifi or data. So cool! I was 20 min away a couple weeks ago and showed a coworker how I can turn my lights on from work. My neighbor texted me a short time later asking if i was home yet because she saw my lights on. I said, no, I turned them on from work. Not sure it's worth the $70, when you can just get an outlet for $30 on sale and control the same light. It just wont dim that way though. No biggie."}
