{"Author": "Mr M", "Date": "on January 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It's a great help, and a nifty conversation starter.", "Text": "It's a little more time consuming to set up than I thought it would be, but well worth it. The control unit has a set-up button that will need pressed every time you add a controlled-device or control-device, so put it in a location that's easily accessible. The phone/tablet applications are easy to use. I'm a single guy who works weird shifts, and it's great for turning lights on when I'm not home.\n\nIf you're going to use Amazon's Alexa with it, you will need to address each light by it's name: \"Alexa, Hue white lamp 2 on, please.\" I have found that saying \"please\" at the end of a command helps as well. \"Alexa, Hue white lamp 2, 25% please\" works better than \"Alexa, Hue white lamp 2 25%\". Once you are familiar with how to navigate through the application, there are two places to re-name the rooms and lights, you'll need to do that if you want to just simply say \"Alexa, Living Room on.\""}
{"Author": "S Anderson", "Date": "on January 17, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good for lights that you just want \"on\" and \"off\"", "Text": "Pros: easy set-up, works perfectly with echo dot and iPhone app, easily set timers and scenes, good price for initial Philips hue set-up kit.\n\nCons: limited number of scenes because it's not hue ambiance (only \"bright\", \"dimmed\" and \"night-light\"), flickers when dimmed manually to any settings other than preset scenes.\n\nI bought these for my kitchen island so I could turn lights on when I arrive home and when I wake-up in the morning. They work fine for that purpose. I was able to install the hue hub, lights and app on my network in less than an hour. Took a little fooling around to figure out the iPhone app (light settings and scenes aren't intuitive) but I have since set up a widget on my iPhone that allows me to turn lights on and off with a single button. The remote app works well too.\n\nI only gave 3 stars because my main complaint is that they flicker when dimmed. That may be due to the fact that the bulbs are installed in a fixture that also has a dimmer switch. But regardless of cause, they flicker except when set to the preset \"dimmed\" scene in the app. Down the road I will probably replace these bulbs with Hue ambiance bulbs (when the price comes down a little) & switch these bulbs to non-dimming light fixtures. But all in all, they do the job of turning the lights on and off with a timer and remotely."}
