{"Author": "scott", "Date": "on January 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great", "Text": "Set up easily with alexa. Working great so far. Haven't installed the Philips Hue app on my phone, only the amazon alexa app. They have seemingly random names though, one is bedroom 1 and the other is yoga lamp 1. I can't rename the individual bulbs through the alexa app, The Philips hue app had trouble finding them, but I assume if I got that working I would be able to rename them there. It doesn't matter to me though because I set a group in alexa for both of them with my preferred name (I use them both in a ceiling light)."}
{"Author": "Chris M", "Date": "on January 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy setup, works as advertised", "Text": "Easy setup, works as advertised. I've owned three of this lights and hub for several months now. Apart from a couple of times that I'd blame my wifi connection, I've never had the lights disconnect from the network. The bulbs are sufficiently bright at 100%. Works seamlessly with both my Google Home and Amazon Echo. I love being able to dim the lights with my voice. I also have timers set so that the lights come on at a low level just as I'm waking up and switch off as I'm leaving the house for work. I'd recommend to anyone with home wifi looking for basic smart home lighting, particularly if you have one of the aforementioned voice assistants. The phone app also works just fine for controlling the lights. I have noticed a couple of times there is a slight delay between opening the app and actually being able to control the lights. It can sometimes take just a moment or two for the app to connect to the lights."}
{"Author": "Hilde", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it!", "Text": "Just awesome! Shop around though.... you can get better pricing elsewhere on the Philips lights. Also, be careful not to purchase the Philips A19 bulbs thinking they are Hue compatible... If it is not \"Hue\" it is not going to work with the Hue bridge."}
{"Author": "jdub", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great concept - questionable reliabiltiy", "Text": "The concept is great but the reliability seems to be poor. I set these up and created routines to turn them on at night and off in the morning. Pretty simple. The problem is that they only follow the routine about 50% of the time. Why it fails is a mystery to me. When I check my smart phone the routines are off even though I never turned them off. I can turn the lights on and off by voice with Siri but the real value is in being able to set a schedule and forget about it - even if you are away. I am not certain these are dependable for that. The bulbs are nice and bright."}
{"Author": "****", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works sometimes", "Text": "Very buggy, works intermittently. My Wink stuff is on the same Wifi network with Alexa and works flawlessly"}
{"Author": "Cookieman", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product.", "Text": "Love this product. We put one bulb downstairs and one in bedroom upstairs. We are able to set timers with our iPhone app to have the lights come on and go off at variable times to make it look as if we are home when we are gone."}
{"Author": "Pistol Pete", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Works well with amazon alexa."}
{"Author": "Mikey", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome deal for a starter pack.", "Text": "Great price as a starter kit - Absolutely love these lights. Love that I can control via the smartphone app, as well as with my Echo dot. Especially love creating scenes for different times/activities, and auto programming the lights (e.g. I have my bedroom lights come on gradually from 0%-100% in the morning right before my alarm goes off to simulate a sunrise) Highly recommended!"}
{"Author": "Toni and Mark Z", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "gives me pleasure seeing him enjoy this so much", "Text": "christmas present for my husband. it is the 1st gift I have bought him that was a hit. as much so that he is filling the house with, \"alexa, turn on...\" all over the house. gives me pleasure seeing him enjoy this so much. and the 3 year old great grand son comes over and asks alexa to play his songs, and wants his own for his house. his parents say no. afraid they would be living with constant lights strobing."}
{"Author": "Anand Poovekurussi", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love it"}
{"Author": "Mike", "Date": "on January 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My 78 y/o dad loves telling alexa to turn on/off the lights", "Text": "Love the hue system. Purchased this for my parents and they are having a blast controlling the hue bulbs using Alexa on an echo and dot. Installation is quite simple but it does require an ethernet cable (not WiFi) and should be placed in a central location. If the hub cannot connect to a remote bulb buy an additional bulb $14, as each bulb is a repeater for the Zigbee Light Link network used by Hue. I have used the v1 hub with the GE smart bulbs, but I am pretty sure Hue will not work with the osram bulbs, if you are looking for alternate bulbs. To connect your Hue to Alexa you need to add the Hue Skill and connect the hub to the my.meethue.com web site and configure each of your bulbs and rooms. To add some more features connect the Hue to IFTTT.com and you can turn on/off lights when arriving home or leaving, turn on lights when the sun sets through simple recipe's. IFTTT (if this then that) is a great service with hundreds of connected services you can control your lights and other home automation systems using."}
{"Author": "L. Romme", "Date": "on January 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amazing Product and Low Price", "Text": "These are the best out there for the price. Add on bulbs are decently priced too! Love the dimmer options and using the lights as an alarm clock to wake up slowly is perfect for those of us who suffer from being glued to bed in the mornings."}
{"Author": "JKlimeck", "Date": "on January 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This start kit makes it easy and convenient to make your home into a smart home.", "Text": "The Hue setup is very easy to setup to any home network. I had the main hub and two light all setup in under 10 minutes. add more bulbs in under 5. This start kit makes it easy and convenient to make your home into a smart home."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Super easy set up", "Text": "Super easy set up! Just note that the hub needs to be connected to your router. I was not prepared for it to be located there but found a way to make it work. Love being able to turn lights on/off while out of the house! Highly recommended!!"}
