{"Author": "JD in Rochester", "Date": "on January 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hue + Alexa = Easy installation and flawless operation!", "Text": "I had read some of the mixed reviews on these and decided to give it a try anyway. I am so glad I did. This kit installed quickly and easily on my . home network just by following the instructions on line (no detailed instructions in the box.) Some reviews claimed that the bulbs needed to be in close proximity to the hub - or that it needed to be on the same floor - I found this to be untru as I have placed the bulbs at opposite ends of a large house with the hub in the basement - all work perfectly. I believe it has more to do with your home network's wifi coverage that it does with placement of this hardware. I'm using Alexa to control this system and by just following the advice and instructions given, no problems. As a bonus, the hub and ap also recognized the electronic (wifi) thermostat I've had in my home for three years but had never before controlled remotely.\n\nI love this thing!"}
