{"Author": "Lulu", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "its great if you are lucky.", "Text": "purchased the kit when it was on sale in July this year. it has been about half year. our house is close to the rail track so when the light bulb sometimes turns itself on, I blamed it wifi being interrupted and it causes the bulb to \"misbehave\". until one day it just stopped working altogether. there were two bulbs in the kit so I switched to the other bulb and it has been 3 months now without a glitch. I gave it three stars because overall it does what it says it does WHEN you have a good bulb. I would like one day to have more of these at home, BUT with the price for these bulbs....I am worried how lucky I will get for proper working bulbs in the future.\n\np.s. I googled a lot when the 1st bulb was turning itself on... a lot of people said it has to do with your internet connections...which I 100% believed at the time. Now I think it is really just these people got unlucky like me and got a bad bulb.\n\nUpdate after a year. So the first bulb didn't work properly, but the second one did.......BUT it stoped working just few days ago. So yeah....GREAT QUALITY PRODUCTS!"}
{"Author": "Read &amp; tweet", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not convenient to use. Wish we can use Alexa ...", "Text": "Not convenient to use. Wish we can use Alexa instead of the iPhone for the command. The bulbs are not bright enough for most fixtures. For the price, not worth it."}
{"Author": "tanstaafl", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works well with Amazon Alexa/Echo or without.", "Text": "I thought these were a bit gimicky and I wouldn't use them very much, but they are awesome. The dimming capability alone is wonderful, and it's nice to be able to set all the lights up to turn off at night and other scenarios. Very easy to set up. You can connect many more bulbs to this one hub."}
{"Author": "John A. Coverstone", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Be prepared to return it - Best to avoid this kit", "Text": "This seems like a nice kit to get you started with smart home devices. However, the hub will only work with the light bulbs included. In my case, the reseller had probably replaced the light bulbs (likely after a customer return) and the kit did not work at all. I was never able to get the light bulbs paired and working with the Wink app.\n\nAfter extensively researching this system online, my experience appears to be a fairly frequent problem. I called Wink and a very helpful individual talked through the entire issue with me to the point where I was certain I would not be able to get it working with this hub. I ended up throwing away the Link hub from this kit and purchasing a Wink hub, which immediately resolved my issues. The support person informed me that the manufacturer of this hub went out of business and has been replaced with a different company who does not support this product. With the Wink Hub 2 Wink Hub 2 now released, the original Wink Hub Wink Connected Home Hub is very affordable. I would highly recommend purchasing that hub with the light bulbs separately. It won't cost much more and you are pretty much guaranteed compatibility, including for future expansion. I would stay away from this kit."}
{"Author": "Nicola Mullen", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I bought this for the hubby for Christmas. He ...", "Text": "I bought this for the hubby for Christmas. He put the light bulbs in and downloaded the app Christmas day and started to \"play\". The bulbs are bright, I texted him to turn down the light while he wasn't home and it worked so he turned them up and then down and then up!! He plans on getting more bulbs for the rest of the house"}
{"Author": "Dee Pfryde", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If you like the old fashioned pre 1990s look that might not ...", "Text": "Be warned, despite being sold as \"white lights\" these are very yellowy. If you like the old fashioned pre 1990s look that might not be a con for you, I was hoping for white lights though.\n\nThe bulbs also arn't very bright and don't dim very much.\n\nThey do pair well with Alexa although you have to name them differently in Alexa app and Hue app for them to work properly.\n\nOverall a very cool concept, just a shame the bulbs are so dim and yellow."}
{"Author": "Linda E.", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "They were easy to set up with the Philips app on my ...", "Text": "We purchased these to use with Amazon's Alexa and also to use with the Philips Hue app so that we can turn the lights on even when we are not home. They were easy to set up with the Philips app on my iPhone. We set the lights up with Alexa and that was easy too, It takes a little practice with Alexa to ask the correct way to get the lights on, off, and to dim and brighten by percentages. I don't think you can set scenes with Alexa, but with the Philips app this can be done easily. We also purchased one of the Philips Hue color bulbs and the colors are very pretty. The colors must be changed with the Philips Hue app."}
