{"Author": "Kalinedrive", "Date": "on December 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy smart home starter kit!", "Text": "My wife and I love it! It took maybe 3 minutes to get Alexa to communicate with Hue. I have 4 lamps in 3 different rooms and it works flawlessly. You don't have to be technically savvy to set this up.\n\nSpecifically, here is what is very cool for us:\n\n1. You can dim or brighten a light by saying, \"Alexa, dim living room lights 50%.\"\n2. You can group lights by room. Even with it grouped per room, I can still control individual lights in that room (with voice using Alexa) because I gave each lamp it's own name.\n3. I can control my lights from anywhere in the world as long as I am connected to the internet using my Hue account.\n\nWe are hooked on the smart home devices. Next up, thermostat control."}
{"Author": "Molly", "Date": "on December 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love the Phillips White A19 Starter Kit with bulbs", "Text": "This is really amazing! I can set the lighting up on a timer as well as turning lights off and on with my Echo! I am planning to pick up some additional lights for different areas of the house as well. I also purchased the TP-Link Smart plug and have my Christmas tree plugged into it so I can turn off and on with my Echo without having to grope behind the tree to plug and unplug the lights."}
