{"Author": "Dr Gregory Butler HVAC", "Date": "on December 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart home = $$$ savings", "Text": "Works great even from my bedroom...my Alexa Echo and Dot bot control lights...labeled bedroom and living room lights...either request is met with almost immediate response...the Philips Hue White works very good with Echo and the light bulbs are what seems to be 60w brightness...gave them for Christmas gifts too...my whole family is slowly leaning towards smart home technology...we're all considering dropping cable tv and going strictly to streaming internet media..."}
{"Author": "Rob Grant", "Date": "on December 21, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... new \"Smart Home\" thing that is catching on is pretty sweet! These bulbs and bridge work great", "Text": "This new \"Smart Home\" thing that is catching on is pretty sweet! These bulbs and bridge work great. Took minuets to setup and be working through my phone app. I have noticed occasionally while playing with the dimmer, that they sometimes flicker just a bit. But nothing too serious to worry about. I recently added the Amazon Echo, and can now control the lights by voice. Perfect for the person who is too lazy to move to mess with the lights!"}
{"Author": "Rich", "Date": "on December 20, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Light work great with my Alexa and my iPhone app!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 20, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easily worth it!", "Text": "The lights work great! Flawlessly integrate with both Amazon Dot, Apple HomeKit and with Google Home. Being able to control the lights with your voice is a breeze. More importantly, it is extremely handy to be able to set up automated tasks to turn your lights on in the evening or turn them on if you'll be away for the night. Highly recommend!"}
{"Author": "S Hazelwood", "Date": "on December 20, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love Hue lights!", "Text": "I use this with my Amazon Echo in addition to with the Hue app. Since I work hours that sometimes has me home after dark, I used the free Hue app to have the lights come on automatically come on at around sunset.\n\nI also have them come on at the same time in the morning so I'm forced to wake up. Waking up when it's still dark outside is not easy for me and this has helped a lot. Using it with the Echo, I just say \"Alexa, turn the living room light on\" and the lights come on. You can also tell Alexa to turn them on to 10% and it comes on just enough to walk through the house at night.\n\nMy favorite part though is that my lights come on at a certain time without having to do anything at all. When I'm away on trips, I don't worry so much about would-be robbers noticing that my house stays dark and assuming I'm not home. Every little bit of peace is helpful when I'm away for days at a time.\n\nPlus they are LED lights so they're much better on energy consumption. I'm not sure where there is a con to these lights."}
