{"Author": "SF Amazon Fan", "Date": "on December 20, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does NOT work consistently with Alexa....", "Text": "Lights are cool but I bought primarily to use them with Alexa. Alexa cannot consistently 'find' the Hue lights so it works maybe 25% of the time. I reset the device and chatted with customer service and unfortunately it seems this is an accepted product deficiency. Overall don't wait your $$."}
{"Author": "steve", "Date": "on December 20, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty cool idea", "Text": "Pretty cool idea. I like that they have an auto timed dim feature so you start to know when it is time to go to bed; the lights begin to dim.\nI have had issues with the mobile app which is not very good but the physical product is good so far. Not sure why the base station has to be wired\nvs wireless but that is the case so it needs to be in close proximity to the router as well as take up one of your router ports."}
