{"Author": "bruce rademacher", "Date": "on December 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "love it"}
{"Author": "sarah_dan10", "Date": "on December 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "We love the Hue Lights", "Text": "We love the Hue Lights, They are great lights, slightly overpriced if you considered for replacements. But we love that they hook up to our Alexa. We bought another set for a gift."}
{"Author": "Chuck from Dallas", "Date": "on December 13, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Really Great Automation with Amazon Echo", "Text": "Love my Philips Hue lights. They work well with my Amazon Echo Dot. So cool to dim or turn lights on and off by voice. The best part is that one hub operates lights all over the house. One complaint is the Hue lights are just NOT bright enough. They really need 100 watt equivalent lights. I personally don't need lights that change color and the dimmable white lights are only $15 each - about the same as a regular LED bulb."}
{"Author": "Michael C. Alicea", "Date": "on December 13, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Decided to try these and am very happy with how they work."}
{"Author": "jose", "Date": "on December 13, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "The best thing i ever had"}
{"Author": "EvanMO", "Date": "on December 13, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Product!", "Text": "Works great with Alexa! Now to get more light bulbs. Also keep in mind you don't need this directly connected to your router. If you wall jacks in you house or apartment are activated that will work too. The only thing I'm trying to figure out in the Hue App is the location. It keeps turning off in the app. I have a Samsung Note5."}
{"Author": "Kimpropriety", "Date": "on December 12, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice Product, Frustrating App", "Text": "Edited Review: My husband convinced me to try these again, but this time we hooked it up to Apple Homekit and don't use the Hue app at all. When I do try to use the Hue app, I still have connection issues about 50% of the time. (I don't see how that's not relevant when you literally cannot control these lights without using some kind of app. :P) But when using Siri or the little home button in the iOS 11 dashboard, I have yet to have any trouble.\n\nOld Review: If you want to lose all light functionality from a product promising to add functionality, then Phillips Hue is for you! I have never once opened the Hue app and had a connection already established to the Hue bridge, so a wait for it to connect is always mandatory, but in fact the vast majority of the time the connection attempt fails and I have to close the app and reopen it - repeat as necessary for the thing to finally work -- EVERY TIME you want to use the light/s in question. Why can't a background enabled app just stay connected?? I thought the ability to dim any light in your house was a lovely concept, but it is not an on demand deal. It happens after five minutes of fiddling with the Hue app or bridge, if it works at all, and I for one don't have time for it. They are getting uninstalled."}
{"Author": "jakeh53cc", "Date": "on December 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great!", "Text": "Works great!"}
{"Author": "Alex Hilt", "Date": "on December 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Working great after some initial hickups", "Text": "Has worked pretty well up to this point. There were a few issues at first, and Alexa was not able to find the hub or lights shortly after resetting everything, but that appears to have been remedied by moving the Hue bridge to the router instead of on a Wifi bridge. The Hue website always seemed to work for controlling the lights even when the Echo was struggling.\nEach light shows up as an individual unit, you can then group the lights so that fixtures with multiple bulbs can be controlled with a single command.\nSet-up is pretty easy. Generally does not require a \"technical\" background.\nPossibilities are pretty much limitless with set up and control."}
{"Author": "Dan Leveille", "Date": "on December 11, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The best lighting automation product on the market", "Text": "I've tried a number of home automation products, and the Phillips Hue is by far the best I've tried. I've replaced most of my lightbulbs with Phillips Hues and now I can control almost all of my apartment's lighting just by asking Siri.\n\nPROS:\n- So easy to set up.\n- Great price for buying bulbs individually\n- Your existing lighting switches will work just as normal -- when you swap out a bulb with a Phillips Hue, your light switches will work just as normal.\n- Works great with Siri and Apple Homekit.\n- You can use Siri to configure your lighting. \"Siri, I'm home.\" \"Siri, dim the bedroom lights.\" \"Siri, let's watch a movie.\"\n- Scenes can be scheduled so that they turn on/off at certain times, or even when you arrive or leave.\n- Sufficient brightness.\n\nCONS:\n- Not a huge deal, but it'd be great if the bulbs could dim a bit more. The dimmest level is still a little bright for my tastes. Probably not a big deal in larger apartments and homes.\n- Buying additional colored bulbs are pricey.\n- (Rarely) will sometimes not respond. Usually this corrects itself very quickly, but there will be times where Siri will briefly not be able to connect your lights."}
{"Author": "Arthur Putman", "Date": "on December 11, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy setup."}
{"Author": "Hunter", "Date": "on December 11, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Doesn't work well", "Text": "I deal with a lot of smart home products and decided to try these. I was really disappointed in integrating this into my smart home test system at my house. I test products athat my house prior to ever trying to install these products at my customers houses.\n\nThis units failed fairly quickly.\n\nIntegration into typical smart home or even alexa control did not go to well. I was having a lot of issue with alexa even turning on the lights. After I failed with that I tried the integration intuitive other systems that we install and I found their responsiveness sporadic at best. I would suggest staying with hard wired control devices instead of bulb controlled devices. Very disappointed.."}
{"Author": "Adrian", "Date": "on December 11, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I like the product and works well from phone app", "Text": "I like the product and works well from phone app. Only reason not 5 star is the app could be improved. Like many I suspect I just want to have a light on when I come home and timer function is"}
{"Author": "Alpinestarninja", "Date": "on December 11, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great! Device must stay at home", "Text": "Initial setup was easy but when I tried to change it to an apple TV it became hard. There Apple device MUST stay at homes for remote control....."}
{"Author": "pwj44", "Date": "on December 11, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... uo with Alexa and dot and this is very cool..", "Text": "hook it uo with Alexa and dot and this is very cool...."}
{"Author": "Brian K.", "Date": "on December 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "LOVE THIS! 5 Stars all day long", "Text": "I have been wanting more \"Smart Home\" Products & Philips Hue just made a huge difference. HomeKit compatible for the iPhone / iPad & with an Apple TV, you can even control the lights when you aren't at home. Setup is rather simple. Connect to your network (through a router or switch) download the Hue App & follow the steps. Incredible. Able to create Scenes & even control with my Apple Watch using Siri! I already have about 8 bulbs & will definitely be getting more in the future! LOVE THIS! 5 Stars all day long!"}
{"Author": "Barbara Jane Price", "Date": "on December 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very nice, wish they were cheaper. I would have more than 2 if they were"}
{"Author": "Allan P. Johnson III", "Date": "on December 10, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Too complicated to set up. I returned it."}
{"Author": "County Girl", "Date": "on December 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love it", "Text": "I love not having to get up at the last moment to turn off the light switch once you get all tucked in!\ud83d\ude43"}
{"Author": "Greylin", "Date": "on December 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love the convenience!", "Text": "Works well with my echo dot. Love the convenien9ce of turning on a light before I head into a dark room. No fumbling for switches in the dark. Give your lights simple names. I made the mistake of naming my nightstand light \"Robin\" and had to listen to everyone in the house say, \"Turn Robin on! Turn Robin off!\" My spouse quipped, \"We'll my life just got a whole lot easier.\" There were a couple times that the Hue app updated so there was delay with Alexa reaction for a few minutes. The bulbs are very expensive but I think having just 1 in each room or area will work for us, reducing costs."}
{"Author": "Sara Dancer", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great!", "Text": "Godsend for child with Autism so he can turn off his lights from his bed. What I didn't understand at first is that the hub doesn't communicate with the wifi router via wifi. Major frustration setting this up because it says to connect it to the wifi but not HOW. Needs clearer instructions about that."}
{"Author": "BlueRidgeAl", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Automated Lighting with Alexa", "Text": "works very well with Alexa! Easy to install and use."}
{"Author": "Bryan", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Work great but would recommend the adjustable bulbs.", "Text": "My first try at the smart home game and I found set up to be quick and intuitive. The product is great as it is, but the color temperature is very warm, limiting where I could use the bulbs. I ended up installing these in by bedroom and ordering the temperature-adjustable \"Ambiance\" bulbs to match the lighting in my common areas."}
{"Author": "Bill hammer", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Never walk into a dark room again. Great product", "Text": "Works great with Alexa. Lights come on after dusk by setting or by your gps location. Then when you leave they turn themselves off"}
{"Author": "MajinMike", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy set up, works flawlessly... Paired with my echo dot makes controlling the lights simple."}
{"Author": "Bruce Luxon", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great. Surprised it needs a hard connection to a ...", "Text": "Works great. Surprised it needs a hard connection to a router rather than just use wifi which would be much more convenient."}
{"Author": "SimplyT", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good, but not amazing (yet).", "Text": "Good, but not amazing (yet).\n\nSome of the features are useful.\nSome are purely gimmicky/novelty.\nSome are lacking...but the great thing is that Amazon will continue to update abilities/skills.\n\nIt would be nice if it were a little more intuitive."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works as Advertised!!!"}
{"Author": "J Higgins", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Definately Worth It!!", "Text": "This has been an awesome product! One of the best of its kind. I have been able to turn the lights on and off while away through the Hue App. I have been able to connect it to my Amazon Echo Dot (Alexa) which works great too. When my hands are full all I have to do is have Echo (Alexa) turn the lights on / off for me."}
{"Author": "A. Junco", "Date": "on December 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "How useful is this thing really??", "Text": "This is an interesting idea. But how practical is it really? It is useful to be able to turn lights on and off remotely through the internet, but you never know if it is working and after some testing, it's about 60\u2105 accurate. Had someone at home while I was at work and as I played with the internet connect light, I got about a 60\u2105 accuracy on the ons and offs. That is disappointing as the app said all was fine, so you might not get an on when you ask or you might leave the lights on when you think they are off. So it's useful, just not completely reliable."}
{"Author": "D. Powell", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Phillips Hue Starter Kit", "Text": "What can I say? It is fantabulosa!!!! I can't say enough good things about this product! I got more bulbs and planning to get even more. I use it with Amazon (Alexa) and it is absolutely the greatest!!!!! What a wonderful product!!!!!"}
{"Author": "Honest Abe", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These are great", "Text": "The new bridge is better-more responsive. Did 19 color hue bulbs for halloween animated to mimic red and yellow flickering flames in the windows of my house. An elderly neighbor was going to call 911----REALLY"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So awesome I ordered more.", "Text": "I was a bit worried that the color of lights would be more soft then warm, but I think it is fairly in between. It's great for me. So, I purchased more. Set up is a breeze. Put the bulbs in, plug the bridge and download the app."}
{"Author": "Ilker A.", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "no color control through Amazon Alexa", "Text": "nice update to my existing Hue system.\nBut I was expecting to control colors through Amazon Alexa.\nThat feature is Still not available."}
{"Author": "crystal", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fast, Easy but light has yellow tinge", "Text": "Love Love Love the convenience of setting this up. Bought 16 bulbs and took me about an hour to screw them in get them loaded to Hue and then to Alexa. What I love is the ability to set the % of light. So you want dim lights, set at 5%. What I don't like about this is lightbulbs have yellow tinge and not the clear white that I like. If they could clear that up I would give a 5 star. Being able to turn on and off lights from your phone or Alexa device is PRICELESS!"}
{"Author": "Big Pa", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Simple to setup", "Text": "Works well"}
{"Author": "LauraLee", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hands-free lighting at its best", "Text": "Having hands-free control of my house lights is an amazing experience. I plugged in the hub to the outlet, plugged it into the modem, told Alexa to find wireless devices, and voila! I use a light bulb in the living room and one in the bedroom. It's convenient to tell Alexa to turn the lights on and off when I'm not near them. It took about 15 minutes to set up because I had to get the app on my phone and had some trouble making an account for some reason. The bulbs are just as bright as my regular ones so there's no difference in anything other than being hands free! I'm getting more light bulbs for more lamps and soon the entire house will be under my voice command."}
{"Author": "Gary Reid", "Date": "on December 8, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Convenient but the apps. need more polishing.", "Text": "I do like it. It adds a nice convenient feature to my home. Although adding lights can be a bit of a challenge at times. The other issue I have\nis that there is no app. for my Windows 10 computer. You have to go the the My Hue web page where all you have is basic on and off control. The Android app. is better but not great. Also makes a nice addition to the Amazon Alexa."}
{"Author": "John Thompson", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not as implied", "Text": "This an update to my previous review below. Phillips sent me a link to get a java app that works on IBM and Mac computers and to find the bulbs. Note the app requires that the bulbs be turned on and with in 30cm of the bridge so you will probably need a small portable light fixture and possibly an extension cord. It works and you have to go through meethue and rename the devices. [...] It would be nice if Phillips would include this and other information in printed form with the bulbs instead relying totally on their app. Also I have not been able to use Alexa to access the Color temperature on my Ambiance bulbs.\n\nThe started kit will work with Alexa, the meethue web site by Philips, and the All 4 HUE app in the amazon app store. However the setup is not that nice no written instructions other than to go to the meethue website and download the Philips hue app for your phone. The Philips hue in the amazon app store does not work on a fire phone (not compatible with fire Os). I recommend that you check the web site and the phone app before ordering. Most of this information has been extracted from a conversation with Phillips support over the phone\n\nAnother important thing the bridge must be hardwired to an ethernet port on your router it will not wifi connect to the router. Also The Bridge and the bulbs come pre linked. The Phone app is the only way to link extra bulbs to the bridge. the web site will not link extra bulbs but it will allow you to rename the bulbs and setup groups and even turn them on and off the names can be used with Alexa. Once the bridge is connected the ring light and the 3 other indicator lights should be on.\n\nLinking to Alexa is relatively easy, ask Alexa to discover devices and push the button on the bridge. But all extra bulbs must be discovered by the phone app and listed on the website for Alexa to use them. at the moment there is no way to use these and expand the system with out the phone apps. I ordered 3 extra ambiance lights and I have not been able to connect to the bridge."}
{"Author": "Joshua", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love Phillips Hue lighting", "Text": "I love Phillips Hue lighting, I have about 6 bulbs, and 8 light strips. I have connected them all to amazon alexa and it is amazing! the ease of control and customization makes live easier and more efficient. I highly recommend this starter kit."}
{"Author": "jason", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great!!!!!"}
{"Author": "Ryall", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dim some", "Text": "It's good. Fun to use and show off to guests. Sometimes it's just faster to hit the physical light switch. Easy set up. It dims some (lol)."}
{"Author": "Clay D.", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great. I have linked Alexa with my Phillips HUE ...", "Text": "Works great. I have linked Alexa with my Phillips HUE and she handles all my lighting. Very cool. Set up was a snap."}
{"Author": "Bruce Darling", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great.", "Text": "An inexpensive entry level system . Works great ."}
{"Author": "Bob Wallace", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great way to get started if you are only going ...", "Text": "Great way to get started if you are only going to use white bulbs. The setup on this is quick and easy. If you have plans on using color bulbs then get the color starter kit. It's a bit more expensive but you'll save money versus buying the color bulbs later at full price."}
{"Author": "Yandry Tacoronte", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I don't Have to Wake up Anymore :)", "Text": "Amazing lights!!! I was really excited with the lights when I did my review about them. I bought with the same the Echo Dot which via voice command you can turn on and off the lights. When I got this lights my wife was really mad, saying that was a waste of money, that's ridiculous, can you return this light... 10 days after, baby can you buy two more lights? Now she use them more than me. In conclusion, if you really have the money and you're tired of waking at midnight because you have to turn off the lights, those bulbs are going to solve your problem."}
{"Author": "S. Gladwin", "Date": "on December 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent", "Text": "Works well and integrated with my Amazon Dot perfectly."}
{"Author": "SC", "Date": "on December 6, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It's great not having to search for the light switch in ...", "Text": "Package received as promised. We were able to hook it up with no problem. Not complicated at all.\nIt's great not having to search for the light switch in the dark...it's even nicer having \"Alexa\" turn it on for you."}
{"Author": "R", "Date": "on December 6, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it so far", "Text": "so far (1 week) it works well. I have turned on lights when I was out longer then expected so when I returned it was not to a dark homes where I could not see (I have a old home switches are in odd locations). I like turning lights on for the dogs as well if I am not home. I had no issue setting it up at all. Some of the bulbs ( I purchased more) are very far from the base ( I have a 3 level home) and all work as they should. I have been unable to connect it to my Echo but its the Echo not this that is the issue."}
{"Author": "SMB", "Date": "on December 5, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Lights 5-Stars; App 3-Stars", "Text": "There are really two use cases for these lights. The first is that you want to use the colored lights to pair your lighting with your mood. I don't really feel the need to do that. The second is to automate lights to save energy; to make the home look lived in; or to dim otherwise non-dimmable lights (e.g. lamps). I have a lot of use for that.\n\nI have installed the Hue app and I mostly control the lights through the apple integration on the iPhone. Initially, I had a hard time with the lights. They wouldn't reliably go on according to schedule. I couldn't always access them. A week ago my router died. I replaced it and all is well now. So apparently that was my router not Hue. So the lights work as advertised.\n\nThe app is clearly oriented around \"scenes\". That's the first use case, the one for which I have no use. For automation the app pretty much sucks. You can set the lights to go on/off/dim at a given time. If, you want that time to be sunset or dawn, you'll have to adjust that yourself. It might not be a big deal for some people, but it was kind of the point for me. Fortunately, I have Apple TV and an iPhone. I can set a sunset schedule using the phone and the AppleTV will execute it even when I'm away. That's fine, but I think the Hue app should handle that on it's own."}
{"Author": "echam", "Date": "on December 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I have one in my foyer and it's nice to have a light on there", "Text": "I've been playing with these since I got them. I have one in my foyer and it's nice to have a light on there. Another is in a bedroom lamp; the rest of my lights are recessed. The app is easy to use and I like the options to have the lights turn on when I arrive home and turn off at night. I can also have them turned on and off at different times when I am out. I'm looking forward to using more of these features."}
{"Author": "Tdubl", "Date": "on December 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "You'll wonder how you got along without them", "Text": "My best purchase in a while. I love being able to set up routines with these. Wake up and the lights are already on. Come home from work and the lights are on. Leave for work and they turn off. Super helpful having a two story house and being able to turn them off remotely from upstairs (or just have them turn off via a routine every night at a set time). You can also dim them from your phone, and have them fade in or out over a set period of time. Very very cool, and they work without a hitch."}
{"Author": "The Reef Rocket", "Date": "on December 5, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "will not respond correctly ...not ready for prime time", "Text": "very easy hook up then doesn't work all the time. turns off only one in group, then nothing. after power loss still doesn't respond right.\nVery disappointed. will not buy any more. I purchased two TP-link switches which are farther away and they work fine\nLive and Learn"}
{"Author": "Amazon Forever", "Date": "on December 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great Product"}
{"Author": "Kevin Bast", "Date": "on December 5, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very easy to set up", "Text": "Very easy to set up. Integrates well with the Alexa device. We will be expanding the use of smart lighting throughout the house. Very good product. The only reason for the 4 stars rather than 5 is for the App. It's a little clunky and could use some improvement. Just a couple of times we've found the lights to have glitches and become unresponsive. Just turn off and on and they are good to go. I recommend this product."}
{"Author": "Richard S.", "Date": "on December 4, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I have to say that I'm not happy I can't get Alexa to work with the lights ...", "Text": "Ok I purchased this because of all of the extra features compared to the WeMo. I have to say that I'm not happy I can't get Alexa to work with the lights and have to use the Hue application. I spent over 6 hours trying to get this to work and still nothing. If you want everything in one place with Alexa don't buy this until Phillips fixes this issue."}
{"Author": "Pete K", "Date": "on December 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Phillips Hue System is a Win with Amazon Echo Dot", "Text": "We have the Phillips Hue white Light system working seamlessly with the Amazon Echo Dot. It is a hoot!\n\nWe wish the white light bridge would workwith the colored lights. Now that I see how easy and effectively they work, we would like to try out the colored bulbs."}
