{"Author": "Elizabeth Dillon", "Date": "on December 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Yes you will be able to set this up!", "Text": "I am not the most tech savvy person but with a bit of perseverance and refusal to be intimidated...I did it! At first I was concerned because it said Apple Home Kit and I don't have any Apple products. But I paired it with Alexa it was fine. Hook up the bridge to the router with the ethernet cable, it doesn't have its own Wifi. Set up 2 lights in the house, named them on the hue app, paired with my Alexa and it is awesome. Plus it is fun to have the light go on in the other room and confuse the dog!"}
{"Author": "HoustonTexansfan", "Date": "on December 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Starting small in home automation and LOVE THIS STUFF!! So easy to set up!", "Text": "Philips HUE Starter Kit:\n\u2022 Wanted to start small, see how easy or difficult it was to set up, and see how it worked with Echo\n\u2022 LOVE these. Easy to set up (you will need to hook the hub up via LAN cable (included in kit) to your wireless router or a hub/switch (I have my hub in my office since I have a hub in there)\n\u2022 Easy to set up once you download the HUE app (make sure you download the right app)\n\u2022 Communicates with Echo, so you set things up on THIS hub, then Echo picks it all up and you use Echo for the voice control part\n\u2022 Bought 3 more bulbs today\u2026So cool\n\u2022 Also make sure you know whether the bulb is just a white bulb or colored\u2026with Colored, you can set a million colors\u2026I don\u2019t need it but could be cool"}
