{"Author": "Joe Vrablik", "Date": "on November 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent System", "Text": "Excellent system, easy to use. If combining with Alexa, I would recommend creating groups of bulbs within the Smart Home section of the Alexa app. You can have bulbs be members of multiple groups (i.e. a bulb can be a member of the \"Kitchen Chandelier\" group and also a broader \"Kitchen\" group), which I was unable to do (initially, have not gone back to try again) in the native Hue app. Be careful in ordering, as the bulbs I received are the latest generation, whereas an additional set ordered at the same time from Amazon were the previous generation. The differences are noticeable when used in the same fixture. (In store, the previous generation had black packaging, the new one white.)"}
{"Author": "Stuart", "Date": "on November 29, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I like the functionality and convenience of Hue", "Text": "I like the functionality and convenience of Hue. The two drawbacks are that the Hue hub is required though I already have a Smart Things hub and other bulbs function directly with the Smart Things hub, and the price. I hope it will get more reasonably priced when the newness wears off."}
