{"Author": "MATTHEW CORDARO", "Date": "on November 28, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "When coupled with Alexa/Echo this becomes awesome and frustrating at the same time", "Text": "When coupled with Alexa/Echo this becomes awesome and frustrating at the same time.\nKilling my lights at night from my bed or turning them on when I walk in the door at night is great.\nHowever, the problem is that each bulb has a name, can be grouped into rooms, which also have names. This can complicate things. Saying \"Alexa turn off the kitchen light\" will return either a \"sure\" with the light going off, or something like \"you have multiple things with that name, please specify.\" This happens seemingly randomly.\nAs it's primarily a software issue, this gets 4/5 since I'm expecting updates to resolve the unintuitiveness of this human computer interaction."}
{"Author": "A. Wheeler", "Date": "on November 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The bundle price is very good as compared to buying the components separately", "Text": "The bundle price is very good as compared to buying the components separately. We've been adding additional Hue lights over time, and they all work flawlessly. It's easy to program your own routines, which make it seem as if someone is home. Overall, very happy."}
{"Author": "G. Hobson", "Date": "on November 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Extremely easy to set up and use", "Text": "I bought this product along with the echo dot. Extremely easy to set up and use. I have already added four more lights to go with the start up kit. The Philips Hue can accommodate up to 50 lights."}
{"Author": "bigbreeze8\ud83d\ude07", "Date": "on November 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I am pleased with the product, and now12/3 totally jazzed becase I got help from Hue", "Text": "With a little help from Amazon I had these working in 10 minutes. I am pleased with the product. I have two color light also, I was able to get one of those working, I know I am doing something wrong, I just have to figure out what?\n\nAdd on to above review 12/3: I finally got the right info. Download the app from the Hue support page( there's a link to the app store and the correct app.) Set up an account online, download the app, set-up your bridge, to set up your lights follow the instructions and before you search for the lights. First copy the 6 digit S/Number of each light on a piece of paper. Enter the serial number and check the search button. Wa La, this will be rewarding! One by one your lights will appear and blink once! When your done you will see all your lites in a list with a description of each. Now if you have Alexa and echo dot you can say, \"Alexa discover devices?\" and by golly she will answer you! If you have four devices she will answer that she found four znd they will be listed. Now you can create groups. Enjoy\n\nps I mainly control and create my scenes with my phone and control my lights via voice with Alexa.\n\n1-800-555-0050 Mon-Fri EST 9am-6pm, 6am-3pm PST They are very helpful!! Do yourself a favour and call them. Oh, by the way. I don't work for Hue or Amazon\ud83d\ude02.\nMichael"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 27, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not as cool or user friendly as the other echo connected devices ...", "Text": "Not as cool or user friendly as the other echo connected devices I've bought. The app is difficult to maneuver. Product does work manually but the timing isn't cooperating."}
{"Author": "Amazon Addict", "Date": "on November 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smarter lighting!", "Text": "Great starter package, once you try these you'll be hooked!"}
{"Author": "Jswizzy", "Date": "on November 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Fun"}
{"Author": "cva", "Date": "on November 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It is like living in the future", "Text": "We are having a blast with our Alexa Dot. It is like living in the future. I have mobility issues and find little things like being able to turn the lights out is facilitated with the Dot."}
{"Author": "The Redfish", "Date": "on November 26, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is a great product when it works", "Text": "Ok here is the only review that you need to look at.\n\nThis is a great product when it works, I have spent over 150.00 in the light bulbs alone, it was easy to setup and worked right away and worked with echo when it wanted too, the problem started four weeks later, no communication with lights from echo or the hue app. Reset and reprogrammed worked for a week, then no communication again I tried everything to get work but did not work\n\nI would have given 5 stars in first month, but there is an obivious flaw in the hue hub and or lights\nultimately dissapointed"}
{"Author": "Jared", "Date": "on November 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great reliability and a while ago they rolled back their ...", "Text": "Great reliability and a while ago they rolled back their previous really bad move of excluding 3rd party products. I have 24 hue bulbs, 2 switche, and a motion sensor and I'm back to highly recommending them to everyone else!"}
{"Author": "Nick Keough", "Date": "on November 25, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Purchased the Starter Kit a while back as a gift ...", "Text": "Purchased the Starter Kit a while back as a gift. Light bulbs worked fine--as lighting sources--but the bridge never worked. Plugged it into every outlet in the house, but it never powered on. Tried resetting the device, but still nothing. Return window closed (though, that's my fault for purchasing the gift so early in advance), but ultimately, spent 80 dollars for two regular light bulbs."}
{"Author": "Arthur Chin", "Date": "on November 25, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Product - Be aware that you need a cable slot on your router!", "Text": "Awesome product that makes life so much easier.\n\nI have two floor lamps so turning each on and off would be annoying as they are on opposite sides of my bedroom.\n\nI reduced one stay because you need to have a slot on your router for the bridge which isn't apparent when purchasing. Luckily i had one slot left"}
{"Author": "Phillip Randall", "Date": "on November 25, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Esy To Set Up with Echo", "Text": "Easy to set up with Amazon Echo. Turns the light on and off easily with voice."}
{"Author": "JC Strout", "Date": "on November 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic lighting system!", "Text": "Best smart lighting system, regular software updates so you do not have to worry about security, Phillips has your back!"}
{"Author": "Betty Truax", "Date": "on November 24, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not as bad as you might think, but maybe not worth it", "Text": "It took me almost a week (not full time, but an hour or so a day) to get this to work, but it eventually did. I think the problem is primarily in the software and/or customer support. Virtually no instructions come with the package, it basically says plug it into the network. When you look at the related apps, there are 3 or 4 of them depending where you look. I primary use a Fire tablet at home so I went there first. There are 2 apps available. The first is is just called Hue and it appears to be from Phillips. It didn't work at all for me. It would get to the bridge paring step and just sit there. I then downloaded the other App called \"All 4 Hue\". It seemed to find the bridge OK, but then couldn't find the lights. I was about to give up, but I figured I would see if Alexa could see them. Lo and behold she could, and I could control them. However, there appeared to be no way to change the name of the lights from the default \"Hue ultra light ...\". I quit in frustration. The next day, I tried downloading and installing the Hue app on my iPhone. It seemed to work much better than the Fire version - the bridge paring worked anyway, but still no way to changes the name. I decided to go back through the sequence, and noticed I had failed to create an account on the Phillips Hue web site (I generally skip this step , not being a fan of never-ending spam.) I went ahead and set up an account, and discovered that all my devices we're visible on the website, and there is a way to change the names! I did so, and once I \"forgot\" and \"rediscovered\" the devices on Alexa all was well.\n\nSo, a few observations\" 1) You have to be willing to struggle a little to get things to work. I can't imagine why Philips can't just fix their app so that it works correctly in all its versions,. It seems to indicate that they aren't real committed to this whole Hue thing, so it may not be a good long term play, especially in the smart home space that has so many competing technologies. 2) It's a little disturbing that all your stuff ends up out on the web and you have no control over it. Smart home devices may be the next big target for hackers, since there don't seem to be any user accessible security controls provided beyond having a strong password at the site. Of course, this is true for the vast majority of the devices on the internet of things."}
{"Author": "david knight", "Date": "on November 24, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "worked as expected"}
{"Author": "Christopher John", "Date": "on November 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love these bulbs", "Text": "I'm hooked on these bulbs, started with these 2, bought 3 more. Love them"}
{"Author": "marc chase", "Date": "on November 23, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "works with alexa", "Text": "Works great with Alexa/Echo"}
{"Author": "Slainte", "Date": "on November 23, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very easy to use and set up", "Text": "Very easy to use and set up. Works with Amazon Echo and Harmony remote. I just wish the bulbs were brighter."}
{"Author": "dep", "Date": "on November 23, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "The addiction begins."}
{"Author": "R. Thompson", "Date": "on November 23, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't bother", "Text": "Huge disappointment.I loaded the Hues app onto my Fire 8.9hdx. Hues app just doesn't work. Perhaps it works on the Kindle Fire. Loaded the app onto my iphone. It works there. BUT I bought two types of Hue bulbs and it only sees one. I'll give this a week and probably return it. Very, very disappointed. Flat out won't work with Alexa."}
{"Author": "Jason", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works with Alexa, but you have to configure it properly first. Which is somewhat misleading.", "Text": "I had trouble connecting this properly to my echo dot. Alexa did not want to turn lights on and off when I configured her with the Hue groups.\n\nThat's the trick, you CAN NOT use the Hue groups with Alexa. Skip those entirely and make an Alexa group, and the Alexa group must have hardware only items things like \"Hue white lamp 1\"... no hue groups allowed.\n\nFix the hue groups so they can work with Alexa and I would give it the fifth star."}
{"Author": "Healthy living", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "as stated"}
{"Author": "jackemama", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "it's hard to gt the system to recognize ant hue bulb not included in the set up package."}
{"Author": "cjcassidy07", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it except for one flaw", "Text": "Works great with Alexa and would be great overall if there wasn't one issue. After a certain amount of hours of being off the lights will automatically turn on. 3 times this week I have come home from work and the lights have been on.\n\nIs there a way to fix this."}
{"Author": "Jeremy Hendricks", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not there yet", "Text": "I recently purchased a house and have been slowly outfitting it with various \"smart devices.\" Despite the expensive entry point to the hue bulbs I decided to make the plunge and give it a try. The idea was to have it linked with my Amazon Echo and be voice controlled. It didn't really work out very well to be honest. I am a tech guy and was able to start getting things figured out and getting it to work with the help of some forums and youtube videos. I can imagine my mother having quite the time trying to get everything up and running.\n\nAnother annoyance for me personally was the \"warm\" color of these bulbs. Now I will take responsibility for not fully researching and figuring out which bulbs were \"warm,\" which were color, and which had the varied \"whites.\" I recently purchased both SHINE HAI LED Light Bulbs 60 Watt Equivalent, A19 LED Bulb UL-Listed, Daylight Light Bulbs 5000K, E26 Socket, Not Dimmable - Pack of 6 and Philips 455717 100W Equivalent A19 LED Daylight Light Bulb, 4-Pack absolutely LOVE them. The bright \"daylight\" whites these bulbs emit is almost life changing. By far the overall best and biggest change I have made to the house. After research I understand the hue bulbs can come in \"daylight\" versions, but this wasn't it and they are much more expensive.\n\nAlso with these the power to the lights have to be on at all time (light switch on). Where this may be a problem for some (me for example) is that in my kitchen for example I have nine light bulbs that are actuated by the light switch. Therefore if I wanted to install the hue I would have to go \"all in\" with all nine lights. It isn't a pick and choose thing.\n\nThese could work out for some I could imagine but I'll pass for now until the connectivity and price issues are improved."}
{"Author": "Jenn Grover", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Why did I wait so long to get these?", "Text": "I wish I had known how awesome the Hue lights were a year ago. These are simply excellent bulbs. I was always blowing bulbs for turning the switch too fast - now, I never turn the switch, I control the lights from my phone, tablet, or automatically set them from the app or from IFTTT. The starter set is enough to get you hooked. After reading various reviews, it seems that these are by far the best on the market today and from my experience, I would concur.\n\nThe starter set gets your what you need for a basic home set-up. Internet through wifi hotspot (not cellular) is required. I love that this plays nicely with Alexa, Google, and SmartThings.\n\nMy favorite light \"recipes\" include flashing when I get a text message, automatically turning on a \"scene\" at sunset, and flashing along with my Hue Go light changing colors when it begins to snow."}
{"Author": "Fadhlan Rahim", "Date": "on November 22, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to install. Fast delivery.", "Text": "Great product. Fast delivery. Easy to install. Would have given 5 stars if it could be changed to Cool Daylight. It's warm white, which is basically yellow. Should have known better."}
{"Author": "Tisa Y.", "Date": "on November 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product.", "Text": "Using these in desk lamps that required low watt bulbs due to plastic housing. They are great. Bulbs don't get hot at all but put out a large amount of light. I'm using them with Alexa and they work flawlessly. Great product. I didn't use the bridge because I have a newer generation one but the price was still cheaper this way."}
{"Author": "Kenneth E. O'Rourke", "Date": "on November 21, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There is no information on how to set this item ...", "Text": "There is no information on how to set this item up or use it. There is no web site to contact for help and there is no telephone number to call"}
{"Author": "A. Pinhel", "Date": "on November 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy to use and install."}
{"Author": "JVY44", "Date": "on November 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love them"}
{"Author": "Geo", "Date": "on November 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Extremely satisfied."}
{"Author": "Schlemazl Beerbaum", "Date": "on November 20, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't buy if you have no empty Ethernet sockets left in your router.", "Text": "Can only connect via Ethernet cable to your router. What a joke. Really, its 2016. Google OnHub router comes with just 1 (ONE) Ethernet port, because usually EVERYTHING nowadays are WiFi capable. This bridge is not WiFi capable. You literally need to plug it into your router with a provided Ethernet cable. I could not believe this. I have also noticed, that if you router is somewhere in one corner of the house and this is where you will have to set your Hue Bridge - its signal may not reach all of its light bulbs, if they happen to be located far enough from it without other hue lights in between to act as signal extenders.\n\nUPDATE: Thanks to the alert reader who pointed out that I neglected to add the following disclaimer: You must be prepared to buy an ethernet switch (nowadays gigabit is probably a better option) in addition to this HUE Bridge, if you are out of available sockets on your router. They run anywhere between $15 to $30. Make sure you have enough available electrical sockets to plug in all that extra gear near your main router, or that your ethernet cords are long enough to get you to the next available wall plug or power strip."}
{"Author": "Kevin n Lange", "Date": "on November 20, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty much junk", "Text": "Hue works ok stand alone, and works about 20% of the time with Alexa. If you want a stand alone light control, it will work ok in your house with your cell or tablet on wi fi. Outside the house you will constantly get a \"no connection\" and it is very spotty. I have a Hub and two bulbs. I have 2 echo dots and a TAP. With the TAP the Hue lights work about 80% of the time. With the DOT I typically get \" the device names bedroom is not responding\" then the DOT stays blue for about a minute. The UE hub plugs in to your router to connect to your tablet or ECHO, but transfers to the lights over Zig bee. It's a really stupid design. When it works it's cool, but it is extremely limited. As an example you have to control each light or group with one command. You can not say \" Alexa turn bedoom off and living room to 50%\"...you would have to name that scene \"bromance\" etc. You also can not set the lights to turn on at a specific time with Alexa, just shut off as a sleep timer. A ton of improvement. Will return all my DOTs and hue lighting as it is not ready for real world......sorry to give some reality to all the fake reviews."}
{"Author": "Spyderman", "Date": "on November 20, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I was eventually able to get this up and running ...", "Text": "I was eventually able to get this up and running, and now it is working as advertised. Documentation was only so-so. The main reason I only gave it a three star rating is the rather modest benefit. Perhaps when I begin experimenting with other features, this opinion will change. While I can see this as a Godsend for someone with mobility disabilities, I don't see being able to turn off a light with my voice to be a major advantage, and not worth $60-$70. But, again, I have not progressed beyond the most basic applications.\nBTW you will need a router in your network to connect the bridge to.\n\nAddendum 12/11/16: If you recently received this and are having difficulty setting it up and are beginning to think it's a POS, wait until you start using it. I tried to set it up for my wife's account in addition to mine, again with NO INSTRUCTIONS, and found it could no longer 'find' MY account. Don't know if the problem is with the Echo or Hue. I'm about 2-3 hours into resolving this, with the end nowhere in sight. This is such a pain in the butt, before trying to enhance your system I'd recommend you purchase an industrial size tube of preparation H"}
{"Author": "Charati", "Date": "on November 20, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "After 6 months the bridge just quit working.", "Text": "I bought this in April, 2016 and after six months of using it and enjoying it, the bridge just stopped working. Their website gives no real support and after googling it, it seems to be a nightmare to try to fix it. It just stopped working. I have gone through rebooting the router, trying to manually put in the IP address, even resetting it to factory settings and nothing has worked.\nI gave it two stars because when it worked it was awesome, but now I am stuck with some very pricey light bulbs. Even replacing it for another $60 for a new bridge probably won't work according to reviews, because the software says I have to get permission from the previous person to share it with me, which is me, of course.\nI will call support and report back if they are any help.\n\nhttps://smile.amazon.com/dp/B014H2OZAC/ref=cm_cr_ryp_prd_ttl_sol_0"}
{"Author": "Amanda J. McMahan", "Date": "on November 19, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great... when it actually works", "Text": "I bought this kit locally because I was impatient and did not want to wait for it to be shipped. I wanted to love it, I really really did. Unfortunately, I think this technology needs a little more work to get the final bugs out before I can love it.\nThe bulbs periodically become \"unreachable\" which is annoying as you have to try all sorts of things to get them back to working again. Sometimes a simple reset of the hub works, sometimes you have to go through many steps to figure out why it will not work and sometimes you end up on the phone with tech support as they walk you through the same things you have already tried.\nI have owned this set for 6 months now, it is the latest generation and I have the latest firmware update and yet my bulbs STILL end up \"unreachable\" which leaves me not being able to control them with any app, and also makes them not work when they are set up as a routine. This has happened at least 5 times since I got them and it is quite frustrating. Especially since I depend on one of my bulbs to help me wake up with a gradual brightening of the room. I should have just bought a daytime simulator for the room but I wanted controllable bulbs elsewhere and it would be nice to have everything on the same system.\nThere is no rhyme or reason to the issue either: they go offline after any power outage, the distance from the hub makes no difference, sometimes I have to actually delete them from the app and add them back manually..a real pain to have to keep doing. And today that is not working at all. Which means I will be back on the phone with tech support. Again.\nWhen it works, it is great but then I face disappointment and inconvenience when it does not work. It definitely makes me hesitate to continue to add bulbs to the system. My original plan was to replace most of the bulbs in my home with these. I will NOT be doing that until they are more dependable."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 19, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "automated lights", "Text": "Works good. I got it set up with my amazon echo, goggle home and IFTT. Using IFTTT the lights turn on at sunset and turn off at my set time. The android app works well allowing on/off and dimmable controls."}
{"Author": "Amelanchier", "Date": "on November 18, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love the concept, but....", "Text": "After reading simple instructions multiple times hoping I missed something, plugging and unplugging power suppy, moving device, changing light bulbs, installing multiple software, uninstalling software, moving ethernet ports, watching youtube videos, reading tech support webpages, I was left with an interminable, flashing blue light. I'm relatively tech savvy and have many devices contentedly communicating through our ethernet. Two hours fiddling with this simple device yielded no connection. Perhaps this is a faulty hub, but I'm reluctant to invest more time and money to determine if my hypothesis is correct."}
{"Author": "Robyn", "Date": "on November 18, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These were easy to set up with my home network and I ...", "Text": "These were easy to set up with my home network and I love that I can control the brightness right from the hue iPhone app."}
{"Author": "Tomas", "Date": "on November 17, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not really wireless.", "Text": "The hub does not have wifi and has to connect to router with cable.\nStupidest idea from Philips ever.\nEven my smart plugs have wifi why not this bulky hub?\nI don't have a router at home, so I cannot connect the hub even if I wanted to."}
{"Author": "mezzie", "Date": "on November 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love the lights", "Text": "I love the lights, HATE the app. the app is a pain. But once you get it up and running and pair it to Echo or Google Home it makes life so much easier."}
{"Author": "LostinSouthBama", "Date": "on November 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Purchase", "Text": "installation was smooth as can be and I use it with my Echo Dot to control lighting in the living room. The bulbs are kind of pricey so I'm adding additional lights for other rooms slowly. I love that they are dimmable."}
{"Author": "J. Fortier", "Date": "on November 16, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Useful and intelligent!", "Text": "Not much can be said, great package price with amazon, and great product."}
{"Author": "David D. Brown", "Date": "on November 16, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Use with Echo? Dont waste your time or money.", "Text": "I can't begin to tell you how disappointed I am worth this purchase. If you're buying to use with Alexa/echo, don't bother. It is irritating to set up, inconsistent in operation, frustrating to use...and Alexa isn't smart enough to help. Watching YouTube instruction videos will get you sort of there...but it just isn't consistent or intuitive on any sense. Basically, I bought a remote timer for two lamps. Echo integration (or poor job of it) makes me dislike the device more than I did. Yuck."}
{"Author": "P. Devoe", "Date": "on November 16, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These are white lights only", "Text": "Works well but Buyer Beware, despite the fact that Hue means 'a color' by definition these are white lights only. I didn't read very closely I guess but these are white lights only. They do work well and can be dimmed, temperature can be changed, timers set, etc. I will be keeping them but with no color options on these bulbs I would have stuck with my Wemo."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 16, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very easy to set up on a smart phone", "Text": "Very easy to set up on a smart phone. Significantly more difficult to set up with Alexa, which was why I purchased it. Got it to work and love it. Just have to learn the terms it understands."}
{"Author": "Deepblue", "Date": "on November 15, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice to be able to turn lights on while outdoors ...", "Text": "Totally fabulous!! Nice to be able to turn lights on while outdoors etc. Have to purchase more bulbs etc for other areas."}
{"Author": "MacPara", "Date": "on November 15, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice light bulbs, buggy hub and a major design flaw", "Text": "I bought this kit for exactly one purpose. This should act as a sunrise simulation during the darker winter months to help me wake up a bit more energized in the morning.\nUsing the iPad app allowed me to do that successfully and it does help me with getting up.\nIn addition to that I use the lights as bedside lamps dimmed to 20% when going to bed and I integrated the lights with an Echo Dot for convenience, using voice commands instead of an app. All works great - when it works.\n\nRecently (1 week after the return period for my amazon Prime purchase expired), the hub has started to act up. It seems to shut itself off albeit it has no documented function to do that. I find it plugged in with all the lights off and the power supplu plug measures to provide voltage. I plug it back in and the hub starts up as expected only to be off again some 24h later. It seems to happen more frequently too. Also, I have noticed that the range of the hub seems to have reduced slightly. It used to reliably reach my bulbs in the bedroom all the time. Now I find myself repeating commands to Alexa about the lights because only one of them is responding. After about 3 tries usually all of the bulbs followed the request but this is not how it worked in the first few weeks.\nI guess I will have to deal with Philips Customer Service to get my hub repaired. That's pretty annoying given Philips' reputation and the fact that this hub just worked fine for a few weeks. Of course, the lights' main function will not be available for the time the hub is gone as the lights only turn off or fully on when using a physical switch.\n\nOh, and one more thing to consider when you buy these to use in your bedroom! I live in an area where power outages are common. You will not enjoy these bulbs during nights where the power goes down and then decides to come back up at 3am. Even worse if the power flickers and cannot decide if it wants to stay on or not, as these bulbs do NOT go back to their pre-power-loss state but always to full on.\nI learned this the hard way when we had intermittent power outages due to wind tearing off a wire on a close-by power pole. The lights briefly went to 100% and then turned off half a second later and then doing the same over and over within a few minutes. Once I determined what was going on I was of course fully awake and the next work day was a pain to go through. Not what I was looking for exactly. I do not recommend these for your bedroom because of this design flaw!"}
{"Author": "Seven", "Date": "on November 15, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good Purchase", "Text": "Have had this about a month and have had no issues. Works absolutely great."}
{"Author": "Leslie Trowbridge", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Wrong Bulbs Sent -- Actually 840W / 9.5W, Slower Response Times", "Text": "Beautiful lights and great ecosystem but one big problem with this kit specifically: the bulbs included are 840 lumen @ 9W as opposed to 800 lumen @ 9.5W stated in the product description.\n\nCompared to the 800 lumen version, there is a noticeable delay in startup and general responsiveness to brightness change requests.\n\nIn the image, notice the expected bulb on the left is 800W, actual bulb on the right is 840W.\n\nReturning and will buy individual components separate."}
{"Author": "Mike5514", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great"}
{"Author": "MadStan1", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great gift for those interested in home automation/Amazon Echo integration", "Text": "Bought this as a birthday present for my dad who is gone pretty crazy with home automation through Amazon Echo. He said that it was easy to set up and got it paired with Alexa very quickly. This is a good buy for anyone interested in this kind of tech but not ready to make a big investment.He has since bought a set of the color changing bulbs, in addition to a second set of white bulbs as well as well."}
{"Author": "Warren Carter", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Bought this for my buddy for his house warming. His family loves it"}
{"Author": "Jim Geisler", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very disappointed. Still have not figured out the name Alexa ...", "Text": "Very disappointed. Still have not figured out the name Alexa wants to control the lights. The phone app only works with the same Wi-Fi the lights are on. So I cannot turn the lights on or off unless I am within range of my home Wi-Fi. And I wanted to be able to turn the light on from work over the Internet. Very disappointed."}
{"Author": "Walter Carmichael", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very good product & easy to set up with Alexa, plus you can dim or brighten bulb"}
{"Author": "Spike", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Have to yell to make it work. Total junk!!!!"}
{"Author": "Sgitheanach", "Date": "on November 14, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If your lights go out, even for a second... All of these lights will be turned on when the electricity is restored", "Text": "These lights are great... except If your lights go out, even for a second... All of these lights will be turned on when the electricity is restored are great except i... That's great in the middle of the night... Not... When you retire for the night, you might want to set the manual switches to the off position... But, if you're away from home, maybe not so bad..."}
{"Author": "Lauri", "Date": "on November 13, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "WHAT do you mean..where's the bridge? It's right here darnit!", "Text": "After downloading the Hue app it didnt recognize my wifi and couldnt find the bridge. Seriously?\nI am not very techie, so it's frustrating when things dont work as they say they will.\nI got the white lights to just control at home with my Alexa Dots, and was determined to be able to ask her to dim and turn them on and off!! (This is going to work if it takes all night...mumble curse mumble) But the app never worked.\nSurprisingly no help from Mayday, I think I got someone from a Country speaking little English.\nIn desperation I went to my Alexa app...lo and behold after clicking on smart home and find devices...she found the lights immediately and is dimming and turning on and off like crazy!!! I am a giggling fool having such fun with this.\nI have a Kindle HDX (which I Iove), so maybe the Hue app just doesnt work well with that as opposed to a smartphone (which I dont use)...but for others like me...if you have Echo or Dot you can plug the Hue hub into your router and power outlet, and still be able to control your bulbs WITHOUT the Hue app by using your Alexa app.\nSigh..looks like I will have to break down and buy a smartphone soon in order to use these lights remotely...but for now I have Alexa controlling these fabulous lights, and I am doing the happy dance!\nThe lights are extremely cool, the white color shades are inviting, and I plan to automate the whole house now. Seriously addicting I'm tellin ya.\nThe lights are a 10 star for sure..but I'm giving 4 due to the set up issues.\nGet it together Philips..if it weren't for Alexa (and Amazon) I would never have purchased these in the first place. Set up needs to work with the KINDLE FIRE TABLETS as well :)"}
{"Author": "AIS", "Date": "on November 13, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works well with Echo", "Text": "Works well with Amazon echo. But needs more light options. Looking for something similar to daylight"}
{"Author": "Love it", "Date": "on November 13, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for starters", "Text": "Works great"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 13, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do I need to use the light switches in my ...", "Text": "Do I need to use the light switches in my house? Do I keep the light switches always on or what?"}
{"Author": "Bryan", "Date": "on November 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Probably my favorite purchase in the last month i can control my ...", "Text": "Probably my favorite purchase in the last month i can control my entire houses lighting from my house. extremely easy to set up and get working."}
{"Author": "Holly Mehringer", "Date": "on November 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love them!", "Text": "Not sure how easy they are to get going, my husband handled that but they work great. Love being able to turn lights on and off and even dim and brighten them without getting up."}
{"Author": "anton cupid", "Date": "on November 12, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Good"}
{"Author": "earl07", "Date": "on November 12, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "One bulb quit working after two weeks Light still works but will not turn on or off"}
{"Author": "Brandon S.", "Date": "on November 11, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bulb Burnt Out After 1 Hour of Use", "Text": "After about 1 hour of total use and three weeks after the purchase, one of the bulbs is already dead. The dead bulb was plugged into a regular kitchen ceiling light. The previous generic bulb, which probably cost $1.50, had not been changed since I bought the house over two years ago. Needless to say, at the price paid for these bulbs, I'm terribly disappointed."}
{"Author": "Rendall Seely", "Date": "on November 11, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I bought this new (Square) Bridge with the promise from ...", "Text": "I bought this new (Square) Bridge with the promise from Hue Philips that it would be able to control my Hue Philips Color Bulbs. (Yes, I know that I can't do color scene changes with my white bulbs) I have followed all of the directions listed. I have not yet been able to control any of the Hue Philips Color Scenes through my Amazon Echo. If you are thinking about spending more money to purchase a new Generation 2 Square Bridge I would advise you to save your money and wait until Hue Philips's technology is able to catch up and provide a reliable service."}
{"Author": "rytchard", "Date": "on November 11, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "We'll Leave the Light on for Ya!", "Text": "Have only had this item for a day but I am definitely liking it so far. It was easy to set up and working within minutes. The apps (both the hue app and Iphone My Homekit) are a little klunky but I am sure with some time I will learn their ins and outs. I set it up last night to wake me in the morning with a gradual increase of light over a 30 minute period of time. Worked like a charm. Siri interface works well too! Now that the time has changed I used to leave a light or two on since it is dark by the time I get home. Now, I set the lights to come on automatically at sunset during the days that I work. A little pricey but if you are like me and enjoy your electronic toys this one is a keeper."}
{"Author": "Rookzer", "Date": "on November 10, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bright White Light", "Text": "I use this with my Amazon Echo and love it. You can always tell when there is an update because they will not work until the update completes. The bulbs are, or can be, very bright depending on what you set them on."}
{"Author": "Richard T. Heagberg", "Date": "on November 10, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "App could not find the bridge", "Text": "what a waist of time trying to set this up only to find that my hue app could not find the bridge. rebbooting everything and still could not find the bridge. When are they going to make something that does not need a bridge but only the echo.."}
{"Author": "danielduck", "Date": "on November 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but this is a great way to start off your smart lighting collection", "Text": "The bulbs were 'warmer' in color than I had expected (I typically prefer a brighter white bulb), but this is a great way to start off your smart lighting collection.\n\nI set up programs where the lights turn off automatically, are already on when I get home from work, and dim as the night goes on.\n\nThe Echo/Alexa integration is just icing on the cake."}
{"Author": "Leslie Wizner", "Date": "on November 9, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Gets room very bright on alarm if u use app to turn of lights", "Text": "I set these up as my alarm it works much better than my light alarm clock because they get the room much brighter:) Works well when I use the hue tablet app to turn off my bedroom light but it won't work if I use the switch to turn off my bedroom light"}
{"Author": "Ed B.", "Date": "on November 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Well made Great quality well worth the money."}
{"Author": "Angel98", "Date": "on November 9, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It doesn't work like it suppose to", "Text": "Product is terible, It doesn't work like it suppose to. The lights turn on when ever and they never turn off when they suppose to. What is the purpose of paying premium when you can pay 1/4 of the price for a timer and it works whenever is needed?"}
{"Author": "Charles Johnston", "Date": "on November 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Automating lighting, a tech geeks dream!", "Text": "Loving my light automation! As a techie I love automation. Still learning the lights but paired with the Echo Dot they are alot of fun. Will be buying more!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on November 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Buy buy buy", "Text": "The light work great. My wife loves using them the kids love the dim"}
{"Author": "TheGreatMangini", "Date": "on November 8, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Won't Turn Off", "Text": "Loaded all the apps on my Alexa and iPhone no problem. Found the lights no problem. Dim the lights with voice command no problem. Turn off the lights - PROBLEM! The lights momentarily turn off and then turn on again. So strange. Oh well, return!"}
{"Author": "Lisa", "Date": "on November 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So easy to set up! Highly recommended!", "Text": "I am absolutely thrilled with my Philips Hue starter kit. I purchased it and two additional bulbs and was able to get them installed and set up within 10 minutes. It was so easy and I love the fact that they are dimmable and can be programmed to turn on and off on a schedule. I have an Amazon Echo and it works seamlessly with that as well. Highly recommended!\n\nI previously purchased two WeMo switches that were a pain in the rear to set up, but did work well for few months. It took quite a few tries for my Echo to find them though. Then they stopped working and I could not get them replaced. I've also tried a GELink starter kit but the bulbs would not connect at all."}
{"Author": "Dave Hemke", "Date": "on November 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love them, even if I really don't have a use case for them.", "Text": "These work quite well, and do what you expect them to do. However, they are still very much a cool tech toy without any real purpose or utility.\n\nMy house and my office is now a hodge podge of smart HUE bulbs and light strips, wemo switches and plugs, all controlled from app or the Amazon echo. Besides Alexa occasionally talking back, \"I was unable to find xxx device on your account,\" or a single light in a room group refusing to play nicely everything works pretty well.\n\nHaving said that, I think we're still squarely in early adopter territory, and one should be ready for their more tech challenged spouse (we would have just said wife in the good ole days) to frequently point out that the automated timers frequently fail, arguing with Alexa takes more time than flipping a physical light switch, and there is hardly ever a good reason to turn the room blue."}
{"Author": "Eileen Champagne", "Date": "on November 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "AWESOME", "Text": " Simple to install and compatible with the Amazon Echo! Love i!!"}
{"Author": "R. Good", "Date": "on November 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worked like it should", "Text": "Was easy to set up and worked like it is supposed to work. Just wish they had 100W bulbs."}
{"Author": "Donna H.", "Date": "on November 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I really love the system. Works great and super easy to install. I wish they were sold at Lowe's!!"}
{"Author": "jack rastin", "Date": "on November 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "great product. lot of fun but needed contact fue ...", "Text": "great product.lot of fun\nbut needed contact fue service to conect to Alexa.\nwas done in 5 min."}
{"Author": "Marina", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great lights", "Text": "Easy to use and easy set up. It only took a few minutes for the bridge to connect to my home wifi and it was easy to set up the Rooms on the Hue app and then voice controlled by Alexa."}
{"Author": "C. Hull", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Be Warned. Philips wants iCloud Keychain Actived To Work. NO NO No", "Text": "When I went to setup the light bulbs, I found it required me to active iCloud Keychain. A light bulb does not need access to my passwords and credit card information. With all the security breaches going on, I will not give that information to a company that does not need it. No other home automation product company has asked for access that information."}
{"Author": "Elks", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These bulbs are 840 Lumens. Great set!", "Text": "Jumping into Smart home lighting for the first time, we went with this starter kit to start. With all the different apps involved (he hue app, apple home kit, amazon Alexa), it seemed a little daunting. We have 2 echo dots, use apple home kit, have two Ecobee's (which we love), so we were ready to make the leap. After installing the bulbs and plugging in the bridge, we were completely shocked with how easy it was to be up and running. Everyone's results will vary of course, but we had the echo dots connected to the bridge, the lights registered on the hue app and connected, the lights showing up in home kit, and voice commands to Siri and Alexa changing the dimness within 10 mins! We were impressed.\n\nOne thing to note, amazon is not advertising this, but these lights must be a new release as they are 840 Lumens, a touch more powerful than the last series of bulbs. We also went to Bed Bath and Beyond and they were selling single 840 Lumen bulbs as well. Last week however, we ordered the 2 pack from Amazon of the regular A 19 bulbs that were including in this kit and they were only 800 lumens. Hopefully Amazon is just working through inventory and the new generation bulbs that BBB is selling and the ones included in this kit will be sold on Amazon as pairs.\n\nBottom line is this kit is great, astonishingly easy to set up and use (even set timers and commands) , and most important look great and don't flicker!"}
{"Author": "Robert Tarasov", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It doesn't work with Echo/Alexa", "Text": "It doesn't actually work with Amazon Echo. Without voice command this thing is useless ..."}
{"Author": "Shelo", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I have to give them away.", "Text": "Don't buy this type of you don't have a spot on your router to plug them in. Useless!"}
{"Author": "Joseph H.", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not Bright Enough", "Text": "These standard A19 bulbs are not nearly bright enough and Philips does not make a brighter Hue LED bulb. Sort of a head scratcher. Probably wouldn't buy this again."}
{"Author": "Archie", "Date": "on November 5, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product. Unfortunately the setup process for linking it ...", "Text": "Great product. Unfortunately the setup process for linking it to Alexa is a bit ridiculous (I am not going to go into the steps it took)."}
{"Author": "Madelin Corrales", "Date": "on November 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy setup."}
{"Author": "David Simon", "Date": "on November 3, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Perfect Alexa integration", "Text": "You light up my life automatically. Perfect Alexa integration. Flawless setup."}
{"Author": "GARY W HICKS", "Date": "on November 3, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Hue Lights and Gadgets Really Work Great.", "Text": "This is the heart of my Philips Hue lighting automation setup. I now have Hue lights and gadgets throughout my house. They are great."}
{"Author": "Jeanne Nichols", "Date": "on November 3, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Useless to me! Didn't work and no support from Philips ...", "Text": "Was very excited to get this product to work with my Alexa echo dot (which i LOVE) and was very disappointed when the app did not recognize the bridge device on my Wi-Fi system. I could see it on my system but the app could not ~~ I checked online support and it was suggested that I try to reboot/reset the router which i did and it didn't work. They then suggested, if that didn't work and if I have a dual band router (which i do) to delete my guest, 3ghz and 5ghz channels and start over one at a time to see if the device would be recognized. Well i was not going to remove all my channels, so I contacted Philips support and they sent me a ticket telling me that they would contact me as soon as possible. That was 6 days ago! Needless to say, I am returning this item and letting all buyers know that if this is not working with your system there seems to be no real solution or explanation. Very, disappointed in the device but maybe more so by Philips .... VERY BAD CUSTOMER SUPPORT"}
{"Author": "Pantera", "Date": "on November 2, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice but not perfect", "Text": "Nice but not perfect"}
{"Author": "Michelle schriver", "Date": "on November 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Fabulous."}
{"Author": "Ruthie", "Date": "on November 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Add 8 more light works great"}
{"Author": "C. Jennings", "Date": "on November 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but I love being able to tell Alexa to turn on the", "Text": "it's kind of spendy, but I love being able to tell Alexa to turn on the lights"}
{"Author": "Jay W. Murphy", "Date": "on November 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great But Pricey Lights", "Text": "I have purchased 2 sets of the Phillips Hue LED White Bulbs Sets to go along with this Starter Kit and they work fantastic! I have the six bulbs, 2 each in my master bedroom, my living room, and my second bedroom and have ordered another set of bulbs to put in my computer room. They can be driven by my Amazon Echo device by voice and they really work well. I also bought 3 Amazon Dot's (these work in concert with the echo device) to put in my master bedroom, second bedroom and computer room. That way I can be in any room in my house and turn lights on or off. At night I can turn on an alarm to wake up in the morning. I can also set timers in the kitchen. These are amazing personal assistants and you can ask them any question at all and receive an answer immediately. Definitely cool!"}
{"Author": "Alison Harris", "Date": "on November 1, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These are so great! The HUE app isn't the best", "Text": "These are so great! The HUE app isn't the best, but we use these lights with Alexa and the iHome app anyway. We've been very impressed with how easy it is to make groups and operate them. We even had the added surprise that they were dimmable. We'll say \"Alexa, put the living room at 50%\", etc. It took us a few tries to find the right commands, but it was easy. Highly suggested!!"}
{"Author": "ProfessorJD", "Date": "on November 1, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Inconsistent with Alexa", "Text": "Philips app lets you turn on and off, and dim each bulb (we have two bulbs grouped together: matching table lamps on the MBR dresser). Alexa can turn them both on and dim them, but ask her to turn them off and one stays on. Literally cannot turn the second bulb off without using the phone ( which is downstairs, since we don't want the NSA listening to everything) or physically getting up out of bed and turning off the light switch across the room. Not much point of being wireless if it doesn't work."}
{"Author": "Mike Chombeau", "Date": "on November 1, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Warning, requires a hardwired network Connection to use", "Text": "Warning, requires a hardwired network Connection to use."}
{"Author": "Geghard", "Date": "on November 1, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not functional", "Text": "If you are going to use this product with Alexa so you will probably use ifttt to make it easier to use.Philips hue has many connection problems with ifttt so few times a week you need to visit ifttt website to fix connection problems. I'm using Alexa+ifttt with other devices such as harmony hub and I haven't had any problem with them."}
{"Author": "Chris W.", "Date": "on November 1, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Sooo Easy!", "Text": "This system is so cool! We have an apartment with limited preinstalled lights and switch operated outlets, so this setup is perfect. It's beyond easy to set up, and use. I even find myself using these bulbs on switch operated lights since they are dimmable via the app, regardless of switch type."}
{"Author": "ChumlyDad", "Date": "on November 1, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Cool Product", "Text": "This is a really cool system to manage lights. I use it mainly to manage my outdoor security lights on porches, over the front door etc. I've found it much easier and more intuitive than a competitor."}
{"Author": "C.B.", "Date": "on October 31, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Quick and easy - no more walking into a dark room.", "Text": "I was skeptical but with the days getting shorter I always hate walking into a dark room or house. Thanks to a quick 5 minute set up, all I have to do is ask Alexa to turn on the kitchen, bedroom light. Now I need to buy more bulbs for more area in my house!"}
{"Author": "KAS", "Date": "on October 31, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love using it, especially with Echo", "Text": "Works great, including with Amazon Echo. I use it as a nightly timer and also turn the lights on and off with Echo at other times. The software interface on the Philips site needs improving so took some patience and trial and error to get set up. Probably took 30 minutes to register and get it working - not bad, but definitely needs improving."}
{"Author": "Joe", "Date": "on October 31, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "very cool easy set up . works with the amazon echo"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 30, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "ORANGE LIGHT COLOR. BE AWARE.", "Text": "It works fine, but you should know that the light color is ORANGE, not white. A total disappointment. The color should be white, like all other modern bulbs."}
{"Author": "CharlieG", "Date": "on October 30, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "you can't do anything like controlling a ceiling fan", "Text": "Can't get much easier to install. The box plugs into your router... and you screw in the light bulbs. Only thing to keep in mind with this system is that they don't have wall switch replacements. It's the bulbs that you buy/replace. So... you can't do anything like controlling a ceiling fan. Also, at ~$15 per white bulb or ~$45 per color light... replacing bulbs could get expensive. (As if the system itself isn't expensive) To control the lights you have to use a cell phone app unless you have an Amazon Echo. Then you can voice control. IMHO it will get old booting up your phone app to turn on the lights... but with Amazon Echo it's fun and easy. Now they do have light switches that you glue to the wall or use as remotes. This avoids having to use the phone app. Of course those cost extra. Oh another advantage is the the bulbs are dimmable. So you can control the brightness without a dimmer switch. With Amazon Echo you can tell it what % you want them to glow. \"Alexa living room lights on at 50%\".... Kind of cool."}
{"Author": "Aphrodite Teya Rios", "Date": "on October 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I LOVE this gadget", "Text": "If I could give this 10 stars i would! I LOVE this gadget. You MUST set up with a computer, didn't set up with Android but once configured on computer great. Easy to connect to the hub for lights and any other angst device and Bluetooth! Use it every day!!"}
{"Author": "TdyerD", "Date": "on October 29, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Misleading color but still good.", "Text": "I love the idea and how it works great with the Echo Dot. I don't use their app bc I have an iPhone and use the iPhone home. The only complaint I have is the miss leading online and the box. It isn't white color light it's the ugly color yellow. Don't call them white color when they light up and it's yellow. Not happy about it bc I want a white LED room not a yellow colored room."}
{"Author": "MichaelReader", "Date": "on October 28, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "Won't connect to wifi, need to be plugged to ethernet. I don't even have one."}
{"Author": "Laurenad2005", "Date": "on October 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "works like a charm. Love being able to turn on lights before I walk in the house."}
{"Author": "doug- florida.", "Date": "on October 27, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "I return the product because I could not connect the bridge from the router to control the lights ."}
{"Author": "Chad Lovegren", "Date": "on October 27, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do not buy...wait to see if Philips works on the app and the integration.", "Text": "Horrible. The app is not easy to use at all. There are no instructions on how to work with the app. The main reason for the 1 star is I wanted this to work with my Alexa and it would not. I only have two light, but Alexa would find 12 for some reason. When I would tell Alexa to \"forget\" the extra light it would work for a couple hours then the extra light would come back. Philips needs to work on the app and the integration."}
{"Author": "NeedleGuy", "Date": "on October 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The starter kit is so easy to install and use!", "Text": "The Phillips Hue LED Starter Kit could not be easier to set up and use with Alexa. Simply plug the starter into your WiFi router (and wall power), screw in the lightbulbs and download the app. It's as simple as that. The app defaults to \"living room\" and \"light 1\" and \"light 2\" so you can use those Alexa commands right away to turn on/off the lights. We love it!"}
{"Author": "Jason Olsen", "Date": "on October 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "How cool!", "Text": "I bought this as an accessory to my Echo Dot 2 and am loving them. Buying more bulbs as soon as I finish this review! I was extremely surprised how easily this hooked up and paired with the Echo Dot. Only thing that caught me off guard was that it needs to be directly linked to your router via Ethernet cable (included). Not a big deal for me but may be for you if your OCD on wires/device placement."}
{"Author": "Danny", "Date": "on October 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "simple setup", "Text": "easy, it was plug and play my alexa was controlling the bulbs, they seem to heat up really hot tho so i dont think ill be leaving these on for too long at a time"}
{"Author": "Amy Harkins", "Date": "on October 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Incredibly Simple Setup", "Text": "The entire setup, from start to finish, took maybe 3 minutes...screw in bulbs, download app, plug in bridge, and connect! The Philips Hue app worked the first time, and my Echo Dot had no problems. Siri is able to control the lights too. Lights are dim-able and look great. It honestly can't get any easier that this!"}
{"Author": "sperkin", "Date": "on October 25, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Work intermittently", "Text": "Great concept when they work - which is only some of the time. Keep getting a message that the lights are unreachable. (And Yes Phillips I have changed the zigbee channel many times)\n\nBought a new router hoping that might make a difference but sadly no change.\n\nWhen they are detected, Echo works great and it's really fun to turn them on when guests are over.\n\nJust be aware when you purchase these lights that you will spend a great deal of time troubleshooting....which kinda defeats the purpose of buying them in the first place."}
{"Author": "Sliph", "Date": "on October 25, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works Great with Echo Dot 2nd Gen!", "Text": " Very pleased with these lights. Setup is fairly easy although you do have to first set up the lights with the hue lights philip app and THEN use the Alexa app to further connect the lights to work with the echo dot. Not a huge deal and I love all the options available. Making groups is a lifesaver! Very happy with results will be buying more for the rest of the house but wanted make sure this actually worked before buying more and happy to report it works flawlessly."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 25, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Get it now.", "Text": "Easy to setup and to use."}
{"Author": "Joseph Mailloux", "Date": "on October 25, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Super easy with Amazon Alexa", "Text": "Super easy with Amazon Alexa,The Hue APP did ot work at all,but My Alexa found the devices and worked right away !!"}
{"Author": "Bryan Hargrave", "Date": "on October 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I can not believe how easy this was to set up", "Text": "I can not believe how easy this was to set up. The lights look fantastic. Very warm temp. I was so impressed that I got more lights. Soon enough I will be all Hue."}
{"Author": "Kindle Customer JennaW", "Date": "on October 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "AWESOME!", "Text": "I got this working in about 5 minutes and I am a senior citizen. I don't have a smartphone but the kindle fire hue app worked easily to name two rooms Now Alexa can turn the lamps on and off as well as dimming. The white lights give out good light. I will be adding more including a multicolor bulb when the next gen. Is available. These voice-controlled lights are a huge safety feature especially for seniors and those with disabilities.\n\nUpdate: I thought one of my bulbs had died and was very upset. After reporting to Philips how embarrassing, I found my housekeeper had accidentally unplugged the lamp behind the couch when she was cleaning."}
{"Author": "Hattie Lake", "Date": "on October 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome", "Text": "Love these! So fun to be able to turn lights on and off with my phone."}
{"Author": "BKRiley", "Date": "on October 23, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Awesome! I'm so lazy now. I just tell my amazing \"Alexa\" to turn off the light."}
{"Author": "Timothy", "Date": "on October 23, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Sometimes it works, sometimes it doesn't", "Text": "App is probably the culprit of the inconsistent ability of the lighting"}
{"Author": "Catcoot", "Date": "on October 23, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Missing pieces", "Text": "The system works, but I'm giving this to stars because I received the package with the wrong adapter and no way of putting it in. Philips customer service was not the best and it took me a while to get the parts I needed for it to work."}
{"Author": "Tills", "Date": "on October 22, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product. Easy setup", "Text": "So easy that I didn't even read instructions. Attached the light bulbs and hub. Downloaded the app. Turned the lights on. Synced the hub by following app instructions. Named the bulbs and voila. All done. I had it ready in 15 minutes start to finish. Then I connected it to Alexa and now my whole family loves turning the lights on. I bought 6 more bulbs and I can't wait to do my whole house."}
{"Author": "Eric R. Roberts", "Date": "on October 22, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The set up was easy and it worked right away", "Text": "I was impressed. The set up was easy and it worked right away. Then, a few minutes later, it didn't work. The connection to my network is unstable. I am trying to control it with my Echo Dot. The bridge is upstairs. I have to go upstairs and physically touch the Hue Bridge/Hub to get the dot to reconnect. The app on my iPhone 6+ does not stay connected either. Given the price, and the hype, this product falls far short of its potential.\nI will revisit this review after I get it working. Fortunately I am somewhat technically savvy, so it should help. But spending hours combing the forum as and help sites on a product, in order to get it to work in a stable condition is flat out ridiculous.\nAn hour later and it does work, but re-establing connection with the Hue app appears to be slow. The Alexa Dot can't find it at all unless I physically touch the bridge."}
{"Author": "Greg Kudasz", "Date": "on October 21, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bad Android App + Bad Support", "Text": "I really wanted this to work as I picked it up with the Dot promotion. Caveat Emptor but not the way I'd usually do it. I wonder how many of the positive reviews are for iOS products being the Android app is horrible. The first generation app (gen 1 in the Play store) has 3.6 stars but I also like to look at the ration which is 2400 5 stars and 1040 one stars. I want to setup a scene but when I press the + button it wants to do a color recipe which also apparently doesn't do anything. The gen 2 ratings are 2.6 with 532 5 stars and 1100 one star. A trivial note is on their FAQ page they don't capitalize \"Windows\" but it looks to me now that it was a sign of the trip down the drain later. The big thing though with gen 2 is that IT WON'T WORK WITH TABLETS 9\" OR GREATER. Phillips is a $24B company with 105,000 employees. They are charging $45 for light bulbs yet they can't get it to work with a tablet. I contacted their tech support to complain and I was a bit miffed when I did. After a bit of sarcasm on my part they told me to come back when I had USEFUL suggestions. Nice way to take it personally. Finally I have one bulb that hasn't started to work yet. I'll troubleshoot. Might be my problem. I'm 90% everything that I bought for it will be going back. I don't know how long Android support has been available but all the paperwork that was in the boxes said Apple products were needed to get it to work. I got it to \"work\" but I'm wondering if Android programming needs to come up or if it was rushed to market. Regardless there's no excuse for a bad app and smart talking support techs."}
{"Author": "Justin", "Date": "on October 20, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "Great product but one light keeps disconnecting from the base"}
{"Author": "G.K.", "Date": "on October 20, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Wireless Bridge not really wireless - misleading description (EDIT: Bridge stopped working)", "Text": "EDIT (July 12, 2017): I have to lower my rating from 4 star to 1 star, because the bridge stopped working all of sudden last weekend. I plugged it in different outlet, but it didn't turn on. I contacted the customer service through their website and haven't received any response in more than two days. I called Philips Customer Support yesterday and they want me to send the defective bridge first and then only they will ship the new bridge and the customer support was unable to confirm that I will receive a new bridge not a refurbished one. I find this to be a bad policy, where customer is stuck with bad product and replacement won't be send to me, before the defective product is sent back. Plus a bridge shouldn't go bad within 8 months of purchase - speaks volume to their quality assurance. To make matters worst, all of Hue bulbs are dumb bulbs now, it is beyond me that even though they are recognized by my Echo Dot, why can't Philips program them to follow routines set by Hue Bridge. I feel stuck right now and in future will plan to switch to a bridge-less configuration for my smart light needs.\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nI have been using Philips Hue kit for couple of days now and the initial set-up was somewhat of a pain. Mainly because the instructions regarding how to pair bridge with the Hue App are sparse in their packaging and the fact that they label their hub as \"wireless bridge\", I assume that means you don't need to connect to your internet router via ethernet cable. However, in my case it didn't work and it only paired with the app, when I connected using ethernet cable, which is disappointing as I have limited ethernet outlets on my router and it creates more mess on my desk.\n\nOther than this issue, everything else works as described. And I am happy with this purchase."}
{"Author": "Brandon", "Date": "on October 20, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Was great but then they got greedy and dropped support", "Text": "I like Hue but Phillips' new firmware upgrade broke support for all of my other bulbs. My Hue bulbs are nice but every light doesn't need to be their brand, it uses a standard called ZigBee. My other bulbs worked great until they got greedy and purposely broke support for other bulbs. Unless you want every bulb to be $60, you're screwed."}
{"Author": "Jeffrey", "Date": "on October 20, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't buy these it will reck your life", "Text": "Yeah I bought these and now I have two rooms filled with color lights. Now I want to do the rest of the house. These are like Pringles"}
{"Author": "arrowspace", "Date": "on October 19, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "quirky. multiple bulb failures. Poor tech support.", "Text": "I bought a bunch of them. 3 have failed. I am switching to some other, untried brand.\nThe failed bulbs started going haywire before they failed. They would switch off as the others in the fixture switched on.\nThen they just died altogether and don't work even in a single bulb lamp. Dead, Jim.\nPhillips was no help. I should reduce to 1 star, but 10 are still working.\nI would say the failures occurred after only a few weeks."}
{"Author": "Fred Berful", "Date": "on October 19, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Intermittment (daily) connection issues mean this does not work as advertised", "Text": "WARNING: If you have a Cisco router you may have difficulties using the Hue lighting system.\n\nUPDATE: After many hours of frustration and trying different things suggested by Hue support, they finally told me that their system does not work well with Cisco routers (mine was a Cisco from Xfinity) and suggested I replace with a Netgear router. I did this and now the Hue Bridge and lights seem to be working without issue including through HomeKit. Happy to get things working, but they really should tell you up front their product does not work with some hardware. I spent way too much time trying to get things to work and too much frustration when I would go into app to change lights and would not have a connection. I'm leaving rating at 2 stars, but I imagine if I had a Netgear to start with and not had these issues it would have been 4 or 5 stars.\n\nORIGINAL POST:\nI installed this a couple of weeks ago after witching from TCP lighting (they quit supporting their product).\n\nDay 1 was complete frustration. Getting the bridge to connect was brutal. It set up initially, but then was constantly cycling between being connected and not connected. This was occurring while I was trying to get my lights set up which was extremely frustrating. I did manage to get all lights working and programmed (I was leaving town next day and wanted these running while I was gone), but with a lot a patience since it would \"connect\" then I'd start doing something, it would then lose connection and re-establish connection. I would lose whatever routine I was in the process of setting up and have to start over. If I had not been leaving town next day, I probably would have just quit.\n\nThe interesting thing on the connection issue is in the app it would sometimes be connected within the network (green \"connected\"), so I could use iOS HomeKit. Sometimes it would connect \"out of home connection\" even though I was in home and on same network , so I would have to use the Hue app. And sometimes it would just not be connected even though all lights on the bridge were on and not flashing (note sometimes the third light for internet will be flashing). Anyway I left town and checked remotely and it seems the lights were coming on as programmed.\n\nAfter returning home the connection issue has been more intermittent (vs. constant before I left), but still occurs daily. Any given day I will go into HomeKit and sometimes have access, sometimes not even though I am home and on same network as the bridge. Then I have to go to the Hue app. And sometimes the bridge is just not available regardless of which app I am trying to use. Really unhappy when that is the case. Also, when home I want to use HomeKit. I like the idea my family does not need to install the app on their phones and can use HomeKit, but that is often not the case.\n\nI love the home automation. I had a TCP system before and never had a problem, but switched when that company quit supporting the product. I went with Hue based on decent ratings and HomeKit compatibility. I want to give this a better rating, but the daily intermittent connection issues are killing me. For the money I paid I need to be able to access lights to turn on or change settings whenever I go into the app. All too often this just is not the case."}
{"Author": "Well written detective and magic series", "Date": "on October 18, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best way to upgrade the house in an", "Text": "These light bulbs will change your life. Best way to upgrade the house in an afternoon"}
{"Author": "antonio t. ruiz", "Date": "on October 18, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "A++++"}
{"Author": "Josie or Frederick Coury", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't Last Long!.", "Text": "Purchased 4 Phillips Hue bulbs and they no longer work with Alexa. When I ask for them to turn on, the bulbs shut off or dim, At any given time, only 1 bulb responds. None of the bulbs respond to wifi. The room that the bulbs are in does not get used a lot. On average, bulbs may be on no more than 30-45 minutes, at any given time."}
{"Author": "Tirey", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "You light up my life....", "Text": "These things are cool. They are working exactly as advertised!"}
{"Author": "T. B. Shafir", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Siri - how many commands does it take to change a light bulb?", "Text": "Love it. This took minimal education - setup is organic with a failsafe serial number option easily found. I love the Siri integration. I started out with 4 white bulbs and replaced 2 in one light fixture. I gave a separate name to each and can turn each bulb on at a time or both. I can operate only 1 ceiling fixture in the kitchen now wheras before, both fixtures were connected to 1 switch and sometimes too bright. Now I can dim the one over the table and keep the one over the stove bright for cooking. I find a single white bulb gives adequate brightness when turned to 100% so I replaced 4 bulbs in the kitchen ceiling fixtures with 2 Hue bulbs.\nI just sprung for a color bulb - I've added a couple of scenes. I can see that I have to play a bit more with it to get the mood lighting down - more fun than necessity (of course, I've passed the age where I'm inviting a date up for a sound and light show but I can see the advantages!).\nNow I can get into bed without tripping through the living room or using my phone for a flashlight and turn the lights off upon safely reaching my destination. Or I can set them to go off at a certain time and not think about it. And I'm really looking forward to trying out the home away option. So much better than the old timers.\nI'm thoroughly satisfied and having fun as well.\nDefinitely on the Christmas giving list."}
{"Author": "Susan M. Wilson", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Totally useless product", "Text": "I'm going to return this. I cannot use it via wifi from any other location than my home (as in useless). I called Philips and they wanted to know my Internet provider and my router information. The representative told me they typically don't solve these issues in a very timely manner. That was about 5 weeks ago, so this thing is going back. Philips needs to include - if not a disclaimer then - a list of the Internet providers and routers they support. Useless. Useless."}
{"Author": "Chris", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "An indispensable home automation system with only minor flaws.", "Text": "I've been using the Philips Hue system for a month now, and I couldn't go back to home life without it. I have rooms set to a schedule to light the house at about the same time that I'm stepping out of the shower on days that I work, and I turn off the house lights with a voice command (thanks to my Amazon Echo) as I leave.\n\nMy only real complaint is that the location features don't work too well. I initially had it set up to automatically turn on the bulbs when I got close to home, but it would trigger that constantly while I was home, even when I had the trigger radius set to a quarter of a mile away from my house - even though the trigger to turn off the bulbs, at the same distance, worked properly. I decided to simply not use the location features.\n\nAs a minor complaint, the app could use a little bit of work. If the app was already launched and running in the background, it never seems to recognize the Hue bridge when I connect at home. I always have to exit the app and launch it again. Also, scheduled routines cannot be edited while away from the home network. Any edits I make while I'm away will fail to save until I try again at home."}
{"Author": "Raquel", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "very good"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 17, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dimmable Yellow Light. Not a Yellow to White light for study.", "Text": "Honestly this is great. It wasn't really clear to me on the advertising if the light are Yellow to White and Dim but after testing I now see they are a yellowish light that dims which was exactly what I am after. People who want to study this is probably not the light for you. For lounge rooms, hall ways, stair cases this is perfect."}
{"Author": "S. Fite", "Date": "on October 16, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works like a charm with ECHO", "Text": "Connected through ECHO and loving the convenience. Plugged it in and told ECHO to search for devices. After a pause, ECHO said \"If this is a Phillips Hue you must press the blue button.\" Wow. You can dim it to any percentage and control each bulb individually. I went into the ECHO app and grouped named it \"LIGHTS\" with light1 and light2. Make sure you use a name that ECHO hears clearly. I originally name the group \"Wall Lights\" and was often misunderstood. The bulbs are soft-white which give a nice warm yellowish light to a room. I bought this as a frill to play around with and it has turned out to be anything but frivolous. It is really convenient. I had to hide the switch (which must always be turned on) because I kept going on autopilot and turning the lights off. Put the app on my Fire HDX tablet which worked in seconds but that was a frill. It's really expensive but with the bridge you have a lot of flexibility for the future. Like to do my ceiling lights but I get vertigo on the first step of a ladder and my ceilings are high. Maybe next year."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 15, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "really wanted to like this product", "Text": "I really, really wanted to like this product. A friend recommended it to me to help me wake up in the mornings, and so I ordered the product. I followed the very limited directions, and the bridge showed that it was connected to the wifi (all three lights illuminated). However, I could not connect to the bridge from my smart device. I tried the Hue App, HomeKit, and a couple of other apps. I tried on several smart devices. I manually input the Bridge's IP Address. I reset the bridge, reset my router, reset my smart device. Nothing. Believing the bridge was defective, I returned it. I bought a second starter kit at Best Buy, and had the same problem. I tried the same troubleshooting I contacted Philips Hue Customer Care--went through all of their suggestions.\n\nI spent HOURS trying to get this to connect to my smart device. The Hub's ID number showed up in the Gen 1 app, so clearly it was creating some signal, but I never was able to connect to the bridge. My boyfriend, a radio frequency engineer with 16 years in wireless, could not get it to work. He logged into the router, tried to access the bridge using command prompt, NOTHING worked. Philips Hue finally just told me I must have received a defective device.\n\nSo, as I see it, one of two things has happened here, and either would make this product deserving of a one star review. The first is that Philips has produced so many defective Hubs that I was able to purchase two devices from two different retailers and managed to get a defective product both times. The second, and more likely, issue is that the bridge was not compatible with my router. This is problematic because Philips does not specify in the product's poor excuse for a manual, on its website, or anywhere as far as I know, any router or network requirements to use this product. Their customer care could not tell me whether this was a problem with the router--they believed it to be a defective product. Without any information available as to what I would need to look for in a new router, or whether that is actually the issue, I cannot justify spending another $70 on a new router and resetting my network in hopes that it MAY solve the problem. I am very disappointed in this product."}
{"Author": "John", "Date": "on October 15, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Returned it.. I couldn't get it to connect to Wifi"}
{"Author": "Natasha G", "Date": "on October 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to set-up, amazing to use smart lighting", "Text": "I remember back in the day before I had the Philips Hue lights (yesterday) and I would lay in bed half asleep wishing there was magic in the world so I wouldn't have to get up and turn off the lights (yes, lazy, I know). These lights are the next best thing and probably better in some ways. Once the package arrived, I was up and running in less than ten minutes. The bridge connects directly to the router and is little enough that it didn't make my already very full entertainment center look any more crowded. The app was a quick download and easily found the lights right away and was very intuitive - I didn't need directions to figure out anything beyond the initial set-up. I did need to search for the Hue Ambiance I ordered separately, but once I found my way around the app, that was really simple too. You can dim the lights directly from the app home screen and after you create a log-in account, you can control the lights even when you aren't home. I haven't had any issues yet with the router in the basement not reaching the upstairs or outside light, so the range has been fine. I'm still trying to work out the coming home and leaving feature that is based on GPS, but I'm hoping this will be a breeze once I have more time to play with it."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 12, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works.", "Text": "So far so good. Easy hookup just need to get more to make this work and my wife keeps turning off the light switches so then it stops working on that ligh."}
{"Author": "Doc T", "Date": "on October 11, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love them. I have 5 now", "Text": "I love them. I have 5 now, all in my bedroom. They wake me up when I want them to, and they dim easily at night, allowing me to get ready to fall asleep. I'm a big fan."}
{"Author": "Oliver Walton", "Date": "on October 11, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "Very flaky and does not work well. I would not get this again."}
{"Author": "Ramon W.", "Date": "on October 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love it"}
{"Author": "Tech Kid", "Date": "on October 10, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I just spent 1 1/2 hours talking to the Philips ...", "Text": "I just spent 1 1/2 hours talking to the Philips hue technical support but still Philips hue won't connect to siri apps. Feeling frustrated nothing happen with technical support talking and exhausting all possibilities. Then place men a waiting list to a product manager to contact me, which by the way the tech support stated \" I don't know when\". I don't normally write reviews but just feeling frustrated with this product."}
{"Author": "Brian C. McCauley", "Date": "on October 9, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I would not recommend this to my worst enemy", "Text": "It doesn't work. I would not recommend this to my worst enemy. If I could give it a zero I would.\nThis was my review two months ago. It actually gets worse.\nWEMO switches are awesome. LIFX bulbs are awesome. In the event you have a power failure or need to reboot your router they bounce back like champs. Philips Hue however needs two days of tweeks to get it back to barely working. I will never buy another Philips product again. \ud83d\udca9"}
{"Author": "Don U in Big Sky Country", "Date": "on October 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I am loving my Hue lighting.", "Text": "I am loving my Hue lighting.\n\nSo I had a new house built. It is \"smart home\" ready, and I've jumped in and started taking advantage of that.\n\nI started with the Starter Kit, of course, and purchased more than the two starter bulbs. The Hue APP works OK, but I really found best results when I linked the Hue Bridge/Hub to my Amazon Echo and was able to control lighting with voice commands.\n\nThen ... I sort of when bonkers and Hue'ed up the entire house. Again using Echo, I was able to create entire scenes and scenarios. For example, I have a set up for my \"Morning Lights\" that turns on every light I need for my regular morning routine. Another command turns on the hallway, garage, and yard light for taking out the dog.\n\nUsing two other aftermarket apps -- Hue Pro, and IFTTT -- I can now do all kinds of specialty tricks with my Hue lights.\n\nTurn on specific lamps at sunset? No problem.\n\nWant your driveway lights to come on as you enter a specific geographic circle? Easy!\n\nFor me, Hue lights are a WIN - WIN situation. The initial cost will be more than returned in energy savings. The \"cool\" factor and convenience are just icing on the cake."}
{"Author": "Kim", "Date": "on October 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love this lighting system!", "Text": "I've been curious about the Hue system since it first came out. I bought the white starter kit to try it out and see if I liked it. Took about 15 minutes to set up and 10 mins of that was user error! Super easy and more useful than I anticipated. I have mine set to come on when I pull into my driveway. Love them and look forward to integrating more lighting and more rooms."}
{"Author": "Stuart Levine", "Date": "on October 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Perfect lighting solution", "Text": "Easy setup, just works!"}
{"Author": "El Jefe", "Date": "on October 7, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Seems like a great system", "Text": "Seems like a great system, but sadly they do not make a bulb to fit MR16 bulb recessed light systems, which are very common."}
{"Author": "rs_amz", "Date": "on October 7, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There is an issue with the hue hub that I ...", "Text": "There is an issue with the hue hub that I got. it is unable to keep the brightness to the setting that I program it to. All other program settings stick except the brightness. I contacted Philips and they even opened a case # but never got back to me. Disapointed!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on October 6, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very cool product. Works great."}
{"Author": "vegrider", "Date": "on October 6, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Connection problems", "Text": "Constantly looses the connection with my Echo."}
{"Author": "The One", "Date": "on October 6, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I received my order yesterday and I love it. The only issue is one of the ...", "Text": "I received my order yesterday and I love it. The only issue is one of the lights do not work. it says unreachable. However because I ordered extra lights the others work fine through the house. its just that one light. How do I get that one light replaced without having to get the whole order replaced as Amazon keeps trying to do :( ? I just need 1 light!! Other than that Alexa loves Hue.. and all my locations throughout my house.. that's why I gave it the 5 stars even with the 1 light malfunction."}
{"Author": "Hung Chi Lin", "Date": "on October 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "just loved it as what i was expected"}
{"Author": "castro", "Date": "on October 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "exactly what I was looking for", "Text": "A must have as a sidekick for your Amazon Echo\nIt is easy to setup and control from your smartphone or Echo"}
{"Author": "Ashwin S", "Date": "on October 3, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy setup, decent brightness and easy to control with the app", "Text": "Easy to setup, and easy to use with the default app but have had a little connectivity issues at times. It's been great to use with the IFTTT app. However one of the bulbs has stopped functioning in less than a month. I am not able to turn it on even manually; I need to check out how to go about with this :("}
{"Author": "Rachelle R.", "Date": "on October 3, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bought Phillips Hue to use with my new BEDDI smart alarm clock", "Text": "Bought Phillips Hue to use with my new BEDDI smart alarm clock. Once I got use to the app and how to use the Hue lights, I loved it!!"}
{"Author": "k johnson", "Date": "on October 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great item"}
{"Author": "kevin Steinike", "Date": "on October 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Live in the future, buy these lights!", "Text": "I bought this kit from a local box store, just to see what the big hubbub was about. Turns out, I like having lights turn on and off for me without having to reach for the switch. These lights can be as useful as you are willing to set up.\n\nMy favorite features are:\n\nI have them set in my living room to turn on to full brightness once I arrive home\n\nI have them set to dim to night light after 10, usually when I head to bed\n\nI can tell siri to turn them on or off\n\nI can manually dim them through the app if I want to put a movie on\n\nI was so blown away with how easy to use and how useful they are that I went right back to the store and bought another pair of bulbs for my bedroom. The bridge plugs right into your router or switch and downloading the app is easy-peasy. My only annoyance is whenever I want to rename or set something up, I have to go into the hue app and re-authorize Siri to access the light with its new name, but I don't foresee that happening very often.\n\nThis whole smart light thing might be nothing but a novelty, but I'm sold, I just wish the colored bulbs weren't so expensive"}
{"Author": "Daniel Paiva", "Date": "on September 30, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "First step for a fully automated home!", "Text": "I love this! Works perfectly with Homekit on my iphone and Apple Watch. Sometimes, when I ask Siri to act on the lights, somehow she doesn't \"hear back from the lights\". So I go to the Hue Widget and manually turn the lights ON/OFF and it works instantly. Looking forward to buy the color bulbs!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent Product", "Text": "This was a GREAT addition to Alexa. Setup 4 lamps around downstairs and now have them on a scheduled time to turn on/off. In addition, I can say at anytime, \"Alexa, turn on/off lamps\" - and boom, it's done. Plan on replacing other bulbs around the house as they go out. On a side note, I also am very happy with the color of light - it's not that weird super white that you can accidentally get with some LEDs"}
{"Author": "Angievel", "Date": "on September 29, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Waste of time and money", "Text": "Waste of time and effort. The amount of time I lose waiting for the hue bridge to connect so that I can simply turn my bedroom lamp off is frustratingly not worth the investment.\nI don't think there has been one instance in which the light operated as expected. I spend most of my hue experience time touching the on/off button repeatedly to try to trigger the dam bridge to wake up and work, which eventually does the trick but defeats the purpose. On top of that, the bulbs gets hot like incandescent bulbs but claim to be LED so I'm not sure they're even using LED-expected power which means they won't even save on the electric bill. $57 for a \"LED\" bulb that works when it wants to work and doesn't when it doesn't want to work? No thank you. And now I'm stuck with them."}
{"Author": "C. Moss", "Date": "on September 28, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Has lots of Potential", "Text": "Easy set up. Everything works as described and designed. No issues with bulbs or connectivity. The Software (Version 2) and overall capabilities are disappointing and limited. Paying for 3rd party software, that may or may not be better, is insulting. This is not a mature product offering yet and I believe we will all be Beta Testers for at least 2-4 more years. The potential is there. I would like to see improved software controls and more features for home security rather than all this \"mood\" lighting nonsense. Come on Phillips,its 2016, not 1989. The software (and hardware) should be more robust and versatile at this price point. (Why are the software controls on the My Hue website not the same as the Phone app?? Am I missing something?) And build and offer a decent handheld remote - because smart phones are so reliable as a controller - NOT."}
{"Author": "Amara H", "Date": "on September 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "changed my life", "Text": "I LOVE THESE LIGHT BULBS. I use them in conjunction with the Amazon Echo\u2014you can easily turn lights on and off, and adjust brightness by voice command or with the app.\n\nI just wish there were more types of bulbs (the only ones with special bases seem to be the color-changing ones, at $50 apiece list price) for a wider range of lamps, etc. I did end up replacing a couple of the lamps/light fixtures in my house to be able to slot these in. Still, totally worth it for the convenience."}
{"Author": "S. Sharpe", "Date": "on September 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it!", "Text": "Love this! It works well with Siri for iPhone users and the Echo for the diehard Amazon fans. It's great. I haven't touched a light switch in months. Easy set up."}
{"Author": "Sharon", "Date": "on September 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 26, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Thought it was a great idea, except the lights will randomly turn on ...", "Text": "Got these to use in our kid's bedroom since we are in an apartment. Thought it was a great idea, except the lights will randomly turn on to full bright for no apparent reason when they are dimmed down. Doesn't happen if they are turned off, only when dimmed."}
{"Author": "atmj", "Date": "on September 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice idea, great customer service if there is an issue with a bulb like I had", "Text": "SETUP\nSeemed simple enough. Connect hub to your router (hard wired, had hope it was WiFi), and make sure it has power and put two light bulbs in an area you want to use them. Load the app on your phone and follow the directions.\nIt was simple and it was easy.\n\nWHY, I WANTED THIS\nI\u2019ve lived in this house 23 years. There has never been a way to turn the foyer lights on from the garage in all that time. Electrically it would cost more than you might think due to the amount of wires in that area and switches. Instead $60 later I have a more flexible solution.\n\nMy phone can turn the foyer wall light on, if I\u2019ve realized I forgot to leave it on, right from my car, as my phone will connect with the wireless from the driveway. Similarly I can turn a kitchen light on as well. Neither of these needed any special color, so the plain white Hue bulbs worked fine.\n\nTO ADDRESS NOT NEEDING TO USE A SMART PHONE, PAIR IT WITH A LOGITEC POP.\nWhat prompted me to finally go with this solution, is that I could eliminate the use of the smart phone with a simple little electronic switch. Inside my garage is a Logitech POP and if I tap this once, it turns on the foyer light, twice the kitchen light and a long press turns on both.\nThis seems like a lot of technology to do such a simple thing, but the wiring to do this would be formidable. This is one of the few lightly solutions that work with the POP and this is why I bought the Phillips Hue.\n\nAMAZON ECHO:\nYes, now I can talk to my lights and tell the Echo to turn them on or off. I had not thought of this till I saw it on the box. Handy.\n\nWORKS WITH APPLE AND ANDROID:\nI was very disconcerted when I saw the box as it gave the illusion that it only worked with Apple devices. While I have an ipad, I have an Android phone. I\u2019m happy to report that it works with both and the info was included.\n\nISSUES:\nOne of my Phillips lights never turns fully off though the app says it\u2019s off. I have an email into customer service at Phillips to see if there is any recourse to fix this. I will let you know how that turns out. So far I have waited a week. There is a do not reply on their reply to me, so I can\u2019t quickly ping them, but would have to get back to them via the web site. Hence the 3 stars. Would be 5 if it worked or Phillips responded in 24-48 hours.\n\nUPDATE ON ISSUES:\nPhillips came through for me. Shortly after I posted this review, a rep contacted me and sent me a label to mail back the bulb in question. I have the new one and it works great.\n\nFor years I dealt with a difficult lighting situation in my foyer and this solution works great for me. Paired with Amazon's Echo. I tell the light to turn on before I leave and using the Logitech Pop switch in the garage I turn it off. I could also use my phone."}
{"Author": "Hemimagrt", "Date": "on September 25, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The ease of setup for this kit is second to ...", "Text": "The ease of setup for this kit is second to none. Now I've bought almost $600 worth of bulbs and still going lol."}
{"Author": "Bmurphy1", "Date": "on September 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Too say the least durable. I use this hook ...", "Text": "Too say the least durable. I use this hook to tow @murderblazer on IG up and down the street."}
{"Author": "tierney", "Date": "on September 22, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great", "Text": "My furry family member loves it when I'm not home to turn that light on."}
{"Author": "ReadMoreOrDie", "Date": "on September 22, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Update changes the way you discover new bulbs.", "Text": "New update from Phillips. To discover your new bulbs, don't press the button on the bridge. Go to the Phillips Hue app and go to light setup, then press the + button and then search."}
{"Author": "Steve B", "Date": "on September 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Using it with Amazon Echo. My all house lighting is now controlled by voice."}
{"Author": "Christina E. Blanco", "Date": "on September 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Women, looking for a gift for your tech-man?", "Text": "This is you solution for a unique gift for the man who you don't know who to buy for. The one who loves his iPad? He can control the lights from his iPad. Omg, he will love it. He can use mood lighting. It's like a toy for your man. Best gift I've gotten him and you can buy more things to expand it for future gifts. This is a must!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 20, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Bridge requires ethernet cable connection!", "Text": "I was surprised to find I had to have the bridge in proximity to my wifi router as it must be cable (not wifi) connected to your home network - real hassle in my case. The location (finally) worked ok but I'm not sure I'd have gone this way if I'd known in advance."}
{"Author": "Tony Boersma", "Date": "on September 19, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome lights, awesome app.", "Text": "We got thisand I had it set up and running in the time it took the wife to go pick up a pizza. She got back and halfway through dinner I started toggling lights and scared the hell out of her. The kids loved it."}
{"Author": "Robert55", "Date": "on September 18, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This works fine for a start in home automation", "Text": "This works fine for a start in home automation. I can now turn off lights that my wife leaves on without jumping up and going over to the light switch. However, the Android app does not work with my Android tablet but does have one for my Fire tablet."}
{"Author": "Simon S.", "Date": "on September 18, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These bulbs are super addicting. I started off with 2", "Text": "These bulbs are super addicting. I started off with 2, and now my whole home has them. Telling Alexa or Siri to turn the lights off has saved me so much time when leaving.\n\nEven more interesting is the dimming feature, if I feel like watching a movie, I just tell Siri (after scene creation) to enable movie time! The uses are endless, and they save you money and last a good long while.They are rated for damp locations, so the bathroom would be no problem, if you want to pair them with a motion sensor for night time.\n\nLastly, they are plenty bright at 800 lumens. They are only a warm white, but you can buy ambience bulbs now for not much more that allow the color temp to change so do keep that in mind."}
{"Author": "Bleed Green", "Date": "on September 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great with Echo! Love them!!"}
{"Author": "Michael Vezza", "Date": "on September 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to set-up, easy to love.", "Text": "Very easy to set up - plug in the power cord, plug in to your router, install the app - done. You just have to link your phone to the Hue bridge and you're good to go from there.\n\nCreating an account is worth the extra step as you can then control the lights away from home (to see if they've been left on inadvertantly.)"}
{"Author": "Dan", "Date": "on September 17, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "received the item today, already spent over an hour ...", "Text": "received the item today, already spent over an hour trying to trouble shoot the bridge. it will not connect to my router and cannot be found on the app. Tried to factory reset and that was no use. Hopefully the seller can send a working replacement. Will revise my review after assistance."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 16, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "like white led light", "Text": "I thought it was, indeed, white light... like white led light, but is more of a yellowish light."}
{"Author": "Sid", "Date": "on September 16, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome product!", "Text": "Works just as expected and integrates well with Siri. Awesome product!"}
{"Author": "Garrett", "Date": "on September 16, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Could not make the app (IOS) talk to the bridge ...", "Text": "Could not make the app (IOS) talk to the bridge no matter what I tried. Tech support was not able to help. I went so far as to open my router to see if I could determine the IP address. Although the bridge showed it was connected, I couldn't find the device on the router's active device page. Router is Fios Quantum Gateway."}
{"Author": "G. Brown", "Date": "on September 16, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Lamps themselves are great. The app is a disaster (old and new ...", "Text": "Lamps themselves are great. The app is a disaster (old and new one). Was able to transfer my alarms etc. over but of course I cannot find a way to edit them in the new app. So they exist but cannot be managed??? There has to be an easier way to manage lights via an app. Great product but in order to manage the lights it is way too time consuming. Maybe they will get it right in the third app?"}
{"Author": "Nick", "Date": "on September 16, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "As Advertised!", "Text": "Amazing Lighting System! Easy to setup and use!"}
{"Author": "William Sullivan", "Date": "on September 15, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worthless. Has to be hard wired to the cable ...", "Text": "Worthless. Has to be hard wired to the cable modem and is unable to connect with the lights in any other room unless you have Ethernet throughout you house."}
{"Author": "W K F", "Date": "on September 15, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "fun but maybe not necessary", "Text": "It's a fun device, though I'm having trouble refraining from turning off the bulbs by hand. Perhaps it's a force of habit, but I find it cumbersome to go to my phone to turn the lights off. It is pretty cool, though, to turn the lights on from the car as I drive up to my apartment.\n\nI have had the problem of Siri not \"hearing back\" from the Hue base. I thought it was the base, but it turns out my phone hadn't connected to the wifi at home. I've been cursing the base at time, and it was actually my fault for not remembering to turn my phone's wifi back on.\n\nNot a bad device \u2013 it does everything it says it does \u2013 but just not a convenience that I'm finding all that convenient."}
{"Author": "born too late", "Date": "on September 14, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very versatile!", "Text": "I'm really quite pleased with how these work. I have mostly been using the bulbs with the Hue app and not so much with the Echo, although I do have one and like it. I will allow others with more experience to review the Alexa/Hue experience. I like using the app because I can precisely control both the brightness and the level of whiteness. I like these so much I went out and got a color hue bulb for a bedside lamp. The app allows me to separately adjust each light to get exactly the mood I want in the room. So in the morning I can have bright white light while I'm getting ready for work, and in the evening I can keep it soft, then turn off the room light altogether and adjust the bedside lamp to a soft blue-ish with just enough brightness for reading. It may be a fluke, but I have been sleeping better since I started doing this.\n\nBut even the white bulbs allow a range of adjustments, so you can have a bright white, or a soft yellowish. And the app allows you to set \"scenes\" using combinations from the various lights in the room. And one very cool thing I discovered is the ability to use a photo on my phone to set my own color scheme, thus I can enjoy the dimming glow from a Colorado sunset complete with rose undertones.\n\nAlso, you can purchase a 'switch plate' that requires no wiring. It is magnetized, and can be stuck to an old switch plate. It holds very well and is synced with the room lights, so you can still manually turn on room lights and control the brightness.\n\nOne note, the bridge must be hooked into your wireless modem, and it involves tapping the top button. If, as it is in my case, your modem is on a different floor, that means you must get the bulbs up and running, so to speak, while in the same room with the bridge. I solved this problem using a nearby lamp until the bulbs and my wifi had discovered each other. Then I moved the bulbs to the room I wanted them in."}
{"Author": "LinckG", "Date": "on September 13, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Works well. Integrates with Alexa, Harmony and IFTTT. Wish it came with a different temperature color."}
{"Author": "Jp", "Date": "on September 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great kit, works very well."}
{"Author": "Cristin H", "Date": "on September 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Live like Bill Gates for under $100!", "Text": "We purchased this to work through the Alexa app on our Amazon Echo device. It is super addicting! Started out with 2 bulbs and now at 5 with no plans to slow down. Very easy to setup hub to router, download philip hue app and then add to our Alexa devices. I named each lightbulb and created groups as well so i could control better. I LOVE the voice command feature with this through Alexa. I also went to IFTTT.COM to create light recipes such as, \"If i unlock door then turn on bar light.\" When i unlock my door the bar light at end of bar turns on automatically so if house dark when I arrive I feel safer!\n\nYou can make brighter, dim to a certain percentage, turn on single lights or full groups, etc. It is so great to take advantage of technology previously only available to the very wealthy. Awesome!!"}
{"Author": "JHI", "Date": "on September 11, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great, but would like brighter option.", "Text": "I love my hue lights, but I wish you could make them brighter. Otherwise, everything else about them is great."}
{"Author": "One Black Man", "Date": "on September 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great", "Text": "Bulbs are really bright and setup was awesome. Use this in Nigeria with 220V (bulb is rated 110V or so.\nControls work fine from the hue app. Yet to connect my Echo but I'm sure it'll work flawlessly."}
{"Author": "Scott Giesecke", "Date": "on September 10, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product used with Alexa Step one in our smart ...", "Text": "Great product used with Alexa Step one in our smart home setup. Only gripe is that sometimes Alexa can't find the devices and you need to repeat yourself a few times until connectivity is reestablished."}
{"Author": "Tracy S.", "Date": "on September 10, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One of the two bulbs works brilliantly with the app", "Text": "One of the two bulbs works brilliantly with the app. The other one doesn't come on until I turn off lights. Then it dims. Odd."}
{"Author": "Letsbefrank", "Date": "on September 9, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice idea but poor execution and expensive", "Text": "Bought this system for security. Bridge setup, simple, even updated itself. but..... The Hue app is very poor. The failure of Philips Hue to provide an online manual and adequate online support. (which is frankly useless) left me deeply dissatisfied with this product. I have used timers for years. When I go on vacation I can set them to turn on and and off and not worry about the simple function. . The Hue not only fails to give me simple options but sometimes doesn't opreate in reliable manner. 15 dollars for a sixty watt bulb with limited use is exensive but not as expensive as the other bulbs Phillips offers which are between $45 to $60 a piece. Much of what Hue attempts to do is to provide different colored lighting atmosphere for different occasion such a house party. Since the focus is on this option there appears to be little thought for security setups. Yes.it can be setup but it is a pain. Tried other Hue apps but did find any that was much better then Hue.. Very dissatified but will keep trying to live with the system"}
{"Author": "Berko", "Date": "on September 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome, but with a word of warning.", "Text": "I needed the new Bridge, and can always use another set of bulbs, so I went with the starter kit, even though I already had the first Hue Bridge. Setting up was easy, but a word of warning:\n\nPhilips gave me the run around trying to get the lights to stop turning on and off on their own, and losing their sync with devices like my dimming switch. I tried just about everything, and Philips was absolutely great in providing easy to follow instructions. However, in the end I did a factory reset and that worked instantly. I would recommend anyone buying this to update their bridge should do the same. Especially if you use dimming switches, the Amazon Echo, or have troubles upon setting up. Much easier, even if it seems like more work."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Control Away from Home", "Text": "Love my Hue Lights! I got these to start my home automation using Amazon Echo, I enjoy just being able to tell Alexa how to dim, turn on, or off the lights. However, the big advantage with the version 2 is the control from away. With my dog at home all day, I like that I can turn lights on and off depending on what the weather ends up being so he isn't at home in the dark but I also don't leave lights on all day if it's sunny out."}
{"Author": "The Great Pumpkin", "Date": "on September 7, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Had old Hue version - replaced with this - doesn't function", "Text": "Doesn't work"}
{"Author": "L. Bruner", "Date": "on September 6, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I'm a happy little nerd", "Text": "Oh my this satisfies the nerd in me. I've got the hub linked so that I can operate the bulb in my bedroom with my Echo \"Alexa, turn on my bedroom light.\" The other bulb is operated via the Hue app, I have it on a timer, called a routine. Makes me happy."}
{"Author": "Zephus", "Date": "on September 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great with Alexa", "Text": "Works great with Alexa, better than the WeMo switches. Light levels are consistent, the app is easy to use. Pleased with this purchase."}
{"Author": "Julie", "Date": "on September 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent Product", "Text": "Love the Philips Hue! It is easy to install and works great with the Echo!"}
{"Author": "Dmitri", "Date": "on September 3, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Good product."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 3, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Waste of money!", "Text": "I really do not like these at all. They do not have a very strong wifi signal. I bought them for the two lamps on my credenza. I get a perfectly good wifi signal in that room, but the hub cannot reach that far. It's really only about 20 feet from the hub, so it seems like a waste. Maybe I'll find another use for them, until then, they are just really expensive, yet ordinary LED bulbs."}
{"Author": "Michael Dunn", "Date": "on September 2, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Let Alexa control these babies....", "Text": "They work great with alexa.."}
{"Author": "RayC", "Date": "on September 1, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Product works fine but software is junk", "Text": "The kit works great. I set up several on/off routines and love being able to control the lights from anywhere. I got rid of 4 timers that are a pain to set up and have limited options.\n\nWhy 2 stars? The software is mediocre and I can't find any type of user manual on-line. I use the Philips Hue software and it is clumsy. I tried a couple of other Hue apps and they are better but still could be improved. For example, one app allows a 30 minute random on/off setting; so if you set the timer for 8:00 it will come on between 8:00 and 8:30. Other apps don't have a random setting, why? If you log into My Hue through a browser you get a stripped down version of the already mediocre version. My Hue doesn't display any of the routines so I have to set them up on my phone. Other than the software, the lights are great."}
{"Author": "old mojo", "Date": "on August 31, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Wish I got them sooner", "Text": "These really do work well. Very easy to set up, and works with Smart Things, and Amazon Echo"}
{"Author": "clamson95", "Date": "on August 31, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome.", "Text": "They get SUPER bright, setup is cumbersome but easy once you get used to it. Make sure you get the wireless switches."}
{"Author": "Ercolino Crugnale", "Date": "on August 31, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Frustrating Software, Even After \"Update\" 8.31.16", "Text": "I bought this set, plus added a color bulb and an a couple extra white bulbs. The challenge is programing the lights to do what you want, when you want. The website has very poor, unclear instructions. I have emailed support, and after waiting in excess of two weeks, don't ever expect a response. There is no clear way to program lights to come on at specific times, at specific degrees of power that you customize. Philips wants you to choose \"presets\" that they have determined. Part of the appeal of this system was that I believed I could program it how I needed. They recently upgraded the software, but to no avail. The buttons for navigating are not clear nor simple. This system needs an Apple like approach to make it seamless, until that happens you will be using ineffective presets. One more note, the one preset located in what Philips calls \"Wake up\", only works with the color bulbs and functions by slowing increasing the lights intensity. Sounds cool, except the white bulbs are not designed to slowly rise in intensity, however I cannot find where you can just have these lights to turn on instantly. Frustrating!"}
{"Author": "Butch Barker", "Date": "on August 31, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "works well"}
{"Author": "Donald", "Date": "on August 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love my Philips hue lights it was so easy to hook up to my echo"}
{"Author": "Jack B", "Date": "on August 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... use these as a sunrise alarm and they do great. They get pretty bright but they don't get ...", "Text": "I use these as a sunrise alarm and they do great. They get pretty bright but they don't get too dim. Sometimes when it turns on with the dimmest setting it is enough of a jump to wake you up. This may be nature of white only and could be fixed with a colored light. Installation was pretty easy and the app is nice.\n\nI use them in my overhead light in my room so if I want them on at night I need my phone, so I recommend getting the wall switch as well."}
{"Author": "Christopher A. Moreno", "Date": "on August 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for Smart Homes", "Text": "Works great and is an awesome starter kit. Got this instead of the color one due to price and tbh I will hardly ever need all those colors in most rooms of the house. Works nice with Alexa as well. We have it doing things with the Harmony hub as well as the IFTTT app as well."}
{"Author": "Jen", "Date": "on August 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love dimming the lights with the app or with Amazon ...", "Text": "Works with the Alexa Echo! Love dimming the lights with the app or with Amazon Echo."}
{"Author": "Deb Noel", "Date": "on August 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Bulbs, Fun Technology", "Text": "Nice white light color that I can control through Alexa or my Apple devices. I've since add more bulbs to the easy to set up bridge."}
{"Author": "Roman", "Date": "on August 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Work great!", "Text": "These lights do everything I hoped they would. I control one in my front porch lamp to go on and off at sunset and sunrise through a recipe in IFTTT. I control the other with my Amazon Dot with voice commands."}
{"Author": "Sony Heir", "Date": "on August 26, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The hub that comes with this kit is the second ...", "Text": "The hub that comes with this kit is the second generation one which is compatible with apple home link as well as amazon echo. The bulbs are not the greates...(wish they were brighter and more white)."}
{"Author": "ryan", "Date": "on August 26, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works just how I wanted it to."}
{"Author": "MileHighGuy", "Date": "on August 25, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Don't Bother", "Text": "Doesn't work. The bridge didn't transfer over... okay, fine. I can reset everything up. Done. Next day, couldn't find the bridge... okay, fine. I repair them, and it's good to go. Then literally the day after that, can't find the bridge, can't find the bridge or any of my lights. I'm going back to gen 1. This is ridiculous."}
{"Author": "Pablo Ruiz L", "Date": "on August 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Excelent product"}
{"Author": "pappajack", "Date": "on August 24, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works perfectly with Amazon Alexa. When you are coming ...", "Text": "Works perfectly with Amazon Alexa. When you are coming into a dark room you don't have to search for a lamp, just tell Alexa to turn it on. Couldn't be easier."}
{"Author": "Customer", "Date": "on August 23, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "decided to use smart switches instead", "Text": "Work as expected. For multiple lights on the same circuit, decided to use smart switches instead. Too costly for most uses."}
{"Author": "George", "Date": "on August 23, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great way to give your home a modern feel.", "Text": "I switched from Wemo to Phillips hue because Amazon Echo didn't recognize the Wemo bulbs. So I switched them out with the Phillips Hue and these works great!. One gripe I have is the lack of an away mode to have lights turn on and off at random to simulate someone at home. There is a home and away mode in the app but it just shuts off or turns off the selected groups of light. Another gripe I had was the lack of a motion sensor. I had my Wemo Motion Sensor in my kitchen so when I go into the kitchen the lights would turn on. Though I heard that there will be a Phillips Motion Sensor releasing this fall. I'd order that the moment I could."}
{"Author": "bing han", "Date": "on August 22, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "One bulb is defective. Doesn't work properly."}
{"Author": "Bill", "Date": "on August 21, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Ehhhhhh", "Text": "Great if you have the switch and the patience to wait for your Siri or your watch to turn the lights on. Also found out today that the bridge signal was massively disrupting my AirPort Extreme wifi strength. I unplugged my hue bridge and then all of a sudden my wifi was hauling again, plugged it back it back in and slow as a snail. Need to located hub much further away from wifi router and get a longer Ethernet chord"}
{"Author": "Linnell Lane", "Date": "on August 21, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Hue Starter Kit", "Text": "There are many ways of automating the lights in your house. However, I feel the Philips Hue hub and bulbs are an idea choice. The Philips Hue hub is easy to setup, use, and maintain. I was able to set mine up in about 10 minutes. This device is incredible. I use this device to set my Hue bulbs to come on or turn off on multiple schedules, whether I am away or at home. Configuring the Philips Hue hub and Hue bulbs can be done from anywhere as long as you have access to your WiFi network and the internet. The Hue bulbs can be configured to come on multiple times a day on different days, just on one specific day, or can be controlled manually. Gone are the days of running around the house trying to turn off the trail of lights your kid(s) have left on."}
{"Author": "Shravan Sundaram", "Date": "on August 21, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent.", "Text": "First setup towards home automation. Easy setup and works as expected. Would be nice for a lower price."}
{"Author": "Suzanne Reinhardt", "Date": "on August 20, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love this product", "Text": "Can you say Amazon Deal day! I love this product! It works great with my Alexa app! It was the second piece I bought for my home automation after I purchased my echo \"Alexa\"! Easy to install and use! No regrets!!!!! Good product!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on August 19, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love the Hue system so far for the ability to ...", "Text": "I love the Hue system so far for the ability to automate using routines and IFTTT integration. I can't wait to save up for some color bulbs."}
{"Author": "RPL", "Date": "on August 18, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Philips Hue gives Homekit lip service", "Text": "First, the hub and software only gives lip service to Homekit. While you can create a schedule, that schedule is not stored in the HomeKit database, thus, other Homekit apps, like Elgato and iDevices will not be able to see the created schedules. If you create a schedule in iDevices, or Elagato, then those schedules, whiele stored in the Homekit database, will not be picked up by the Philips Hue ecosystem. This means, that if any schedules created by iDevices or Elgato, will only execute if you are on the same Wi-Fi network as the Hue hub. If you leave home, before the schedules are meant to execute, your lights will not come on and go off as scheduled. Same thing happens with the IOS 10 Home app. Unless Philips, fixes this issue, there is no way to push a schedule to the Hub from the IOS 10 Homekit app, or any other Homekit. You are forced to use their crappy app to execute something as simple as scheduling lights on and off.\n\nAlso, the bulbs in this set are more yellow than white. I was expecting very white light and what I got was a yellowish light coming from these bulbs. They are definitely not completely white. There is a yellowish tint to them that I was not expecting. It may not bother many people, but the true color tone should be noted in the description.\n\nLastly, I'm surprised at how badly the software is written. After reading the great reviews, I was expecting something really great. If you are comparing the app to the Generation one app, then it's better. if you compare the app to something like iDevices, Elgato Eve, or even Lutron, it's badly organized. For instance, when you set a schedule that executes everyday, you need to click the symbols for every day of the week. Most apps have an \"All\" button you can just click. When I set a schedule, they assume I want it to operate on a room, instead of an individual bulb, like every other app. The app has a look like it was written in the 80s instead of the 21st century.\n\nEvery time you launch the app, it seems like it wants to re-connect to the hub all the time. When you launch the app, there is a brief green sign that comes up and says \"Connected\" every single time it's launched and slows the app down. The act of turning the lights on and off, manually and on schedule, seems to work well. But the app as whole needs work."}
{"Author": "Joemonkey", "Date": "on August 18, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great, and hooked it up to my Echo as ...", "Text": "Works great, and hooked it up to my Echo as well, it is nice to be able to control the lights in multiple different ways."}
{"Author": "TKESlinky", "Date": "on August 17, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The hue lights work really well. We can control ...", "Text": "The hue lights work really well. We can control them via several options including our phones and computers. I bought them primarily to go with our Echo. They work perfectly. Have only have them for about a month, but I don't know how we controlled our lights without the echo and these. We find them indispensable when heading to bed for the evenimg."}
{"Author": "Linda L Boron", "Date": "on August 17, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "\ud83d\ude01", "Text": "Hard to use"}
{"Author": "Brandon", "Date": "on August 16, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works seamlessly. Timers and custom widgets make this very useful"}
{"Author": "H Larkin", "Date": "on August 14, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Needs to be connected directly to your modem which isn't ...", "Text": "Needs to be connected directly to your modem which isn't convenient for us as we don't have an accessible outlet nearby."}
{"Author": "Don Kirby", "Date": "on August 12, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Convenient for hard to reach lamp"}
{"Author": "kgr132", "Date": "on August 10, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Save yourself some grief and buy another brand", "Text": "Updated Nov. 2016: Over the past 6 months the Philips Hue Bridge has been nothing but a pain in the A**. It's compatibility with 3rd party stuff is absolutely horrible. After I searched and found a workaround to get my CREE Connected bulbs to pair with it, Philips released a firmware \"update\" in September that was actually a huge downgrade. I can no longer connect additional CREE bulbs. It's apparently a known issue to the Hue team but, after two months, my bridge has yet to receive any updates that might fix it. Luckily the CREE bulbs I'd already set up weren't unpaired by the \"update\". From what I've read, this is the second time in less than a year that Philips has broken connectivity to third party bulbs with \"updates\" despite claiming to be fully Zigbee compatible. I might just throw my Hue Bridge in the trash and buy something else just to keep my blood pressure down. Save yourself some grief and buy another brand.\n\nAs a side note, just in case you're still considering it because it's cheap...the free Philips Hue app for Android is really lacking in both features and ease of use. The only reason I kept the app installed was in case there was another update the bridge firmware again. That was a huge mistake. If you get your system working, DO NOT update the firmware in your bridge. The Philips Hue team seem to go out of their way to break third party compatibility and then say \"oops, we really didn't mean to screw all of the third party hardware\""}
{"Author": "kimbolaria", "Date": "on August 10, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I like that you can set routines for the lights so ...", "Text": "I like that you can set routines for the lights so they will turn on to wake you up in the morning or turn off by a certain time if you forgot to turn them off before sleep. They can get really bright. One bulb is enough for my bedroom. I wish you could easily switch between manually switching the lights off and switching them off on the phillips hue app or by telling the amazon echo. Unfortunately, if you manually switch the lights off you cannot use the app or tell alexa to turn them on. You can buy the switch form of this instead of the light bulb which seems more cost effective in the long run since the bulbs will have to be replaced."}
{"Author": "Benjamin D Wright", "Date": "on August 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Far better than version 1."}
{"Author": "James Larken Smith", "Date": "on August 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worked Perfect!!! Buy instead of GE Link.", "Text": "I had bought a GE Link starter kit, with zero luck getting it to work. Returned it and bought the Hue starter kit, with opposite result! Easily recognised hub. Easily found bulbs. And then easily connected to the Amazon Echo. Love it!!!"}
{"Author": "Scott Lemon", "Date": "on August 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Simple remote lighting solved", "Text": "Everything hooked up and works great! I do wish I had gotten color bulbs instead of just white though."}
{"Author": "Garth13", "Date": "on August 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love this, works like a charm with Alexa!"}
{"Author": "Darion Carey", "Date": "on August 4, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "everything was great as advertised."}
{"Author": "Rich", "Date": "on August 3, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "My favorite new toy with Amazon Echo. I have had zero problems with mine, easy setup process."}
{"Author": "Val", "Date": "on August 3, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "These light bulbs are awesome and works like a charm with the echo", "Text": "These light bulbs are awesome and works like a charm with the echo. I will be buying more as they are needed. The only drawback I have seen is when electric goes out. The lights turn on when the power comes back on."}
{"Author": "Jordan Webber", "Date": "on August 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Siri, turn off the lights in the hallway.", "Text": "Upgraded from gen 1 to gen 2 mostly to get the Siri functionality. Didn't realize how handy it would be - I now use Siri a lot more. I just wish she could handle compound commands like \"turn off the lights in the kitchen and turn on the lights in the living room.\" Then it would be great!"}
{"Author": "ParrotHead Rick", "Date": "on August 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it.", "Text": "Just what I expected after reading all the reviews. Works very well with my Samsung Smart Things hub and with the Cree light bulbs I had already installed."}
{"Author": "Cody Taylor", "Date": "on August 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great smart home lighting option.", "Text": "I have been building out a smart home that up until the time of this purchase was only controlling lights through smart plugs. I was ready to venture into some of the other smart home lighting options that were capable of being controlled by Amazon Echo. I did quite a bit of research between LIFX and Hue and ultimately chose Hue. It came down to ease of use, reliability and sustainability.\n\nThese bulbs are pretty legit. Easy to setup and sync with Echo. So far, I have had 100% reliability with them working when told to (which is better than I can say for some of the smart plugs (TP-Link *cough*cough*)). I plan on growing the system from just my dining room to the kitchen soon and pretty much any ceiling fixture that isn't a fan (mostly because I am hoping some better approach to controlling the lights and fan through Amazon Echo comes out)."}
{"Author": "M", "Date": "on August 1, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Disappointing", "Text": "Fairly easy to set up and get the bulbs connected. The app and or software in general was a no go. The main reason I wanted the system was to be able to set up schedules for the lights ( off when I'm at work, on when I arrive home from work, lights on when I wake up in the morning).. It worked for maybe the first day and that was it. I tried everything but the Hue app would never keep me logged in for some reason. I even tried other apps like Tasker and the old version of the Hue app which worked for about a day then nothing. The manual functionality to turn the lights on and off worked well but I should have been able to set up my schedules and let that be it. I purchased from Best Buy and returned them after about 5 days of troubleshooting."}
{"Author": "jk", "Date": "on July 31, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Probably saved my toe once or twice", "Text": "I like how i never need to walk in dark after turning off light"}
{"Author": "Rodney A. Pruitt", "Date": "on July 31, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Automation made easy. Hands dirty or full? Use Echo to turn on/off lights.", "Text": "Don't make the mistake I did and not realize these are white bulbs only in this kit. It's ok some rooms like the kitchen only need white light though :) It's a great starter pack and with the Echo I'm loving turning on/off my lights from other rooms and with my hands dirty in the kitchen. Hands free lights at home is like the sensor on/off lights at work. You don't want your lights at home to go on/off as you walk through so this system along with the echo integration provides you the best alternative. Washing something or got your hands tied up,, echo turn on the kitchen lights and there they go. Lying in bed and forgot to turn off the lamp, echo turn off the lamp.. boom. Set up is fairly easy although it needs a wired connection for the hub which I wasn't aware of until I started to setup. Download the skill in echo, plug in the hub, allow it to see the lights and then set up your bulbs on HUE,, then go to your alexa app and you can combine bulbs together to make rooms go on/off in groups."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 30, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible product! After working with the connection for 2 ...", "Text": "Terrible product! After working with the connection for 2 hours only 1 of the 2 bulbs would connect to the internet. The instructions offered NO solutions and on line forums by 3rd party sites still did not fix the problem. Total waster of money and time. Great concept-terrible results!!"}
{"Author": "beau", "Date": "on July 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love my hue lights. They are SMART! Just wish they weren't so pricy or I had more $."}
{"Author": "Lover of Poetry", "Date": "on July 29, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "love it", "Text": "I was worried because they said it was only for the iPhone and ipod brand but I downloaded it on my android and it works awesomely"}
{"Author": "Leanne", "Date": "on July 28, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy, fun, works well.", "Text": "Works great, easy to install, and control with either the app or Alexa."}
{"Author": "NetStab", "Date": "on July 28, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "Should be more prominently annotated that these are WHITE BULBS only. No Color."}
{"Author": "George Wilson", "Date": "on July 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Totally fun and they work smoothly with my Echo and Alexa!"}
{"Author": "mash", "Date": "on July 26, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dirty sticky bulb received", "Text": "One of the bulbs was dirty and sticky. You can see it in the picture; there's a faint watermark where the stickiness is. Pretty terrible for a light that costs a fortune. The other one works great, but if I'm going to pay this much for lights I don't want a dirty used bulb."}
